n/results/LS-002-codex.yaml\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/z_archive/007-sk-code-motion-dev-and-playbook/005-playbook-cross-cli-execution/results/RD-002-codex.yaml\n\n(Results are truncated: showing first 100 results. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"count":100,"truncated":true},"title":"","time":{"start":1784521035080,"end":1784521035184}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c5ef903b45d401f016a5da14ad3f08191b6db3c8a255de0de"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe0d240014wAOB26fIyVFiA","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbde8c3001vs6wcmqYbiB02a"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521035308,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"call_6fsFWsOXO60uCYKb1v9NqIzC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":".opencode/**/*.yml"},"output":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/003-memory-and-causal-runtime/003-embedder-testing-and-architecture/001-local-embeddings-foundation/009-cocoindex-ipc-fix/scratch/coco-home/global_settings.yml\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/z_archive/020-mcp-working-memory-hybrid-rag/scratch/graphrag-hybrid/docker-compose.yml","metadata":{"count":2,"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1784521035089,"end":1784521035306}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c5ef903b45d401f016a5da14ad3f88191a41f37dbb6336617"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe0d4c001hVJeA5fpJWxk1R","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbde8c3001vs6wcmqYbiB02a"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784521036783,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"id":"prt_f7dbe13eb001ik5NUGqTUKtkXz","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","messageID":"msg_f7dbde8c3001vs6wcmqYbiB02a","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":40765,"input":7157,"output":290,"reasoning":38,"cache":{"write":0,"read":33280}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784521041842,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"id":"prt_f7dbe27af001ugZhP7zLBLrd9n","messageID":"msg_f7dbe18e1001iLWanfjjjrWO3I","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521046363,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"call_cfCCORictiikYPRPkU6MfTK4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"cli-opencode"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"cli-opencode\">\n# Skill: cli-opencode\n\n<!-- Keywords: opencode, opencode-cli, opencode-run, cross-ai, spec-kit-runtime, plugin-runtime, parallel-sessions, share-url, detached-session, agent-delegation, deepseek, openai, minimax, minimax-coding-plan, minimax-m3, token-plan, xiaomi, xiaomi-token-plan, xiaomi-token-plan-ams, xiaomi-api, xiaomi-direct, mimo, mimo-v2.5-pro, mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed, ultraspeed, glm-5.2, zai-coding-plan, z.ai-coding-plan, glm-coding-plan -->\n\n# OpenCode CLI Orchestrator - Full-Runtime Cross-AI Dispatch\n\n> **CRITICAL — SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED**\n>\n> This skill dispatches to the OpenCode CLI binary (`opencode`). If the agent currently reading this skill is itself running inside OpenCode (TUI / acp / serve / run modes — detection signals listed in §2), the skill MUST refuse to load and return the documented error message instead of generating any `opencode` invocation. The only exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory.\n>\n> A running CLI skill never dispatches itself. The cli-X skills are for **cross-AI delegation only** — never self-invocation.\n\nOrchestrate OpenCode's `opencode run` from external AI assistants (Claude Code, OpenCode, raw shell) AND from inside an existing OpenCode session for parallel detached workers. Three documented use cases keep the cycle risk explicit while giving every dispatch path a copy-paste invocation shape.\n\n**Core Principle**: The calling AI stays the conductor. Delegate to OpenCode for what it does best — full plugin, skill, MCP, and Spec Kit Memory runtime in a one-shot dispatch. Validate and integrate the output.\n\n---\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### Activation Triggers\n\n- **Full plugin / skill / MCP runtime** (use case 1) — calling AI is Claude Code / OpenCode / Copilot / raw shell AND the task needs the project's full Spec Kit Memory database, Code Graph semantic index, structural code graph, or every plugin/skill/MCP tool in a one-shot dispatch. Includes `@deep-research` / `@deep-review` agent loops with externalized state under `.opencode/specs/`.\n- **Parallel detached session** (use case 2) — operator already inside OpenCode (TUI / web / serve / acp) AND wants a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory for ablation, worker farm, or parallel research. Prompt explicitly mentions \"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", or \"share URL\".\n- **Cross-AI orchestration handback** (use case 3) — calling AI is non-Anthropic (OpenCode / Copilot), task targets a project-specific subsystem (spec-kit, memory, code-graph, advisor), and the non-Anthropic CLI cannot load the project's plugin/skill/MCP runtime on its own and needs OpenCode as a bridge. When the caller only needs a daemon-backed tool call, prefer the shipped front doors (`spec-memory.cjs`, `code-index.cjs`, `skill-advisor.cjs`) over a full `opencode run` delegation.\n- **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent. Primary agents (directly invokable via `--agent`): `general`, `plan` (built-in), `orchestrate`. Generic subagents fully dispatched via the orchestrate primary: `context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`, `ai-council`. Command-owned loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are owned end-to-end by their parent `/deep:*` command; `orchestrate` may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to a recognized loop request, but never manages the loop itself. See §3 \"OpenCode Agent Delegation\" for the full contract.\n- **Cross-repo dispatch** — session in repo A dispatches into repo B's plugin/skill/MCP runtime via `--dir <path>` or remote OpenCode server via `--attach <url>`.\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- **You ARE OpenCode already.** If your runtime is OpenCode (detection signal: `$OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` or any `OPENCODE_*` env var set, `opencode` in process ancestry, or `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` present), this skill refuses to load. Self-invocation creates a circular dispatch loop and burns tokens for no value. The cli-X family is exclusively for cross-AI delegation. The single legitimate exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session id and state directory (use case 2); without that qualifier, the smart router refuses per ADR-001.\n- Simple, quick tasks where `opencode run` overhead is not worth it.\n- Tasks that only need a raw model dispatch — use a sibling cli-* skill.\n- Tasks requiring interactive TUI or web UI (use `opencode` directly instead of `opencode run`).\n- Context already loaded and understood by the calling AI.\n- Tasks where the OpenCode binary is not installed at the expected path.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Prerequisite Detection\n\n```bash\n# Verify OpenCode CLI is available\ncommand -v opencode || echo \"Not installed. Run: brew install opencode (macOS) or curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash\"\n```\n\n### Self-Invocation Guard (ADR-001)\n\nBefore any dispatch, run the layered ADR-001 detection: Layer 1 env-var lookup for any `OPENCODE_*`, Layer 2 process-ancestry probe for an `opencode` parent, Layer 3 a best-effort `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` probe. A positive on any layer refuses the dispatch unless the prompt carries explicit parallel-session keywords (use case 2), which permits a SEPARATE session id and state directory instead. Full bash + python detection: [`references/self-invocation-guard.md`](./references/self-invocation-guard.md). Decision tree + refusal text: [`references/integration-patterns.md`](./references/integration-patterns.md) §5.\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level       | When to Load            | Resources                      |\n| ----------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------ |\n| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation  | `references/cli-reference.md`, `assets/prompt-quality-card.md` |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Intent-mapped reference docs   |\n| ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request| Extended templates and patterns |\n\n### Smart Router\n\nIntent-specific dictionaries (used by the shared helper functions in [`system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared-smart-router.md`](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared-smart-router.md)):\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively scans existing `references/` and `assets/` folders with `base.exists()` safeguards.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` uses `_guard_in_skill()`, `inventory`, and `seen` so raw loads, missing files, duplicate loads, and path escapes are rejected.\n- Pattern 3: Not applicable here - `cli-opencode` has flat resource folders, not keyed `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` subdirectories. Routing selects from `RESOURCE_MAP` by intent signal rather than by runtime resource key.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - low-confidence intent scores return `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` with a disambiguation checklist; missing intent resources still return always-load baseline docs plus a clear notice.\n\n```python\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"EXTERNAL_DISPATCH\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate to opencode\", \"opencode run\", \"from claude code\", \"from opencode\", \"from copilot\", \"external runtime\", \"full plugin runtime\", \"hand this off to opencode\", \"hand off to opencode\", \"send this to opencode\", \"dispatch to opencode\", \"run this through opencode\", \"let opencode handle this\", \"opencode's full runtime\", \"full runtime dispatch\", \"one-shot dispatch\", \"invoke opencode\", \"kick this off in opencode\", \"have opencode take care of this\", \"get opencode to run this\", \"pass this over to opencode\", \"opencode has access to every tool\", \"opencode has the whole toolchain\", \"since opencode has all the plugins\", \"opencode can load every skill\", \"ask opencode to handle this\", \"opencode should handle this\", \"offload this to opencode\", \"outsource this to opencode\", \"forward this to opencode\", \"route this to opencode\", \"push this to opencode\", \"opencode has everything loaded\", \"opencode has the whole toolset\", \"opencode cli\", \"run externally\", \"full toolset\", \"handle this externally\", \"external ai assistant\", \"run in opencode\", \"hand off externally\"]},\n    \"PARALLEL_DETACHED\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", \"share url\", \"share-url\", \"detached session\", \"separate session id\", \"own state directory\", \"spin up a new session\", \"background opencode session\", \"run this in the background\", \"fan out workers\", \"concurrent sessions\", \"isolated session\", \"run these in parallel\", \"spin off a few workers\", \"kick off several sessions at once\", \"run copies side by side\", \"fire off multiple runs at the same time\", \"farm this out to multiple workers\", \"run a bunch of these concurrently\", \"distribute the work across sessions\", \"batch this across sessions\", \"start several sessions at once\", \"spin up another instance\", \"new opencode instance\", \"run it as its own session\", \"own separate session\", \"side session\", \"run this independently\", \"additional worker\", \"background job\", \"separate instance\", \"own instance\", \"parallel run\", \"concurrent run\", \"session of its own\", \"spin up a worker\", \"worker pool\", \"run in parallel\"]},\n    \"CROSS_AI_HANDBACK\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"spec kit\", \"spec-kit\", \"spec_kit\", \"code graph\", \"memory_search\", \"session_bootstrap\", \"skill advisor\", \"cross-ai handback\", \"hand back to opencode\", \"bridge back to opencode\", \"opencode as a bridge\", \"non-anthropic cli\", \"project's memory database\", \"structural code index\", \"use the skill advisor\"]},\n    \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate\", \"agent\", \"deep-research\", \"deep-review\", \"ai-council\", \"review agent\", \"context agent\", \"dispatch an agent\", \"spawn an agent\", \"run a subagent\", \"invoke a subagent\", \"specialized subagent\", \"debug agent\", \"write agent\"]},\n    \"CROSS_REPO\":         {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"cross-repo\", \"different repo\", \"--dir\", \"another repository\", \"remote opencode\", \"different repository\", \"target repo\", \"other codebase\", \"separate repository\", \"remote opencode server\", \"--attach\"]},\n    \"TEMPLATES\":          {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"template\", \"prompt\", \"how to ask\", \"opencode prompt\", \"minimax\", \"MiniMax-M3\", \"tidd-ec\", \"prompt framework\", \"prompt template\", \"how do i phrase this\", \"copy-paste template\", \"prompt quality\", \"prompt craft\", \"costar framework\", \"example prompt\"]},\n    \"PATTERNS\":           {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"pattern\", \"workflow\", \"orchestrate\", \"session continue\", \"resume session\", \"integration pattern\", \"dispatch pattern\", \"continue the session\", \"resume a session\", \"session continuation\"]},\n    # WHY: DESIGN is an intent signal only — a deliberate cross-skill handoff to sk-design,\n    # not a same-skill resource bundle. It intentionally has NO RESOURCE_MAP entry: this skill\n    # hands design work off rather than owning design reference docs. The durable sk-design\n    # loading contract lives in the always-fires Design Standards Loading rule and the dispatch\n    # manifest (see ALWAYS rules 13-14); RESOURCE_MAP stays limited to same-skill markdown paths.\n    \"DESIGN\":             {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"sk-design\", \"interface design\", \"frontend design\", \"visual design\", \"redesign the ui\", \"design foundations\", \"design tokens\", \"motion design\", \"micro-interactions\", \"design audit\", \"ui critique\", \"extract design system\", \"generate design.md\"]},\n}\n\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"EXTERNAL_DISPATCH\":  [\"references/cli-reference.md\", \"references/integration-patterns.md\"],\n    \"PARALLEL_DETACHED\":  [\"references/integration-patterns.md\", \"assets/prompt-templates.md\"],\n    \"CROSS_AI_HANDBACK\":  [\"references/integration-patterns.md\", \"references/opencode-tools.md\"],\n    \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     [\"references/agent-delegation.md\", \"assets/prompt-templates.md\"],\n    \"CROSS_REPO\":         [\"references/cli-reference.md\", \"references/opencode-tools.md\"],\n    \"TEMPLATES\":          [\"assets/prompt-templates.md\", \"references/cli-reference.md\"],\n    \"PATTERNS\":           [\"references/integration-patterns.md\", \"references/cli-reference.md\"],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\": [\"references/cli-reference.md\", \"assets/prompt-quality-card.md\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full reference\", \"all templates\", \"deep dive\", \"complete guide\", \"opencode agent\", \"opencode prompt\", \"share url\", \"ablation\", \"worker farm\", \"self-invocation\", \"memory handback\", \"minimax\", \"MiniMax-M3\", \"tidd-ec\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\": [\"references/opencode-tools.md\", \"assets/prompt-templates.md\"],\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Is the user asking about OpenCode CLI specifically?\",\n    \"Does the task need the project's full plugin / skill / MCP runtime?\",\n    \"Is a parallel detached session what they want?\",\n    \"Is a non-Anthropic CLI handing back to OpenCode for a spec-kit workflow?\",\n]\n```\n\n**Call sequence** (using shared helpers from `shared-smart-router.md`):\n\n1. `discover_markdown_resources()` — recursively enumerate current `.md` files under existing `references/` and `assets/` folders at routing time.\n2. `_guard_in_skill()` + `load_if_available()` — sandbox paths to this skill, reject non-markdown loads, skip missing files, and suppress duplicates.\n3. `score_intents(task)` and `select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)` — preserve provider-specific weighted intent scoring and top-2 ambiguity handling.\n4. ALWAYS-load `LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]`, then return `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` with `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST` when max score is 0.\n5. CONDITIONAL-load existing `RESOURCE_MAP[intent]` entries via `load_if_available()`, ON_DEMAND-load keyword matches, and return a notice when no intent-specific knowledge base is available beyond always-load resources.\n\nThe `route_opencode_resources(task)` function body lives in [`shared-smart-router.md`](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared-smart-router.md) — substitute `<PROVIDER>` = `opencode`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n```bash\n# Verify installation (cli-opencode v1.0.0 is pinned to opencode v1.3.17)\nopencode --version | grep -q '^1\\.' || echo \"Not installed or version drift. See references/cli-reference.md §9.\"\n\n# Self-invocation guard\nenv | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"ERROR: Already inside OpenCode session\"\n\n# Authentication — providers configured via opencode providers (alias auth)\nopencode providers\n```\n\n**Authentication options**: `opencode providers login <provider>` (and `opencode auth login` for subscription plans). Full per-provider login shapes and the configured-provider list: `references/cli-reference.md` §4.\n\n### Provider Auth Pre-Flight (Smart Fallback)\n\n**MANDATORY before any first dispatch in a session.** The default provider may not be logged in — silently failing with `provider/model not found` or `401 Unauthorized` mid-dispatch wastes a round-trip. Run the pre-flight once per session, cache the result, and re-run only on an auth failure.\n\nThe one-shot pre-flight bash, the per-provider decision trees, the user-facing prompt templates for missing providers, and the error-recovery contract live in [`references/cli-reference.md`](./references/cli-reference.md) §4 — do not duplicate them here. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve; ASK when the default is unavailable.\n\n### Default Invocation (Skill Default)\n\n**Default model + variant + format + dir**: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` · `--variant high` · `--format json` · `--dir <repo-root>` (pinned to avoid CWD ambiguity). Direct DeepSeek is the default provider — elevated reasoning at low cost for routine dispatches.\n\nUse `opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root> \"<prompt>\"`.\n\n> **The `--agent` flag (read this):** Do NOT pass `--agent` on a top-level `opencode run` — current opencode treats named agents like `general` as **subagents** and rejects them at the top level, so `--agent general` fails outright. The default agent runs when `--agent` is omitted, which is correct for almost every dispatch. **To target a specific agent profile, describe the role in the prompt body instead** (e.g. open with \"Act as a code-review agent: …\"); only pass `--agent <name>` after confirming acceptance via `opencode run --help` on the installed version.\n\nHonor explicit user model, port, and handback phrasing verbatim; otherwise use the default invocation above.\n\n### Core Invocation Pattern\n\nCore flags: `--model`, `--agent`, `--variant`, `--format json`, `--dir`, continuation/session/fork flags, `--share` and `--port` for detached sessions, `--file`, `--thinking`, `--pure`, and log flags.\n\n> **Non-interactive invocation stdin**: always append `</dev/null` to any non-interactive `opencode run` invocation — without it, opencode can inherit parent-terminal stdin and hang. See `references/integration-patterns.md` §6.\n\n> **Registered command dispatch (`--command`)**: slash-command text inside a `run` message is NOT expanded — `opencode run \"/memory:search query\"` delivers the slash text as raw prose. Execute a registered command via `opencode run --command <family>/<name> [flags] \"<args>\"` (becomes `$ARGUMENTS`; e.g. `memory/search` for `/memory:search`). Full semantics: `references/cli-reference.md` §4.\n\n### Model Selection\n\nRun `opencode providers list` to confirm credentials and `opencode models <provider>` for live choices. Default: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` (direct DeepSeek API). Alternates (all omit `--agent`): MiniMax Token Plan/Direct API `MiniMax-M3`, Xiaomi Token Plan/Direct API `mimo-v2.5-pro` (+ low-latency `-ultraspeed`), Kimi For Coding `k2p7` (256k, subscription), Z.AI GLM Coding Plan `glm-5.2` (1M, subscription), and the OpenAI GPT-5.6 catalog (`gpt-5.6-sol` flagship default; bare/Sol/Terra/Luna x base/Fast/Pro, `--variant` up to `xhigh`). Full model table, per-provider `--variant` mapping, and model-specific operational caveats: `references/cli-reference.md` §5.\n\nShared small-model facts, context defaults, quota pools, and fallback targets live in `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/model-profiles.json`.\n\n### OpenCode Agent Delegation\n\nThe calling AI is the conductor. OpenCode distinguishes **primary agents** (directly invokable via `--agent <slug>`) from **subagents** (dispatched as Task-tool subagents from a primary).\n\n#### Primary agents — directly invokable via `--agent`\n\nOpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Never pass `--agent general`** — it is rejected at the top level; the default agent (used when `--agent` is omitted) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n\n#### Subagents — dispatched as Task subagents from a primary\n\nThese live at `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` with `mode: subagent` and are NOT directly invokable via `opencode run --agent`. Three dispatch surfaces are legal under the single-hop NDP contract:\n\n1. **Generic subagents** (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) — dispatched by `orchestrate` via the Task tool. Route through `--agent orchestrate` and let it dispatch the relevant subagent.\n2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched via `/deep:ai-council` or `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`).\n3. **Command-owned loop executors** (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) — LOOP-OWNED by their parent commands (`/deep:research`, `/deep:review`, `/deep:agent-improvement`, `/prompt`), which own iteration state, convergence detection, and continuity. Never dispatch these directly via raw `--agent <slug>`. `orchestrate` is an authorized **caller/coordinator only** — it may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to the resolved leaf, but MUST NOT re-implement the loop.\n\nSee [agent-delegation.md](./references/agent-delegation.md) for the complete agent roster and dispatch patterns.\n\n### Unique OpenCode Strengths\n\nFull project runtime loading, detached sessions, JSON event streams, agent routing, cross-repo/server dispatch, session continuation, and plugin-disable debugging.\n\n### Essential Commands\n\nDefault invocation for external runtime handback; `--share --port <N>` only for explicit detached sessions; `--agent orchestrate` for generic subagent routing; `--dir` for cross-repo dispatch.\n\n### Error Handling\n\nInstall missing binaries, refuse ambiguous self-invocation, run provider pre-flight for model/auth errors, check version drift for unknown flags, force `--format json` for empty streams, add `</dev/null` for background loops, confirm `--share`, use `--pure` only for plugin crashes, inspect state logs for stuck sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ✅ ALWAYS\n\n1. Verify OpenCode CLI is installed before first invocation; confirm version baseline against v1.3.17 (drift handling per `references/cli-reference.md` §9).\n2. **Run the self-invocation guard before dispatch** (ADR-001): Layer 1 env-var lookup for any `OPENCODE_*`, Layer 2 process-ancestry probe for `opencode` parent, Layer 3 `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` probe. Trip on ANY positive — refuse unless prompt has explicit parallel-session keywords.\n3. Pin model + variant + format + dir explicitly — **no `--agent`** (see the Default Invocation note: current opencode rejects a top-level `--agent general`; put any agent-profile request in the prompt body). Default: `--model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root>`. Honor user overrides verbatim (e.g. `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`, `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`, `minimax/MiniMax-M3`, `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro`).\n4. Pass `--format json` unless the calling AI explicitly wants formatted output — JSON event stream is what external runtimes parse incrementally.\n5. **Append `</dev/null` to every non-interactive `opencode run` invocation** that redirects stdout and/or stderr to files OR runs inside `while read` loops. opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation; without explicit closed stdin, automation hangs forever at 0% CPU after the `+60s service=snapshot prune=7.days cleanup` log line. Position: AFTER the prompt positional argument, BEFORE the `> stdout 2> stderr` redirects. Foreground `| tail` happens to provide closed stdin (pipe stage upstream is empty) and accidentally bypasses the bug, but `> stdout.log 2> stderr.log` does not. The 9-character `</dev/null` redirect provides immediate EOF on stdin, unblocking the dispatch. **DO NOT auto-kill external operator-owned opencode sessions** when sweeping orphans between dispatches; exclude `opencode run` from pkill (per 2026-05-23 operator directive captured in memory `feedback_proactive_orphan_cleanup.md`). See `references/integration-patterns.md` §6 + memory `feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md` + CHANGELOG-2026-05-08-tool-name-regex-fix.md §Fix 4.\n6. **Pass the spec folder to the dispatched session** in the prompt: if the calling AI has an active Gate-3 spec folder, include `Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)`. If none, ASK the user before delegating — the dispatched session cannot answer Gate 3 interactively in non-interactive `run` mode.\n7. **Prompt construction & model-craft (cli-* family precedence).** Compose every dispatch prompt via the 3-tier rule canonical in `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md`:\n   1. **Fast path (default).** Build from the local `assets/prompt-quality-card.md`, which delegates the framework table + CLEAR check to the canonical card.\n   2. **Model override (mandatory for a profiled model).** If the target model has a profile at `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/<id>.md`, that profile OVERRIDES the cross-model default. The **sk-prompt/prompt-models** hub owns per-model prompt-craft (framework + scaffold + gotchas, mirroring `sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/model-profiles.json` `recommended_frameworks`); consult it before composing for any small model.\n   3. **Deep path (escalation).** Dispatch `@prompt-improver` via the Task tool (never load full `sk-prompt` inline) when any canonical **Tier 3** trigger applies — the trigger list lives in `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md` under \"Tier 3 — Deep path\"; do not re-enumerate it here.\n8. Validate dispatched session output: parse JSON events incrementally (tool calls, partial messages, final summary), run syntax checks if code generated, and cross-reference against project standards via `sk-code` surface detection plus its code-review mode when findings-first review is requested (see ALWAYS rule 12).\n9. Capture stderr (`2>&1`) to catch tool errors and warnings.\n10. Classify the use case (1 / 2 / 3) before dispatching — the smart router refuses dispatches that do not map to one of the three.\n11. **Run the Provider Auth Pre-Flight once per session** (see §3 Provider Auth Pre-Flight). Cache the configured-providers list. If the default `deepseek` is missing, ASK the user — never silently substitute the model. If a later dispatch returns an auth error, invalidate the cache and rerun the pre-flight before retrying.\n12. **Code Standards Loading (surface-aware contract)** — When dispatching for code review or code generation, instruct the dispatched session to: (1) load `sk-code`; (2) let `sk-code` emit a surface tag matching the detected stack from markers and target files; (3) load the selected surface resources and run its verification commands; (4) load `sk-code`'s code-review mode only for formal findings-first review output. Fallback: if the surface cannot be determined confidently, ask for the runtime surface and verification command set. NEVER hardcode obsolete sibling code skills in dispatch prompts.\n13. **Design Standards Loading (surface-aware contract)** — When dispatching for design or UI work, instruct the dispatched session to: (1) load `sk-design` (the hub); (2) let the hub resolve a `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json` (interface / foundations / motion / audit / md-generator / design-mcp-open-design); (3) load the selected mode packet, set the design register, and run that mode's design verification; (4) if the work feeds Open Design, carry the `design-mcp-open-design` pairing (a nested transport packet of the hub) — the transport never decides taste. Fallback: if the design mode cannot be determined confidently, ask for the surface and design intent. NEVER treat `mcp-figma` or `design-mcp-open-design` as the taste authority, or hardcode obsolete flat design skills in dispatch prompts.\n14. **Pass the design dispatch manifest to the dispatched session** — when dispatching design or UI work, inline a `DESIGN_DISPATCH_MANIFEST v1` block in the prompt (the child cannot resolve skill paths, so the manifest travels in the payload, not by reference): `skDesignLoaded` true, `register` resolved to `Brand` or `Product` (never `unknown`), registry-valid `workflowModes`, `dials`, `loadedFiles`, and `proofDemandBack`. If the manifest cannot be assembled — `sk-design` not loaded, register unresolved, or no registry-valid mode — ASK before launching the child rather than starting a silent design dispatch. The child returns the demanded proof; the parent reconciles it on the return path.\n15. **Destructive-scope-violation prevention (RM-8) for deep-loop dispatches** — The structured permissions-matrix gate (`permissions-gate.ts`; schema and design in `references/permissions-matrix.md`) is built and unit-tested but has ZERO production callers today — no `opencode run` dispatch path invokes it, so a loaded `--permissions-matrix <path>` config or recipe field is NOT currently enforced and does NOT bypass anything. Regardless of whether a matrix config is present, any non-interactive `opencode run` with `--dangerously-skip-permissions` against a populated worktree MUST apply the four-layer mitigation — it is the only active protection today: (L1) rendered prompt contains literal `BANNED OPERATIONS` and `ALLOWED WRITE PATHS`; (L2) `--dir` points at a fresh `git worktree`; (L3) main `git status` clean OR committed, recovery-baseline commit hash recorded; (L4) for multi-phase / phase-parent targets, prefer `cli-copilot` + `gpt-5.6-sol --reasoning-effort high` (verify `gpt-5.6-sol` availability on the Copilot surface — unverified, carried over from a gpt-5.5-era check; if absent, pick an available Copilot model, don't silently fall back to the risky default) over `deepseek-v4-pro`. Background: on 2026-05-04 an `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` dispatch under `/deep:review:auto` deleted 44 files across two phase folders because the only safeguard was prose and `--dangerously-skip-permissions` granted unrestricted FS write. Full incident + root cause + checklist: `references/destructive-scope-violations.md`.\n16. **Single-dispatch discipline (operator-gated, session-scoped)** — Default: launch ONE cli-* dispatch at a time across the cli-* family (cli-opencode, cli-claude-code). Wait for the dispatched agent's work to return, verify outputs exist, then SIGKILL only the dispatch THIS skill started: capture its PID at launch (`opencode run ... & OC_PID=$!`) and kill that captured PID directly plus its own orphan children (`kill -9 \"$OC_PID\" 2>/dev/null; pkill -9 -P \"$OC_PID\" 2>/dev/null`), then apply the same PID-scoped `gtimeout` / `positional_scoring_fallback:app` cleanup. (A backgrounded `opencode run &` is NOT a process-group leader unless launched with `setsid`/`set -m`, so a negative-PID group kill would target a nonexistent group and miss the process — kill the captured PID directly.) **Kill only the dispatch you started, by captured PID; never a blanket `pkill -9 -f \"opencode run\"` pattern — see Rule 5** (a blanket match kills operator-owned `opencode run` sessions too). Only launch the next dispatch (this skill OR a sibling) after the prior one is dead and RSS has dropped. **Within a deep-flow session** (deep-review / deep-research): the operator authorizes the whole multi-iteration session at start — iterations chain back-to-back with kill-between as the safety mechanism, NOT a per-iteration operator confirmation prompt. **Exception (cross-skill parallel)**: when the operator explicitly authorizes N parallel dispatches, run N concurrently — but still SIGKILL each by its own captured PID as its work returns.\n17. **Set `AI_SESSION_CHILD=1` in the dispatched session's env** when sessions may be launched through the per-session worktree wrapper (`.opencode/bin/worktree-session.sh`). A dispatched `opencode run` is an orchestrated sub-session, not a new top-level session, so it must SHARE the parent's worktree rather than allocate its own. The wrapper checks `AI_SESSION_CHILD` (plus a `git --git-common-dir` structural backstop) and exec's in place when set. Pattern: `AI_SESSION_CHILD=1 opencode run ... </dev/null`. Harmless when the wrapper is not in use. See `.opencode/bin/README.md` → \"Worktree session isolation\". Prepend `MK_SPEC_GATE_ENFORCE=0` next to it so a dispatched child never inherits an enforced spec-gate from the parent shell (belt-and-suspenders alongside the wrapper's own neutralization and the core's `AI_SESSION_CHILD` deny-narrowing): `MK_SPEC_GATE_ENFORCE=0 AI_SESSION_CHILD=1 opencode run ... </dev/null`.\n\n### ⛔ NEVER\n\n1. Invoke this skill from within OpenCode itself for a self-dispatch — refuse with the documented error message; use a sibling cli-* / fresh shell / parallel-session keywords.\n2. Pass `--share` without operator confirmation (CHK-033) — share URL exposes session contents.\n3. Trust dispatched session output blindly for security-sensitive code, send sensitive data (API keys, passwords, credentials) in prompts, or hammer the API with rapid sequential calls.\n4. Use `--pure` outside of plugin debugging (disabling plugins removes the entire point of cli-opencode dispatch).\n5. Nest `opencode run` inside a dispatched session's tool calls — use OpenCode's native Task tool for sub-agent dispatch.\n\n### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n\n1. OpenCode CLI is not installed and user has not acknowledged (provide `brew install opencode` or `curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash`).\n2. Operator wants to publish a `--share` URL — get explicit confirmation per CHK-033.\n3. Binary version differs from the v1.3.17 baseline — run `opencode --version` and `opencode run --help`; surface drift and fall back or require approval.\n4. Smart router cannot map the prompt to one of the three use cases — surface the disambiguation checklist from UNKNOWN_FALLBACK.\n5. Self-invocation guard trips AND the prompt is ambiguous — surface the refusal with three remediation options (sibling cli-* / fresh shell / parallel-session keywords).\n\n### Memory Handback Protocol\n\nWhen the calling AI needs to preserve session context from an OpenCode CLI delegation, run the canonical 7-step procedure (extract `MEMORY_HANDBACK` section → build structured JSON → scrub secrets → invoke `generate-context.js` via `--stdin`/`--json`/temp-file → `memory_index_scan`). Full procedure and caveats: [`system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md`](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md).\n\nFor read-only or hook-style recovery, use the daemon-backed CLI front doors instead of spawning OpenCode: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool>`, `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool>`, or `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs <tool>`. Prompt-time paths must probe warm sockets or pass `--warm-only`; exit `75` is retryable daemon/IPC unavailability, not a model failure.\n\nOpenCode-specific Memory Epilogue template: see [assets/prompt-templates.md](./assets/prompt-templates.md) §14.\n\nExample invocation:\n```bash\nprintf '%s' \"$JSON_PAYLOAD\" | node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --stdin [spec-folder]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\n### Core References\n\n- [cli-reference.md](./references/cli-reference.md) - Full subcommand/flag reference, provider auth pre-flight, models, version drift\n- [integration-patterns.md](./references/integration-patterns.md) - 3 use cases, decision tree, silent stdin\n- [self-invocation-guard.md](./references/self-invocation-guard.md) - ADR-001 layered bash + python detection contract\n- [opencode-tools.md](./references/opencode-tools.md) - Unique value props vs sibling cli-* skills\n- [agent-delegation.md](./references/agent-delegation.md) - Agent routing matrix, leaf-agent constraints\n- [destructive-scope-violations.md](./references/destructive-scope-violations.md) - RM-8 incident, root cause, four-layer prevention playbook\n\n### Templates and Assets\n\n- [prompt-templates.md](./assets/prompt-templates.md) - Copy-paste templates per use case + agent + handback\n- [prompt-quality-card.md](./assets/prompt-quality-card.md) - Executor-specific model overrides; delegates framework/CLEAR check to canonical card\n\n### Shared (cli-* family)\n- [shared-smart-router.md](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared-smart-router.md) - Helper-function bodies for the smart router.\n- [memory-handback.md](../../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory-handback.md) - Canonical 7-step Memory Handback procedure.\n\n### External\n- [OpenCode GitHub](https://github.com/sst/opencode) - Official repository\n- [OpenCode Install](https://opencode.ai/install) - Standalone installer entry point\n- [OpenCode Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs) - Official docs\n\n### Reference Loading Notes\n\n- Load only references needed for current intent.\n- Smart Routing (Section 2) is the single routing authority.\n- `cli-reference.md` and `prompt-quality-card.md` are ALWAYS loaded as baseline.\n- The router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically — task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n\n### Related Skills\n\n`cli-claude-code` and `cli-opencode` for sibling cross-AI dispatch; `system-spec-kit` for handback; `sk-code` plus the selected overlay for generated code; `system-deep-loop` for loop execution (its `research` and `review` modes); and `mcp-code-mode` for MCP-backed tools.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Task Completion\n\n- OpenCode CLI invoked with the correct subcommand, flags, model, agent, variant, format, and dir.\n- Self-invocation guard checked before dispatch — refused when appropriate.\n- Use case (1 / 2 / 3) classified explicitly before invocation.\n- JSON event stream captured, parsed incrementally, validated, integrated.\n- No security vulnerabilities introduced from generated code.\n- `--share` URLs opt-in with operator confirmation per CHK-033.\n- Background dispatches in `while read` loops include `</dev/null` redirect.\n- Memory Handback extracted and saved through `generate-context.js` when applicable.\n\n### Skill Quality\n\n- All numbered sections present and correctly ordered.\n- Smart routing covers all intent signals with UNKNOWN_FALLBACK.\n- Reference files provide deep-dive content without duplication.\n- Self-invocation guard pseudocode reproduced in Section 2 mirrors ADR-001.\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in [AGENTS.md](../../../../AGENTS.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via the Skill Advisor Hook (or `skill_advisor.py` fallback)\n- **Tool Routing**: Per AGENTS.md Section 6 decision tree\n- **Memory**: Context preserved via Spec Kit Memory MCP (`generate-context.js`)\n- **Validation**: `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh` for spec-folder workflows\n\n**Tool roles**: Bash dispatches the CLI; Read/Glob/Grep validate output and probe `~/.opencode/state/` for session locks.\n\nBase directory for this skill: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode\nRelative paths in this skill (e.g., scripts/, reference/) are relative to this base directory.\nNote: file list is sampled.\n\n<skill_files>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/README.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.example-packet-local.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.example-readonly.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.schema.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/prompt-quality-card.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/prompt-templates.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/permissions-matrix.example-repo-wide.json</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/context-budget.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/self-invocation-guard.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/opencode-tools.md</file>\n</skill_files>\n</skill_content>","metadata":{"name":"cli-opencode","dir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode","truncated":false},"title":"Loaded skill: cli-opencode","time":{"start":1784521046351,"end":1784521046362}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0055fd45339e5f5e016a5da155bf908191a573e0daf020de98"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe3870001R9059te52LQqtO","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe18e1001iLWanfjjjrWO3I"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784521047452,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"id":"prt_f7dbe3d99001kuDrfM95L2ypm3","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","messageID":"msg_f7dbe18e1001iLWanfjjjrWO3I","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":63008,"input":23513,"output":21,"reasoning":50,"cache":{"write":0,"read":39424}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784521051259,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"id":"prt_f7dbe4c78001ERZOaAJjjDAqhI","messageID":"msg_f7dbe41d8001jJnEYh1TJPFDC2","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521056902,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_B3rMuSA658kPKxNagxLkvlGs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47:   convergence_mode: \"[default|off|sliding-window|divergent] - Convergence policy modifier. Default: default.\"\n48: \n49: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n50: # CONTEXT LOADING\n51: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n52: context_loading:\n53:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n54:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n55:   mcp_integration:\n56:     tool: memory_context\n57:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n58:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n59:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n60:   behavior:\n61:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n62:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n63: \n64: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n65: # SKILL REFERENCE\n66: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n67: skill_reference:\n68:   skill: system-deep-loop\n69:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md\n70:   references:\n71:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md\n72:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md\n73:     state_format: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-format.md\n74:     convergence: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n75:   templates:\n76:     config: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json\n77:     strategy: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md\n78: \n79: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n80: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n81: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n82: agent_config:\n83:   agent: deep-research\n84:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n85:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n86:   model: opus\n87:   leaf_only: true\n88:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n89:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n90:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n91: \n92: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n93: # STATE FILE PATHS\n94: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n95: state_paths:\n96:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n97:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n98:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n99:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n100:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n101:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n102:   status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n103:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n104:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n105:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n106:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n107:   run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n108:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n109:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n110:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n111:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n112:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n113:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n114:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n115:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n116:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n117:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n118:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n119:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n120:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n121:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n122:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n123: \n124: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n125: # WORKFLOW\n126: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n127: workflow:\n128: \n129:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n130:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n131:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n132:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n133:     if_present:\n134:       bind:\n135:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n136:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n137:         artifact_subfolder: null\n138:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n139:     if_absent:\n140:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('./.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n141:       outputs:\n142:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n143:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n144:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n145:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n146: \n147:   step_fanout_spawn:\n148:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n149:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n150:     instructions: |\n151:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n152:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n153:       fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n154:       deep/research command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n155:       deep-research agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n156:       sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n157:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n158:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n159:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n160:     sub_steps:\n161:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n162:         description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n163:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n164:         command: |\n165:           node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n166:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n167:             --loop-type research \\\n168:             --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n169:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n170:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n171:             --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold}\n172:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n173:         wait_for_completion: true\n174: \n175:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n176:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n177:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n178:   phase_init:\n179:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n180:     steps:\n181: \n182:       step_preflight_contract:\n183:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n184:         verify:\n185:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, convergence_mode]\n186:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n187:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n188:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n189:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n190: \n191:       step_create_directories:\n192:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n193:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n194: \n195:       step_detect_resource_map:\n196:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n197:         inspect:\n198:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n199:         classify:\n200:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n201:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n202:         outputs:\n203:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n204:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n205: \n206:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n207:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n208:         inspect_legacy:\n209:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n210:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n211:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n212:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n213:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n214:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n215:         on_legacy_read:\n216:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n217: \n218:       step_acquire_lock:\n219:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n220:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n221:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n222:         note: \"Uses the promoted runtime/ loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n223:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n224:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n225:         on_halt:\n226:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n227:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n228:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n229:         on_cancel:\n230:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n231:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n232:         on_workflow_exit:\n233:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n234:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n235: \n236:       step_classify_session:\n237:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n238:         inspect:\n239:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n240:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n241:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n242:         classify:\n243:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n244:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n245:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n246:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n247:         outputs:\n248:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n249:         on_resume:\n250:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n251:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n252:           gate3_classification: write-path\n253:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n254:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n255:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n256:           skip_to: phase_loop\n257:         on_restart:\n258:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n259:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n260:           set:\n261:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n262:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n263:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n264:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n265:           skip_to: step_create_config\n266:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n267:         on_completed_session:\n268:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n269:           halt: true\n270:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n271:         on_invalid_state:\n272:           halt: true\n273:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n274:         on_fresh:\n275:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n276: \n277:       step_resolve_session_id:\n278:         action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n279:         branch_on: \"session_id\"\n280:         if_present:\n281:           bind:\n282:             session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n283:         if_absent:\n284:           bind:\n285:             session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n286: \n287:       step_create_config:\n288:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n289:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json\n290:         populate:\n291:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n292:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n293:           minIterations: 3\n294:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n295:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n296:           antiConvergence.convergenceMode: \"{convergence_mode}\"\n297:           antiConvergence.divergent: {}\n298:           stuckThreshold: 3\n299:           minIdeaObservations: 2\n300:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n301:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n302:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n303:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n304:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n305:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n306:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n307:           status: \"initialized\"\n308:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n309:           lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n310:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n311:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n312:           lineage.generation: 1\n313:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n314:           nextRunAt: null\n315:           remainingDelayMs: null\n316:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n317: \n318:       step_create_state_log:\n319:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n320:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n321:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"{convergence_mode}\",\"divergent\":{}},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n322:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n323: \n324:       step_create_strategy:\n325:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n326:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md\n327:         populate:\n328:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n329:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n330:           known_context: \"None\"\n331:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n332:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n333:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n334:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n335: \n336:       step_create_registry:\n337:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n338:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n339:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n340: \n341:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n342:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n343:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n344:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n345:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n346: \n347:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n348:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n349:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n350:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n351: \n352:       step_detect_spec_present:\n353:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n354:         inspect:\n355:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n356:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n357:         classify:\n358:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n359:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n360:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n361:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n362:         outputs:\n363:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n364:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n365:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n366: \n367:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n368:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n369:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md\"\n370:         branches:\n371:           no-spec:\n372:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n373:             seed_markers:\n374:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n375:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n376:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n377:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n378:             set:\n379:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n380:               validate_spec_doc: true\n381:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n382:           spec-present:\n383:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n384:             set:\n385:               validate_spec_doc: true\n386:             idempotency_check:\n387:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n388:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n389:               if_match:\n390:                 skip_append: true\n391:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n392:               if_no_match:\n393:                 append_only:\n394:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n395:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n396:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n397:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n398:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n399:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n400:             verify_markers:\n401:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n402:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n403:             set:\n404:               validate_spec_doc: false\n405:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n406:           conflict-detected:\n407:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n408:             halt: true\n409: \n410:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n411:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n412:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n413:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n414:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n415: \n416:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n417:         action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n418:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n419:         canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n420:         command: |\n421:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n422:           import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n423: \n424:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n425:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n426: \n427:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n428:           const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n429:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n430:           const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n431:           const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n432:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n433:           const row = {\n434:             event: 'started',\n435:             label: 'single',\n436:             at: timestamp,\n437:             duration_ms: 0,\n438:             loop_type: 'research',\n439:             sessionId,\n440:             generation,\n441:             gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n442:           };\n443: \n444:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n445:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n446:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n447:           });\n448:           if (appended) {\n449:             try {\n450:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n451:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n452:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n453:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n454:                 event: row.event,\n455:                 status: 'running',\n456:               });\n457:             } catch {}\n458:           }\n459:           EOF\n460:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n461:         outputs:\n462:           - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n463: \n464:       step_init_complete:\n465:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n466:         set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n467: \n468:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n469:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n470:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n471:   phase_loop:\n472:     purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n473:     repeat: true\n474:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n475:     steps:\n476: \n477:       step_read_state:\n478:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n479:         read:\n480:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n481:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n482:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n483:         extract:\n484:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n485:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n486:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n487:           - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n488:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n489:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n490:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n491:           - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n492:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n493:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n494:           - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n495:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n496:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n497:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n498:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n499:           - memory_context_prompt_line: \"If a refreshed memory context summary exists from the previous iteration, return 'Memory context refresh: {summary}'. Else use prior_context_summary from startup when available; otherwise return 'Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.'\"\n500:           - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n501:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n502:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n503:           - nextRunAt: \"Extract nullable nextRunAt from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n504:           - remainingDelayMs: \"Extract nullable remainingDelayMs from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n505:           - min_iterations_present: \"Boolean true when deep-research-config.json has a numeric minIterations field\"\n506:           - min_iterations_missing_warning: \"Boolean true when minIterations is missing; use no floor and log a warning so older configs keep prior stop behavior\"\n507:           - min_iterations_raw: \"Extract numeric minIterations from deep-research-config.json when present, default 0\"\n508:           - effective_min_iterations: \"Clamp min_iterations_raw to the inclusive range 0..max_iterations; if min_iterations_raw exceeds max_iterations, use max_iterations\"\n509:           - min_iterations_clamped: \"Boolean true when min_iterations_raw > max_iterations\"\n510:           - min_iterations_guard_already_passed: \"Boolean true when state_log already contains event == 'min_iterations_guard_pass'\"\n511:           - convergence_mode: \"Extract antiConvergence.convergenceMode when it is one of 'default', 'off', 'sliding-window', or 'divergent'; default to 'default'\"\n512:           - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when antiConvergence.convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n513:           - rejected_patterns_count: \"Read registry.rejectedPatterns length when registry exists, else 0\"\n514:           - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Read registry.suppressedCandidates when registry exists, else []\"\n515:           - rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold: \"Read config.rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold when present, else 0.85\"\n516:           - min_idea_observations: \"Read config.minIdeaObservations when present, default 2; clamp to 1..10\"\n517:           - observed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.observedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n518:           - promoted_ideas_count: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n519:           - promoted_ideas_list: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas idea text in rank order when registry exists, else []\"\n520:           - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.suppressedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n521:           - pivot_lineage: \"Summarize registry.divergence.completed and registry.divergence.overrides with pivot ids, source iterations, and selected focus; else 'none yet'\"\n522:           - saturated_directions: \"List registry.divergence.saturatedDirections; else 'none yet'\"\n523: \n524:       step_run_now_check:\n525:         action: \"Detect and consume a one-shot run-now sentinel before pause/convergence/dispatch\"\n526:         command: |\n527:           node <<'EOF'\n528:           const { appendFileSync, existsSync, renameSync, unlinkSync } = require('node:fs');\n529: \n530:           const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n531:           const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n532:           const pausePath = \"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\";\n533:           const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n534:           const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n535:           const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n536:           const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n537: \n538:           function append(event) {\n539:             appendFileSync(\n540:               stateLogPath,\n541:               `${JSON.stringify({\n542:                 type: \"event\",\n543:                 mode: \"research\",\n544:                 run,\n545:                 timestamp,\n546:                 sessionId,\n547:                 generation,\n548:                 ...event,\n549:               })}\\n`,\n550:               \"utf8\",\n551:             );\n552:           }\n553: \n554:           if (existsSync(sentinelPath)) {\n555:             append({ event: \"run_now_requested\", sentinelPath });\n556:             if (existsSync(pausePath)) {\n557:               append({\n558:                 event: \"run_now_rejected\",\n559:                 reason: \"loop_paused\",\n560:                 sentinelPath,\n561:                 pauseSentinelPath: pausePath,\n562:               });\n563:             } else {\n564:               const claimPath = `${sentinelPath}.consuming.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}`;\n565:               try {\n566:                 renameSync(sentinelPath, claimPath);\n567:                 unlinkSync(claimPath);\n568:                 append({\n569:                   event: \"run_now_accepted\",\n570:                   sentinelPath,\n571:                   dispatchEvent: \"iteration_start\",\n572:                 });\n573:               } catch (error) {\n574:                 if (!error || error.code !== \"ENOENT\") {\n575:                   throw error;\n576:                 }\n577:               }\n578:             }\n579:           }\n580:           EOF\n581:         outputs:\n582:           - run_now_requested: \"Emitted when {state_paths.run_now_sentinel} exists at the loop boundary\"\n583:           - run_now_accepted: \"Emitted after the sentinel is atomically renamed and deleted before dispatch\"\n584:           - run_now_rejected: \"Emitted with reason loop_paused when pause takes precedence; sentinel remains present\"\n585: \n586:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n587:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n588:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n589:         if_exists:\n590:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n591:           message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n592:           halt: true\n593:         if_not_exists:\n594:           proceed: true\n595: \n596:       step_validate_convergence_config:\n597:         action: \"Validate convergence floor settings when loading config\"\n598:         if_min_iterations_missing:\n599:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"fallback\":0,\"message\":\"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n600:           log: \"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\"\n601:         if_min_iterations_clamped:\n602:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"configured\":{min_iterations_raw},\"effective\":{effective_min_iterations},\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"message\":\"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n603:           log: \"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\"\n604:         if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n605:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n606:           log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n607: \n608:       step_graph_convergence:\n609:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n610:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\" --convergence-mode \"{convergence_mode}\"'\n611:         note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n612:         outputs:\n613:           - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n614:           - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n615:           - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n616:           - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n617:           - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n618:           - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n619:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n620: \n621:       step_check_convergence:\n622:         action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n623:         algorithm: |\n624:           1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n625:           2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n626:           3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n627:           4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n628:           5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n629:                step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n630:                The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n631:                signals = []\n632:                Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n633:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n634:                   avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n635:                   stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n636:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n637:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n638:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n639:                c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n640:                   coverage = answered / total questions\n641:                   stop if coverage >= 0.85\n642:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n643:                if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n644:                Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n645:                if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n646:                  decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n647:                  reason = \"blockedStop\"\n648:                  stop_blocked = true\n649:                  blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n650:                  blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n651:                  gate_convergence_pass = false\n652:                  gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n653:                  gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n654:                  gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n655:                  gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n656:                  gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n657:                  recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n658:                else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n659:                  decision = \"STOP\"\n660:                  reason = \"composite_converged\"\n661:                  stop_blocked = false\n662:           6. else: CONTINUE\n663:           7. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\" and effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count < effective_min_iterations:\n664:                decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n665:                reason = \"minIterationsNotReached\"\n666:                min_iterations_guard_blocked = true\n667:                min_iterations_guard_pass = false\n668:           8. if effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count >= effective_min_iterations and min_iterations_guard_already_passed == false:\n669:                min_iterations_guard_pass = true\n670:           9. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n671:                guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n672:                if not guardResult.passed:\n673:                  log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n674:                  decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n675:           See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n676:           Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n677:         outputs:\n678:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n679:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n680:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n681:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n682:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n683:           - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n684:           - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n685:           - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n686:           - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n687:           - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n688:           - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n689:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n690:           - min_iterations_guard_pass: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor has cleared for the first time\"\n691:           - min_iterations_guard_blocked: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor overrides a STOP candidate to CONTINUE\"\n692: \n693:       step_emit_min_iterations_guard_pass:\n694:         action: \"Persist a first-class event when the convergence floor clears\"\n695:         if_pass:\n696:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"iterationCount\":{iteration_count},\"minIterations\":{effective_min_iterations},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n697:           log: \"Minimum iteration floor cleared for convergence stopping.\"\n698: \n699:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n700:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n701:         if_blocked:\n702:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n703:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n704:           set:\n705:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n706:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n707:             stop_blocked: false\n708: \n709:       step_handle_convergence:\n710:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n711:         if_stop:\n712:           branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n713:           if_divergent_eligible:\n714:             eligibility_contract:\n715:               required_decision: \"STOP\"\n716:               eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n717:               excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n718:               fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n719:             steps:\n720:               step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n721:                 action: \"Generate state-grounded research candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n722:                 command: |\n723:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n724:                   import {\n725:                     buildResearchPivotPreparationInput,\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-725. Use offset=726 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n  convergence_mode: \"[default|off|sliding-window|divergent] - Convergence policy modifier. Default: default.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: system-deep-loop\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('./.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n      deep/research command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n      deep-research agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n      sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n            --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, convergence_mode]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted runtime/ loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_resolve_session_id:\n        action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n        branch_on: \"session_id\"\n        if_present:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n        if_absent:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          minIterations: 3\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          antiConvergence.convergenceMode: \"{convergence_mode}\"\n          antiConvergence.divergent: {}\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          minIdeaObservations: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n          nextRunAt: null\n          remainingDelayMs: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"{convergence_mode}\",\"divergent\":{}},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n          const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'started',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: 0,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n                event: row.event,\n                status: 'running',\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - memory_context_prompt_line: \"If a refreshed memory context summary exists from the previous iteration, return 'Memory context refresh: {summary}'. Else use prior_context_summary from startup when available; otherwise return 'Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.'\"\n          - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - nextRunAt: \"Extract nullable nextRunAt from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n          - remainingDelayMs: \"Extract nullable remainingDelayMs from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n          - min_iterations_present: \"Boolean true when deep-research-config.json has a numeric minIterations field\"\n          - min_iterations_missing_warning: \"Boolean true when minIterations is missing; use no floor and log a warning so older configs keep prior stop behavior\"\n          - min_iterations_raw: \"Extract numeric minIterations from deep-research-config.json when present, default 0\"\n          - effective_min_iterations: \"Clamp min_iterations_raw to the inclusive range 0..max_iterations; if min_iterations_raw exceeds max_iterations, use max_iterations\"\n          - min_iterations_clamped: \"Boolean true when min_iterations_raw > max_iterations\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_already_passed: \"Boolean true when state_log already contains event == 'min_iterations_guard_pass'\"\n          - convergence_mode: \"Extract antiConvergence.convergenceMode when it is one of 'default', 'off', 'sliding-window', or 'divergent'; default to 'default'\"\n          - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when antiConvergence.convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n          - rejected_patterns_count: \"Read registry.rejectedPatterns length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Read registry.suppressedCandidates when registry exists, else []\"\n          - rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold: \"Read config.rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold when present, else 0.85\"\n          - min_idea_observations: \"Read config.minIdeaObservations when present, default 2; clamp to 1..10\"\n          - observed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.observedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - promoted_ideas_count: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - promoted_ideas_list: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas idea text in rank order when registry exists, else []\"\n          - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.suppressedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - pivot_lineage: \"Summarize registry.divergence.completed and registry.divergence.overrides with pivot ids, source iterations, and selected focus; else 'none yet'\"\n          - saturated_directions: \"List registry.divergence.saturatedDirections; else 'none yet'\"\n\n      step_run_now_check:\n        action: \"Detect and consume a one-shot run-now sentinel before pause/convergence/dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, renameSync, unlinkSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const pausePath = \"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n          const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n\n          function append(event) {\n            appendFileSync(\n              stateLogPath,\n              `${JSON.stringify({\n                type: \"event\",\n                mode: \"research\",\n                run,\n                timestamp,\n                sessionId,\n                generation,\n                ...event,\n              })}\\n`,\n              \"utf8\",\n            );\n          }\n\n          if (existsSync(sentinelPath)) {\n            append({ event: \"run_now_requested\", sentinelPath });\n            if (existsSync(pausePath)) {\n              append({\n                event: \"run_now_rejected\",\n                reason: \"loop_paused\",\n                sentinelPath,\n                pauseSentinelPath: pausePath,\n              });\n            } else {\n              const claimPath = `${sentinelPath}.consuming.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}`;\n              try {\n                renameSync(sentinelPath, claimPath);\n                unlinkSync(claimPath);\n                append({\n                  event: \"run_now_accepted\",\n                  sentinelPath,\n                  dispatchEvent: \"iteration_start\",\n                });\n              } catch (error) {\n                if (!error || error.code !== \"ENOENT\") {\n                  throw error;\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n          EOF\n        outputs:\n          - run_now_requested: \"Emitted when {state_paths.run_now_sentinel} exists at the loop boundary\"\n          - run_now_accepted: \"Emitted after the sentinel is atomically renamed and deleted before dispatch\"\n          - run_now_rejected: \"Emitted with reason loop_paused when pause takes precedence; sentinel remains present\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_validate_convergence_config:\n        action: \"Validate convergence floor settings when loading config\"\n        if_min_iterations_missing:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"fallback\":0,\"message\":\"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\"\n        if_min_iterations_clamped:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"configured\":{min_iterations_raw},\"effective\":{effective_min_iterations},\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"message\":\"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\"\n        if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\" --convergence-mode \"{convergence_mode}\"'\n        note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n          - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n          - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n          - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n          2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n          4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n          5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n               step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n               The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n               signals = []\n               Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n                  stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n                  coverage = answered / total questions\n                  stop if coverage >= 0.85\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n               Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n               if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                 decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                 reason = \"blockedStop\"\n                 stop_blocked = true\n                 blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 gate_convergence_pass = false\n                 gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n                 gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n                 gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n                 gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n                 gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n                 recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n               else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n                 decision = \"STOP\"\n                 reason = \"composite_converged\"\n                 stop_blocked = false\n          6. else: CONTINUE\n          7. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\" and effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count < effective_min_iterations:\n               decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n               reason = \"minIterationsNotReached\"\n               min_iterations_guard_blocked = true\n               min_iterations_guard_pass = false\n          8. if effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count >= effective_min_iterations and min_iterations_guard_already_passed == false:\n               min_iterations_guard_pass = true\n          9. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n               guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n               if not guardResult.passed:\n                 log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n                 decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n          See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n          Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n          - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n          - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n          - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_pass: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor has cleared for the first time\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_blocked: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor overrides a STOP candidate to CONTINUE\"\n\n      step_emit_min_iterations_guard_pass:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class event when the convergence floor clears\"\n        if_pass:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"iterationCount\":{iteration_count},\"minIterations\":{effective_min_iterations},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Minimum iteration floor cleared for convergence stopping.\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n          if_divergent_eligible:\n            eligibility_contract:\n              required_decision: \"STOP\"\n              eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n              excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n              fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n            steps:\n              step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Generate state-grounded research candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import {\n                    buildResearchPivotPreparationInput,","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":725,"totalLines":726,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","time":{"start":1784521056889,"end":1784521056899}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05885a86d8766c27016a5da160ceac81919e7c6d742759ff26"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe6252001YGiYXzJIW7zGxG","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe41d8001jJnEYh1TJPFDC2"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521057018,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0qRfJJaZiZSDpGmFPoWsVbRQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-presentation.txt"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-presentation.txt</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: Presentation source of truth for `/deep:research`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Presentation\n6: \n7: This workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n8: \n9: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n10: \n11: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n12: \n13: ### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n14: \n15: Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto-mode-contract.md`.\n16: \n17: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n18: \n19: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`, reserved `antiConvergence.divergent: {}`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml`. End §0.\n20: \n21: 2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n22: \n23: 3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:research:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n24: \n25: `:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n26: \n27: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n28: \n29: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto-mode-contract.md` §2.\n30: \n31: ```yaml\n32: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n33:   research_topic: WebSocket reconnection strategies  # string\n34:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | phase-folder | explicit path\n35:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n36:   maxIterations: 10  # positive integer\n37:   convergenceThreshold: 0.05  # decimal 0..1\n38:   convergence_mode: default  # default | off | sliding-window | divergent\n39:   executor: native  # native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n40:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n41:   executor_config_dir: \"\"  # optional, cli-claude-code only; maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR\n42:   executor_reasoning: \"\"  # optional reasoning effort\n43:   executor_service_tier: \"\"  # optional service tier\n44:   executor_timeout: 900  # optional positive integer seconds\n45:   resource_map_emit: true  # boolean\n46: ```\n47: \n48: Rules: see `auto-mode-contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n49: \n50: ### Default Resolution Table\n51: \n52: | Field                   | Required | Resolves Via                                                                                                                                                                                           | Default                            | Tier-2 Candidate                                        |\n53: | -------------------------| ----------| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| ------------------------------------| ---------------------------------------------------------|\n54: | `research_topic`        | Y        | `$ARGUMENTS` positional topic, or marker `research_topic`                                                                                                                                              | none                               | N                                                       |\n55: | `spec_folder`           | Y        | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, `scope-extract` → a spec-folder path named in the topic/`$ARGUMENTS` that resolves to an existing folder (auto-bound + stripped, per `auto_mode_contract` §1 source 3), or targeted choice among suggested existing/new/update-related/phase folder | none | Y, ONLY when topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous |\n56: | `execution_mode`        | Y        | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode`                                                                                                                                                     | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto`         | N                                                       |\n57: | `maxIterations`         | Y        | flag `--max-iterations`, marker `maxIterations`, or default                                                                                                                                            | `10`                               | N                                                       |\n58: | `convergenceThreshold`  | Y        | flag `--convergence`, marker `convergenceThreshold`, or default                                                                                                                                        | `0.05`                             | N                                                       |\n59: | `convergence_mode`      | Y        | flag `--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent`, marker `convergence_mode`, or default                                                                                                  | `default`                          | N                                                       |\n60: | `executor`              | N        | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, config file, or default                                                                                                                                          | `native`                           | N                                                       |\n61: | `executor_model`        | N        | flag `--model`, marker `executor_model`, or executor-specific validation                                                                                                                               | none                               | N                                                       |\n62: | `executor_config_dir`   | N        | flag `--config-dir`, marker `executor_config_dir`, or executor-specific default                                                                                                                        | none                               | N                                                       |\n63: | `executor_reasoning`    | N        | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor_reasoning`, or executor default                                                                                                                            | none                               | N                                                       |\n64: | `executor_service_tier` | N        | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor_service_tier`, or executor default                                                                                                                             | none                               | N                                                       |\n65: | `executor_timeout`      | N        | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor_timeout`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `900`                              | N                                                       |\n66: | `resource_map_emit`     | N        | flag `--no-resource-map`, marker `resource_map_emit`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `true`                             | N                                                       |\n67: | `fanout_executors`      | N        | repeatable `--executor=<type>` flags or `--executors=<json>`; each `--executor` group accepts `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count` | none (single-executor when absent) | N                                                       |\n68: | `fanout_concurrency`    | N        | flag `--concurrency=N`                                                                                                                                                                                 | `2`                                | N                                                       |\n69: \n70: **Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Native fan-out (count N for `native` executor) runs N sequential `@deep-research` agent dispatches with isolated dirs. CLI fan-out runs N headless subprocesses concurrently in the capped pool.\n71: \n72: ### Consolidated Prompt Template\n73: \n74: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n75: \n76: ```\n77: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n78: \n79: 1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n80:    |-- \":auto\"         -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n81:    |-- \":confirm\"      -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n82:    +-- No suffix       -> execution_mode = \"ASK\"\n83: \n84: 2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for topic:\n85:    |-- Has content (ignoring suffixes and flags):\n86:    |     -> research_topic = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n87:    +-- Empty -> include Q0\n88: \n89: 3. PARSE optional flags from $ARGUMENTS:\n90:    |-- --max-iterations=N -> maxIterations = N\n91:    |-- --convergence=N -> convergenceThreshold = N\n92:    |-- --convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent -> antiConvergence.convergenceMode = value\n93:    |-- --spec-folder=PATH -> spec_path = PATH, omit Q1\n94:    |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code`)\n95:    |-- --model=<id> -> config.executor.model (for example `gpt-5.4`)\n96:    |-- --config-dir=<path> -> config.executor.configDir (cli-claude-code only; fan-out sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\n97:    |-- --reasoning-effort=<level> -> config.executor.reasoningEffort (`none` | `minimal` | `low` | `medium` | `high` | `xhigh` | `max`)\n98:    |-- --service-tier=<tier> -> config.executor.serviceTier (`priority` | `standard` | `fast`)\n99:    |-- --executor-timeout=<seconds> -> config.executor.timeoutSeconds (positive integer, default `900`)\n100:    |-- --no-resource-map -> config.resource_map.emit = false\n101:    |-- --executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=Y] [--service-tier=Z] [--executor-timeout=N] [--iters=N] [--label=X] [--count=N]\n102:    |     (repeatable; each occurrence adds one entry to config.fanout.executors)\n103:    |-- --executors=<json> -> config.fanout.executors = parse(json) escape hatch for complex configs\n104:    |-- --concurrency=N -> config.fanout.concurrency (default 2)\n105:    |\n106:    |   Fan-out default policy:\n107:    |   - 0 or 1 --executor (no --executors, no count>1): write config.executor (single, unchanged)\n108:    |   - 2+ --executor flags, --executors, or any count>1: write config.fanout\n109:    |\n110:    +-- Defaults: maxIterations=10, convergenceThreshold=0.05, antiConvergence.convergenceMode=`default`, antiConvergence.divergent=`{}`, config.executor.type=`native`, config.executor.timeoutSeconds=900, config.resource_map.emit=`true`\n111: \n112:    Executor precedence for setup resolution:\n113:    - CLI flag > config file > schema defaults\n114:    - The generated `deep-research-config.json` stores executor settings under `config.executor.*`\n115: \n116:    Parsing to config mapping:\n117:    - `--executor` -> `config.executor.type`\n118:    - `--model` -> `config.executor.model`\n119:    - `--config-dir` -> `config.executor.configDir`\n120:    - `--reasoning-effort` -> `config.executor.reasoningEffort`\n121:    - `--service-tier` -> `config.executor.serviceTier`\n122:    - `--executor-timeout` -> `config.executor.timeoutSeconds`\n123:    - `--convergence-mode` -> `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`\n124: \n125:    Validation hook:\n126:    - `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` runs at config-write time\n127:    - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-opencode` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n128: \n129: 4. Search for related spec folders across alias roots:\n130:    $ find specs .opencode/specs -mindepth 2 -maxdepth 2 -type d 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -10\n131: \n132: 5. Search for prior work (background):\n133:    - memory_context({ input: research_topic OR \"deep-research\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n134:    - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no]\n135: \n136: 6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n137:    - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the topic text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, or `gpt-5.4`\n138:    - If Q-Exec is omitted and no executor is otherwise resolved, default to `native`\n139: \n140:    Q0. Research Topic (if not in command): What topic to research deeply?\n141: \n142:    Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n143:      A) Use existing [suggest if found]\n144:      B) Create new under `specs/[track]/[###]-[slug]/` (accept `.opencode/specs/` alias roots when already in use)\n145:      C) Update related [if match found]\n146:      D) Phase folder (e.g., `specs/NN-track/NNN-name/001-phase/` or matching `.opencode/specs/` alias)\n147: \n148:    Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n149:      A) Autonomous -- all iterations without approval\n150:      B) Interactive -- pause at each iteration for review\n151: \n152:    Q3. Max Iterations (if not set via flag):\n153:      Default is 10. Change? [Enter number or press enter for default]\n154: \n155:    Q-Exec. Executor (optional, press enter for default):\n156:      A) Native (default) — dispatch via @deep-research agent with Opus.\n157:      B) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n158:      C) cli-claude-code — `claude -p \"PROMPT\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits` with optional --effort and optional `--config-dir=PATH` for CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR. No service-tier.\n159: \n160:    Reply format examples:\n161:    - `\"A, A\"`\n162:    - `\"WebSocket research, A, B, 15\"`\n163:    - `\"WebSocket reconnection strategies, B, A, 10, 0.05, B, gpt-5.4, high, fast\"`\n164:    - `\"agent execution guardrails research, B, A, 15, 0.05, C, gpt-5.4, _, _\"`\n165: \n166: 7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n167: \n168: 8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n169:    - research_topic = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n170:    - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D from Q1]\n171:    - spec_path = [derived path]\n172:    - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE]\n173:    - maxIterations = [from Q3 or flag or default 10]\n174:    - convergenceThreshold = [from flag or default 0.05]\n175:    - convergence_mode = [from flag, marker, or default `default`; one of `default`, `off`, `sliding-window`, `divergent`]\n176:     - executor config = [CLI flags, compact reply, config file, or default `native`; map compact reply fields to `config.executor.type/model/configDir/reasoningEffort/serviceTier`, and accept an optional volunteered convergence value before executor fields]\n177: \n178: 9. SET STATUS: PASSED\n179: \n180: STOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n181: \n182: DO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\n183: NEVER auto-create spec folders without confirmation\n184: NEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n185: ```\n186: \n187: **Phase Output:**\n188: - `research_topic` | `spec_choice` | `spec_path`\n189: - `execution_mode` | `maxIterations` | `convergenceThreshold` | `convergence_mode`\n190: \n191: ## 2. Dashboard / Checkpoint Layout\n192: \n193: ### Deep Research\n194: \n195: Conduct autonomous iterative deep research with convergence detection. Each iteration dispatches a fresh LEAF agent (`@deep-research`) that reads externalized state, performs focused investigation, and writes findings to files.\n196: \n197: For code review and quality auditing, see `/deep:review`.\n198: \n199: ### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n200: \n201: **Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n202: \n203: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n204: \n205: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n206: - `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n207: - `deep-ai-council` (proposed) uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n208: \n209: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See 116 research at `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/z_archive/006-deep-skill-evolution/007-deep-stack-cross-cutting/001-unique-value-differentiation/research/research.md` §2 F56/F78, §5 Recommendation, and §6 Parity Invariants.\n210: \n211: ```yaml\n212: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n213: purpose: Run iterative research cycles until convergence or max iterations\n214: action: Execute YAML workflow managing init, loop, synthesis, and save phases\n215: operating_mode:\n216:   workflow: iterative_loop\n217:   compliance: MANDATORY\n218:   execution: autonomous_or_interactive\n219:   validation: convergence_detection\n220: ```\n221: \n222: ### Purpose\n223: \n224: Run an iterative loop for deep research: Initialize state under `{artifact_dir}` (resolved via `resolveArtifactRoot()` — root specs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child phases and sub-phases use `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/`), dispatch `@deep-research` agent per iteration, evaluate convergence, synthesize findings into `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, and emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` at convergence unless `--no-resource-map` disables it. Use when deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery.\n225: \n226: ### Contract\n227: \n228: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` -- Research topic with optional flags and mode suffix\n229: **Outputs:** Spec folder with `{artifact_dir}/` packet (`{spec_folder}/research/` for root specs or `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/` for nested phases), `research.md`, optional `resource-map.md`, state files, and `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n230: \n231: ### Workflow Overview\n232: \n233: | Phase | Name | Purpose | Outputs |\n234: |-------|------|---------|---------|\n235: | Init | Initialize | Create config, strategy (with research charter), state files | State files in `research/` |\n236: | Loop | Iterate | Dispatch @deep-research agent, evaluate convergence + quality guards, generate dashboard | iteration-NNN.md files, deep-research-dashboard.md |\n237: | Synth | Synthesize | Emit `research/resource-map.md` and compile final research/research.md | research/resource-map.md, research/research.md (17 sections) |\n238: | Save | Preserve | Refresh continuity update in canonical spec docs | canonical spec doc updated via `generate-context.js` |\n239: \n240: ### Execution Modes\n241: \n242: | Mode | Invocation | Behavior |\n243: |------|-----------|----------|\n244: | `:auto` | `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | All iterations without approval |\n245: | `:confirm` | `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Multi-gate review at setup, iteration, and synthesis |\n246: | (default) | `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask user to choose mode during setup |\n247: \n248: ### Memory Integration Before Starting\n249: \n250: - `memory_context({ input: topic, intent: \"understand\" })` -- Load prior research\n251: - Inject results into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section\n252: \n253: ### Code Context Bootstrap\n254: \n255: - Use Code Graph (`code_graph_query`) to find relevant code examples before starting research\n256: - Query: 2-5 word concept descriptions related to the research topic\n257: - Inject discovered code patterns into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section alongside memory findings\n258: \n259: ## 3. Results Display\n260: \n261: ### Output Formats\n262: \n263: **Success:**\n264: ```\n265: Deep research complete.\n266: Iterations: [N] | Stop reason: [converged|max_iterations|all_answered]\n267: Artifacts: research/research.md, research/resource-map.md (unless `--no-resource-map`), [N] iteration files, continuity update in canonical spec docs refreshed\n268: Ready for: /speckit:plan [feature-description]\n269: STATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n270: ```\n271: \n272: **Failure:**\n273: ```\n274: Error: [error description]  Phase: [phase name]\n275: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### Memory Integration After Completing\n279: \n280: - `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json [spec-folder]`\n281: - Verify that the canonical save routed continuity into the expected packet doc (decision-record.md / implementation-summary.md / handover.md)\n282: \n283: ### Anchor Tags (Automatic)\n284: \n285: `ANCHOR:deep-research-[topic]`, `ANCHOR:findings`, `ANCHOR:convergence-report`\n286: \n287: ### Error Handling\n288: \n289: | Error | Action |\n290: |-------|--------|\n291: | Agent dispatch timeout | Retry once with reduced scope, then mark timeout |\n292: | State file missing | Reconstruct from iteration files |\n293: | 3+ consecutive failures | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n294: | Memory save failure | Save to `scratch/` as backup |\n295: \n296: ## 4. Next-Step Suggestions\n297: \n298: ### Skill Reference\n299: \n300: Full protocol documentation: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md`\n301: \n302: Key references:\n303: - Loop protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md`\n304: - Spec check protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md`\n305: - State formats: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-format.md`\n306: - Convergence: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n307: - Quick reference: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/quick-reference.md`\n308: \n309: For code review, see `deep-review` skill (`.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/SKILL.md`).\n310: \n311: ### Examples\n312: \n313: ```\n314: # Single-executor (default — unchanged)\n315: /deep:research:auto \"WebSocket reconnection strategies across browsers\"\n316: /deep:research:confirm \"distributed caching patterns for microservices\"\n317: /deep:research:auto \"API rate limiting approaches\" --max-iterations 5 --convergence 0.10\n318: \n319: # Fan-out: two CLI lineages in parallel (cli-opencode + cli-claude-code)\n320: /deep:research:auto \"caching patterns\" \\\n321:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --label= \\\n322:   --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --label=claude \\\n323:   --concurrency=2\n324: \n325: # Fan-out: native (sequential agent dispatches) + CLI lineages mixed\n326: /deep:research:auto \"distributed systems consensus\" \\\n327:   --executor=native --count=1 --label=native \\\n328:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --count=2 \\\n329:   --concurrency=3\n330: \n331: # Fan-out via JSON escape hatch\n332: /deep:research:auto \"WebRTC internals\" \\\n333:   --executors='[{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"o4-mini\",\"label\":\"\",\"count\":3},{\"kind\":\"cli-claude-code\",\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-8\",\"label\":\"claude\",\"count\":2}]' \\\n334:   --concurrency=4\n335: ```\n336: \n337: > **Note on native fan-out:** `--executor=native --count=N` dispatches N sequential `@deep-research` sub-agents with isolated artifact dirs. Not pooled. Best for count 1–3. For higher parallelism, use CLI executor kinds.\n338: \n339: ### Next Steps\n340: \n341: > **Note:** Deep-research now anchors bounded findings back into `spec.md` through the generated findings fence while keeping `research/research.md` canonical.\n342: \n343: | Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n344: |-----------|-------------------|--------|\n345: | Research complete, ready to plan | `/speckit:plan [feature]` | Use findings for spec/plan |\n346: | Need more investigation | `/deep:research [new-topic]` | Another deep research session |\n347: | Need code/spec audit | `/deep:review [target]` | Iterative code review |\n348: | Want to refresh search support | `/memory:save [spec-folder]` | Refresh the indexed canonical spec document while canonical continuity stays in spec docs |\n349: \n350: ### Key Differences (vs. single-pass research)\n351: \n352: - Iterative (multi-pass) vs. single-pass research\n353: - Dispatches `@deep-research` LEAF agent per iteration (fresh context each time)\n354: - Externalized state via JSONL + strategy files\n355: - Automatic convergence detection with quality guards (3 binary checks before STOP)\n356: - Persistent dashboard auto-generated each iteration for progress tracking\n357: - Negative knowledge (ruled-out directions) as first-class research output\n358: - Research charter (non-goals, stop conditions) validated at init\n359: - Does NOT proceed to implementation\n360: \n361: ### Command Chain\n362: \n363: **Research path:** `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n364: **Review:** `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n365: \n366: ### Offline Optimization\n367: \n368: Convergence thresholds and recovery settings used by this command are a governed maintenance surface managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). The optimizer tunes deterministic numeric thresholds offline against real run traces and emits advisory-only candidate patches.\n369: \n370: **Key constraints:**\n371: - Optimization is offline only -- it does not run during live research sessions\n372: - Promotion is advisory-only until replay fixtures and behavioral suites exist\n373: - Prompt optimization is deferred future work (Phase 4b) and will use generated prompt packs, never direct agent markdown mutation\n374: \n375: **References:**\n376: - Optimizer configuration: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`\n377: - Tunable thresholds: `convergenceThreshold`, `stuckThreshold`, `maxIterations`\n378: - Convergence reference: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n\n(End of file - total 378 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/deep:research`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nThis workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto-mode-contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`, reserved `antiConvergence.divergent: {}`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml`. End §0.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-presentation.txt","text":"# Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/deep:research`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nThis workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto-mode-contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`, reserved `antiConvergence.divergent: {}`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml`. End §0.\n\n2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n\n3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:research:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n\n`:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n\n### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n\nThe dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto-mode-contract.md` §2.\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  research_topic: WebSocket reconnection strategies  # string\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | phase-folder | explicit path\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n  maxIterations: 10  # positive integer\n  convergenceThreshold: 0.05  # decimal 0..1\n  convergence_mode: default  # default | off | sliding-window | divergent\n  executor: native  # native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n  executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n  executor_config_dir: \"\"  # optional, cli-claude-code only; maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR\n  executor_reasoning: \"\"  # optional reasoning effort\n  executor_service_tier: \"\"  # optional service tier\n  executor_timeout: 900  # optional positive integer seconds\n  resource_map_emit: true  # boolean\n```\n\nRules: see `auto-mode-contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n\n### Default Resolution Table\n\n| Field                   | Required | Resolves Via                                                                                                                                                                                           | Default                            | Tier-2 Candidate                                        |\n| -------------------------| ----------| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| ------------------------------------| ---------------------------------------------------------|\n| `research_topic`        | Y        | `$ARGUMENTS` positional topic, or marker `research_topic`                                                                                                                                              | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `spec_folder`           | Y        | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, `scope-extract` → a spec-folder path named in the topic/`$ARGUMENTS` that resolves to an existing folder (auto-bound + stripped, per `auto_mode_contract` §1 source 3), or targeted choice among suggested existing/new/update-related/phase folder | none | Y, ONLY when topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous |\n| `execution_mode`        | Y        | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode`                                                                                                                                                     | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto`         | N                                                       |\n| `maxIterations`         | Y        | flag `--max-iterations`, marker `maxIterations`, or default                                                                                                                                            | `10`                               | N                                                       |\n| `convergenceThreshold`  | Y        | flag `--convergence`, marker `convergenceThreshold`, or default                                                                                                                                        | `0.05`                             | N                                                       |\n| `convergence_mode`      | Y        | flag `--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent`, marker `convergence_mode`, or default                                                                                                  | `default`                          | N                                                       |\n| `executor`              | N        | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, config file, or default                                                                                                                                          | `native`                           | N                                                       |\n| `executor_model`        | N        | flag `--model`, marker `executor_model`, or executor-specific validation                                                                                                                               | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_config_dir`   | N        | flag `--config-dir`, marker `executor_config_dir`, or executor-specific default                                                                                                                        | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_reasoning`    | N        | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor_reasoning`, or executor default                                                                                                                            | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_service_tier` | N        | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor_service_tier`, or executor default                                                                                                                             | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_timeout`      | N        | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor_timeout`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `900`                              | N                                                       |\n| `resource_map_emit`     | N        | flag `--no-resource-map`, marker `resource_map_emit`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `true`                             | N                                                       |\n| `fanout_executors`      | N        | repeatable `--executor=<type>` flags or `--executors=<json>`; each `--executor` group accepts `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count` | none (single-executor when absent) | N                                                       |\n| `fanout_concurrency`    | N        | flag `--concurrency=N`                                                                                                                                                                                 | `2`                                | N                                                       |\n\n**Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Native fan-out (count N for `native` executor) runs N sequential `@deep-research` agent dispatches with isolated dirs. CLI fan-out runs N headless subprocesses concurrently in the capped pool.\n\n### Consolidated Prompt Template\n\n**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n\n1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n   |-- \":auto\"         -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n   |-- \":confirm\"      -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n   +-- No suffix       -> execution_mode = \"ASK\"\n\n2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for topic:\n   |-- Has content (ignoring suffixes and flags):\n   |     -> research_topic = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n   +-- Empty -> include Q0\n\n3. PARSE optional flags from $ARGUMENTS:\n   |-- --max-iterations=N -> maxIterations = N\n   |-- --convergence=N -> convergenceThreshold = N\n   |-- --convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent -> antiConvergence.convergenceMode = value\n   |-- --spec-folder=PATH -> spec_path = PATH, omit Q1\n   |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code`)\n   |-- --model=<id> -> config.executor.model (for example `gpt-5.4`)\n   |-- --config-dir=<path> -> config.executor.configDir (cli-claude-code only; fan-out sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\n   |-- --reasoning-effort=<level> -> config.executor.reasoningEffort (`none` | `minimal` | `low` | `medium` | `high` | `xhigh` | `max`)\n   |-- --service-tier=<tier> -> config.executor.serviceTier (`priority` | `standard` | `fast`)\n   |-- --executor-timeout=<seconds> -> config.executor.timeoutSeconds (positive integer, default `900`)\n   |-- --no-resource-map -> config.resource_map.emit = false\n   |-- --executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=Y] [--service-tier=Z] [--executor-timeout=N] [--iters=N] [--label=X] [--count=N]\n   |     (repeatable; each occurrence adds one entry to config.fanout.executors)\n   |-- --executors=<json> -> config.fanout.executors = parse(json) escape hatch for complex configs\n   |-- --concurrency=N -> config.fanout.concurrency (default 2)\n   |\n   |   Fan-out default policy:\n   |   - 0 or 1 --executor (no --executors, no count>1): write config.executor (single, unchanged)\n   |   - 2+ --executor flags, --executors, or any count>1: write config.fanout\n   |\n   +-- Defaults: maxIterations=10, convergenceThreshold=0.05, antiConvergence.convergenceMode=`default`, antiConvergence.divergent=`{}`, config.executor.type=`native`, config.executor.timeoutSeconds=900, config.resource_map.emit=`true`\n\n   Executor precedence for setup resolution:\n   - CLI flag > config file > schema defaults\n   - The generated `deep-research-config.json` stores executor settings under `config.executor.*`\n\n   Parsing to config mapping:\n   - `--executor` -> `config.executor.type`\n   - `--model` -> `config.executor.model`\n   - `--config-dir` -> `config.executor.configDir`\n   - `--reasoning-effort` -> `config.executor.reasoningEffort`\n   - `--service-tier` -> `config.executor.serviceTier`\n   - `--executor-timeout` -> `config.executor.timeoutSeconds`\n   - `--convergence-mode` -> `antiConvergence.convergenceMode`\n\n   Validation hook:\n   - `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` runs at config-write time\n   - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-opencode` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n\n4. Search for related spec folders across alias roots:\n   $ find specs .opencode/specs -mindepth 2 -maxdepth 2 -type d 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -10\n\n5. Search for prior work (background):\n   - memory_context({ input: research_topic OR \"deep-research\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n   - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no]\n\n6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n   - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the topic text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, or `gpt-5.4`\n   - If Q-Exec is omitted and no executor is otherwise resolved, default to `native`\n\n   Q0. Research Topic (if not in command): What topic to research deeply?\n\n   Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n     A) Use existing [suggest if found]\n     B) Create new under `specs/[track]/[###]-[slug]/` (accept `.opencode/specs/` alias roots when already in use)\n     C) Update related [if match found]\n     D) Phase folder (e.g., `specs/NN-track/NNN-name/001-phase/` or matching `.opencode/specs/` alias)\n\n   Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n     A) Autonomous -- all iterations without approval\n     B) Interactive -- pause at each iteration for review\n\n   Q3. Max Iterations (if not set via flag):\n     Default is 10. Change? [Enter number or press enter for default]\n\n   Q-Exec. Executor (optional, press enter for default):\n     A) Native (default) — dispatch via @deep-research agent with Opus.\n     B) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n     C) cli-claude-code — `claude -p \"PROMPT\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits` with optional --effort and optional `--config-dir=PATH` for CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR. No service-tier.\n\n   Reply format examples:\n   - `\"A, A\"`\n   - `\"WebSocket research, A, B, 15\"`\n   - `\"WebSocket reconnection strategies, B, A, 10, 0.05, B, gpt-5.4, high, fast\"`\n   - `\"agent execution guardrails research, B, A, 15, 0.05, C, gpt-5.4, _, _\"`\n\n7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n\n8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n   - research_topic = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n   - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D from Q1]\n   - spec_path = [derived path]\n   - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE]\n   - maxIterations = [from Q3 or flag or default 10]\n   - convergenceThreshold = [from flag or default 0.05]\n   - convergence_mode = [from flag, marker, or default `default`; one of `default`, `off`, `sliding-window`, `divergent`]\n    - executor config = [CLI flags, compact reply, config file, or default `native`; map compact reply fields to `config.executor.type/model/configDir/reasoningEffort/serviceTier`, and accept an optional volunteered convergence value before executor fields]\n\n9. SET STATUS: PASSED\n\nSTOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n\nDO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\nNEVER auto-create spec folders without confirmation\nNEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `research_topic` | `spec_choice` | `spec_path`\n- `execution_mode` | `maxIterations` | `convergenceThreshold` | `convergence_mode`\n\n## 2. Dashboard / Checkpoint Layout\n\n### Deep Research\n\nConduct autonomous iterative deep research with convergence detection. Each iteration dispatches a fresh LEAF agent (`@deep-research`) that reads externalized state, performs focused investigation, and writes findings to files.\n\nFor code review and quality auditing, see `/deep:review`.\n\n### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n- `deep-ai-council` (proposed) uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See 116 research at `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/z_archive/006-deep-skill-evolution/007-deep-stack-cross-cutting/001-unique-value-differentiation/research/research.md` §2 F56/F78, §5 Recommendation, and §6 Parity Invariants.\n\n```yaml\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Run iterative research cycles until convergence or max iterations\naction: Execute YAML workflow managing init, loop, synthesis, and save phases\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  compliance: MANDATORY\n  execution: autonomous_or_interactive\n  validation: convergence_detection\n```\n\n### Purpose\n\nRun an iterative loop for deep research: Initialize state under `{artifact_dir}` (resolved via `resolveArtifactRoot()` — root specs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child phases and sub-phases use `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/`), dispatch `@deep-research` agent per iteration, evaluate convergence, synthesize findings into `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, and emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` at convergence unless `--no-resource-map` disables it. Use when deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery.\n\n### Contract\n\n**Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` -- Research topic with optional flags and mode suffix\n**Outputs:** Spec folder with `{artifact_dir}/` packet (`{spec_folder}/research/` for root specs or `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/` for nested phases), `research.md`, optional `resource-map.md`, state files, and `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n\n### Workflow Overview\n\n| Phase | Name | Purpose | Outputs |\n|-------|------|---------|---------|\n| Init | Initialize | Create config, strategy (with research charter), state files | State files in `research/` |\n| Loop | Iterate | Dispatch @deep-research agent, evaluate convergence + quality guards, generate dashboard | iteration-NNN.md files, deep-research-dashboard.md |\n| Synth | Synthesize | Emit `research/resource-map.md` and compile final research/research.md | research/resource-map.md, research/research.md (17 sections) |\n| Save | Preserve | Refresh continuity update in canonical spec docs | canonical spec doc updated via `generate-context.js` |\n\n### Execution Modes\n\n| Mode | Invocation | Behavior |\n|------|-----------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | All iterations without approval |\n| `:confirm` | `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Multi-gate review at setup, iteration, and synthesis |\n| (default) | `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask user to choose mode during setup |\n\n### Memory Integration Before Starting\n\n- `memory_context({ input: topic, intent: \"understand\" })` -- Load prior research\n- Inject results into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section\n\n### Code Context Bootstrap\n\n- Use Code Graph (`code_graph_query`) to find relevant code examples before starting research\n- Query: 2-5 word concept descriptions related to the research topic\n- Inject discovered code patterns into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section alongside memory findings\n\n## 3. Results Display\n\n### Output Formats\n\n**Success:**\n```\nDeep research complete.\nIterations: [N] | Stop reason: [converged|max_iterations|all_answered]\nArtifacts: research/research.md, research/resource-map.md (unless `--no-resource-map`), [N] iteration files, continuity update in canonical spec docs refreshed\nReady for: /speckit:plan [feature-description]\nSTATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n```\n\n**Failure:**\n```\nError: [error description]  Phase: [phase name]\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n```\n\n### Memory Integration After Completing\n\n- `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json [spec-folder]`\n- Verify that the canonical save routed continuity into the expected packet doc (decision-record.md / implementation-summary.md / handover.md)\n\n### Anchor Tags (Automatic)\n\n`ANCHOR:deep-research-[topic]`, `ANCHOR:findings`, `ANCHOR:convergence-report`\n\n### Error Handling\n\n| Error | Action |\n|-------|--------|\n| Agent dispatch timeout | Retry once with reduced scope, then mark timeout |\n| State file missing | Reconstruct from iteration files |\n| 3+ consecutive failures | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n| Memory save failure | Save to `scratch/` as backup |\n\n## 4. Next-Step Suggestions\n\n### Skill Reference\n\nFull protocol documentation: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md`\n\nKey references:\n- Loop protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md`\n- Spec check protocol: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md`\n- State formats: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-format.md`\n- Convergence: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`\n- Quick reference: `system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/quick-reference.md`\n\nFor code review, see `deep-review` skill (`.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/SKILL.md`).\n\n### Examples\n\n```\n# Single-executor (default — unchanged)\n/deep:research:auto \"WebSocket reconnection strategies across browsers\"\n/deep:research:confirm \"distributed caching patterns for microservices\"\n/deep:research:auto \"API rate limiting approaches\" --max-iterations 5 --convergence 0.10\n\n# Fan-out: two CLI lineages in parallel (cli-opencode + cli-claude-code)\n/deep:research:auto \"caching patterns\" \\\n  --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --label= \\\n  --executor=cli-claude-code --model=claude-opus-4-8 --label=claude \\\n  --concurrency=2\n\n# Fan-out: native (sequential agent dispatches) + CLI lineages mixed\n/deep:research:auto \"distributed systems consensus\" \\\n  --executor=native --count=1 --label=native \\\n  --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --count=2 \\\n  --concurrency=3\n\n# Fan-out via JSON escape hatch\n/deep:research:auto \"WebRTC internals\" \\\n  --executors='[{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"o4-mini\",\"label\":\"\",\"count\":3},{\"kind\":\"cli-claude-code\",\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-8\",\"label\":\"claude\",\"count\":2}]' \\\n  --concurrency=4\n```\n\n> **Note on native fan-out:** `--executor=native --count=N` dispatches N sequential `@deep-research` sub-agents with isolated artifact dirs. Not pooled. Best for count 1–3. For higher parallelism, use CLI executor kinds.\n\n### Next Steps\n\n> **Note:** Deep-research now anchors bounded findings back into `spec.md` through the generated findings fence while keeping `research/research.md` canonical.\n\n| Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n|-----------|-------------------|--------|\n| Research complete, ready to plan | `/speckit:plan [feature]` | Use findings for spec/plan |\n| Need more investigation | `/deep:research [new-topic]` | Another deep research session |\n| Need code/spec audit | `/deep:review [target]` | Iterative code review |\n| Want to refresh search support | `/memory:save [spec-folder]` | Refresh the indexed canonical spec document while canonical continuity stays in spec docs |\n\n### Key Differences (vs. single-pass research)\n\n- Iterative (multi-pass) vs. single-pass research\n- Dispatches `@deep-research` LEAF agent per iteration (fresh context each time)\n- Externalized state via JSONL + strategy files\n- Automatic convergence detection with quality guards (3 binary checks before STOP)\n- Persistent dashboard auto-generated each iteration for progress tracking\n- Negative knowledge (ruled-out directions) as first-class research output\n- Research charter (non-goals, stop conditions) validated at init\n- Does NOT proceed to implementation\n\n### Command Chain\n\n**Research path:** `/deep:research` → `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n**Review:** `/deep:review` → (if issues) `/speckit:plan` → `/speckit:implement`\n\n### Offline Optimization\n\nConvergence thresholds and recovery settings used by this command are a governed maintenance surface managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). The optimizer tunes deterministic numeric thresholds offline against real run traces and emits advisory-only candidate patches.\n\n**Key constraints:**\n- Optimization is offline only -- it does not run during live research sessions\n- Promotion is advisory-only until replay fixtures and behavioral suites exist\n- Prompt optimization is deferred future work (Phase 4b) and will use generated prompt packs, never direct agent markdown mutation\n\n**References:**\n- Optimizer configuration: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`\n- Tunable thresholds: `convergenceThreshold`, `stuckThreshold`, `maxIterations`\n- Convergence reference: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":378,"totalLines":378,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-presentation.txt","time":{"start":1784521056974,"end":1784521056983}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05885a86d8766c27016a5da160ced48191b63268b71cf801b5"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe62c9001ul5HeNDgSxPNsE","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe41d8001jJnEYh1TJPFDC2"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521057019,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_psQ8tLty2qrZZ7UvjI6foFcm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/cli-reference.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/cli-reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"OpenCode CLI - Complete Command Reference\"\n3: description: \"Comprehensive reference for OpenCode CLI subcommands, flags, models, configuration, agent flags, sandbox boundaries, and troubleshooting. Pinned to v1.3.17.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"opencode cli reference\"\n6:   - \"opencode run flags\"\n7:   - \"opencode model selection\"\n8:   - \"opencode provider auth pre-flight\"\n9:   - \"opencode variant reasoning effort\"\n10:   - \"opencode version drift\"\n11: importance_tier: important\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.3.0.29\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # OpenCode CLI - Complete Command Reference\n17: \n18: Comprehensive reference for the OpenCode CLI binary, every subcommand the cli-opencode skill dispatches against, the flag set it relies on, the agent surface it can target, and the failure modes that need explicit handling. Pinned to v1.3.17 baseline.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Core Principle\n25: \n26: OpenCode is the framework that owns this repository. The same binary that hosts the operator's TUI session also accepts non-interactive invocations through `opencode run`. The cli-opencode skill calls `opencode run` from external runtimes (Claude Code, OpenCode, Copilot, raw shell) so the calling AI can dispatch a task into a fresh OpenCode session that loads the full plugin, skill, MCP, and Spec Kit Memory runtime.\n27: \n28: ### Purpose\n29: \n30: Provide a single-source reference for the OpenCode CLI surface — every subcommand cli-opencode invokes, every flag it pins, every agent it can route to, the version baseline it is built against, and the error envelopes that need explicit recovery.\n31: \n32: ### When to Use\n33: \n34: - Looking up an OpenCode CLI subcommand or flag during a delegation\n35: - Selecting a model + variant + agent for a dispatch\n36: - Confirming the version baseline before pinning a flag set\n37: - Troubleshooting a failed `opencode run` invocation\n38: - Confirming the self-invocation guard signal against the live binary\n39: \n40: ### Key Sources\n41: \n42: | Source | URL |\n43: |--------|-----|\n44: | **Binary** | `$(command -v opencode)` (typically `~/.superset/bin/opencode` or another local bin path) |\n45: | **Repository** | https://github.com/sst/opencode |\n46: | **Version baseline** | v1.3.17 (pinned in this reference) |\n47: | **Runtime** | Node.js 18+ for the npm install path; standalone binary on macOS |\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## 2. INSTALLATION\n52: \n53: | Method | Command | Notes |\n54: |--------|---------|-------|\n55: | **Standalone** | `curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install \\| bash` | macOS / Linux installer |\n56: | **Homebrew** | `brew install opencode` | macOS package manager |\n57: | **npm global** | `npm install -g opencode-ai` | Cross-platform when Node.js 18+ is present |\n58: | **Upgrade** | `opencode upgrade [target]` | Pin a specific version with the `target` argument |\n59: | **Uninstall** | `opencode uninstall` | Removes the binary and related state |\n60: \n61: After installation, run `opencode --version` to confirm. The cli-opencode skill is pinned to v1.3.17. Newer binaries may add or rename flags — consult Section 9 (Version Drift) before relying on a non-pinned flag.\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## 3. SUBCOMMAND MAP\n66: \n67: OpenCode exposes a multi-subcommand surface. The cli-opencode skill primarily invokes `run`, with secondary use of `serve`, `web`, `agent`, and `debug`.\n68: \n69: | Subcommand | Purpose | Invoked by cli-opencode |\n70: |------------|---------|-------------------------|\n71: | `opencode` (default) | Start the TUI in the current project | No (interactive only) |\n72: | `opencode run [message..]` | Non-interactive single-shot dispatch | YES (canonical use case) |\n73: | `opencode serve` | Start a headless server | YES (for parallel detached sessions) |\n74: | `opencode web` | Start a server plus open the web interface | YES (when the operator wants a browser surface) |\n75: | `opencode acp` | Start an ACP (Agent Client Protocol) server | No (specialized integration path) |\n76: | `opencode attach <url>` | Attach to a running OpenCode server | YES (for share-URL flows) |\n77: | `opencode agent` | Manage agent definitions | YES (for agent listing) |\n78: | `opencode debug` | Debugging and troubleshooting tools | YES (for `debug skill` and `debug agent` listings) |\n79: | `opencode mcp` | Manage MCP server registrations | No |\n80: | `opencode providers` (alias `auth`) | Manage AI providers and credentials | No (operator-driven setup) |\n81: | `opencode models [provider]` | List available models | YES (for capability discovery) |\n82: | `opencode session` | Manage sessions | No (state inspection only) |\n83: | `opencode export [sessionID]` | Export session data as JSON | YES (for memory handback flows) |\n84: | `opencode stats` | Token and cost statistics | No |\n85: | `opencode db` | Database tools | No |\n86: | `opencode plugin <module>` (alias `plug`) | Install a plugin | No (operator-driven setup) |\n87: | `opencode upgrade [target]` | Upgrade the binary | No (operator-driven) |\n88: | `opencode uninstall` | Uninstall the binary | No (operator-driven) |\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## 4. `opencode run` FLAGS\n93: \n94: `opencode run [message..]` is the canonical non-interactive entry point. The cli-opencode skill builds every dispatch around this subcommand.\n95: \n96: ### Core flags\n97: \n98: | Flag / Option | Type | Purpose |\n99: |---------------|------|---------|\n100: | `[message..]` | positional | One or more positional message strings |\n101: | `--print-logs` | boolean | Stream logs to stderr |\n102: | `--log-level` | enum | `DEBUG`, `INFO`, `WARN`, `ERROR` |\n103: | `--pure` | boolean | Run without external plugins (skill loads disabled) |\n104: | `--command` | string | Run a known command, the message becomes its args |\n105: | `-c`, `--continue` | boolean | Continue the last session in this project |\n106: | `-s`, `--session` | string | Continue a specific session id |\n107: | `--fork` | boolean | Fork before continuing — requires `--continue` or `--session` |\n108: | `--share` | boolean | Publish a shareable URL for this session |\n109: | `-m`, `--model` | string | Provider/model selector — e.g. `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` |\n110: | `--agent` | string | Agent slug (loads from `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md`) |\n111: | `--format` | enum | `default` (formatted) or `json` (raw event stream) |\n112: | `-f`, `--file` | array | Attach files to the message |\n113: | `--title` | string | Session title (truncated message used when omitted) |\n114: | `--attach` | string | Attach to a running OpenCode server URL |\n115: | `-p`, `--password` | string | Basic auth password (or `OPENCODE_SERVER_PASSWORD`) |\n116: | `--dir` | string | Working directory or remote-server path |\n117: | `--port` | number | Local server port (random when omitted) |\n118: | `--variant` | string | Provider-specific reasoning effort (`high`, `max`, `minimal`, etc.) |\n119: | `--thinking` | boolean | Show thinking blocks (default false) |\n120: \n121: > **`--command` semantics (verified on v1.17.4):** the `run` message is plain text — slash-command syntax inside it (`opencode run \"/memory:search query\"`) is NOT expanded, so the command's template never reaches the model. Executing a registered command non-interactively requires `--command <family>/<name>` with the args as the message (they become `$ARGUMENTS`). Registry names are slash-namespaced (`memory/search` for `/memory:search`); a wrong name fails with the full registry list. Behavior probes of slash commands MUST use `--command`; the raw-text form only measures the model freestyling without the contract. Consequences: (a) any behavior/adherence probe of a slash command MUST use `--command`, and the raw-text form is only valid as a labeled negative control; (b) inside `` !`…` `` template injections `$ARGUMENTS` expands like `\"$@\"` — one word per argument — so renderer scripts must join argv themselves.\n122: \n123: ### cli-opencode default invocation shape\n124: \n125: The skill builds every dispatch from a base shape and overlays use-case-specific flags:\n126: \n127: ```bash\n128: opencode run \\\n129:   --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n130:   --agent <agent-slug> \\\n131:   --variant high \\\n132:   --format json \\\n133:   --dir \"$REPO_ROOT\" \\\n134:   \"<prompt>\"\n135: ```\n136: \n137: | Flag | Default | Reason |\n138: |------|---------|--------|\n139: | `--model` | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` | Direct DeepSeek is the default provider — elevated reasoning at low cost; operator may override (e.g. `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash`, `kimi-for-coding/k2p7`, or any live OpenAI GPT-5.6 slug: `openai/gpt-5.6`, `openai/gpt-5.6-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna-pro`) |\n140: | `--agent` | per use case | Required for use case 1 / 3; optional for use case 2 |\n141: | `--variant high` | high | Routine cli-opencode dispatches benefit from elevated reasoning effort |\n142: | `--format json` | json | Structured event stream is what external runtimes parse |\n143: | `--dir` | repo root | Pin the working directory to avoid CWD ambiguity |\n144: \n145: ### Stdin handling — `</dev/null` is required for non-interactive dispatch\n146: \n147: > **opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation.** If you redirect stdout/stderr to files in automation (`> stdout.log 2> stderr.log`), opencode hangs at 0% CPU after the `+60s snapshot prune cleanup` log line because stdin remains attached to the parent terminal and never receives EOF.\n148: \n149: ALWAYS append `</dev/null` AFTER the prompt argument and BEFORE the stdout/stderr redirects:\n150: \n151: ```bash\n152: opencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" </dev/null > stdout.log 2> stderr.log\n153: #                                  ^^^^^^^^^^\n154: #                                  redirects stdin from /dev/null → immediate EOF\n155: ```\n156: \n157: Foreground `| tail` accidentally works because the upstream pipe stage provides closed stdin, but `> file 2> file` does not. See `references/integration-patterns.md` §6 for the full failure-mode + fix matrix and `../CHANGELOG-2026-05-08-tool-name-regex-fix.md` §Fix 4 for the discovery context.\n158: \n159: ### Sessions, share URLs, and ports\n160: \n161: `--share` publishes the session over the OpenCode share infrastructure. The skill ONLY appends `--share` for use case 2 (in-OpenCode parallel detached sessions). External-runtime dispatches do NOT publish share URLs by default.\n162: \n163: `--port` only matters when the dispatch needs to bind a known port (e.g. for a parallel detached session that another tool will attach to). The default random port is correct for one-shot dispatches.\n164: \n165: `--continue` and `--session <id>` reuse prior session state. `--fork` branches an existing session into a new one. cli-opencode uses session continuation in memory handback flows where the calling AI wants to thread context across multiple delegations.\n166: \n167: ### Provider Auth Pre-Flight (smart fallback)\n168: \n169: Before the first dispatch in a session, run a one-shot auth pre-flight against `opencode providers list` so a missing default doesn't fail mid-dispatch. Cache the result for the session; only re-run on auth failure.\n170: \n171: ```bash\n172: # Pre-flight — one call per session\n173: PROVIDERS=$(opencode providers list 2>&1)\n174: echo \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"deepseek\"            && DEEPSEEK_OK=1       || DEEPSEEK_OK=0\n175: echo \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"minimax-coding-plan\" && MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=1  || MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0   # MiniMax Token Plan (default MiniMax path)\n176: echo \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -qE \"minimax([^-]|$)\"    && MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1 || MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0  # MiniMax Direct API (pay-per-token); regex skips the coding-plan provider\n177: echo \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams\" && XIAOMI_OK=1       || XIAOMI_OK=0          # Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\n178: echo \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -qE \"xiaomi([^-]|$)\"     && XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1 || XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0   # Xiaomi Direct API (pay-per-token); regex skips the token-plan-ams provider\n179: echo \"default=$DEEPSEEK_OK minimax_token=$MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK minimax_direct=$MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK xiaomi=$XIAOMI_OK xiaomi_direct=$XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK\"\n180: ```\n181: \n182: | State | DEEPSEEK_OK | Action |\n183: |-------|-------------|--------|\n184: | Default available | 1 | Proceed with `--model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` |\n185: | Default missing | 0 | **ASK user** before substituting (offer A: openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro, B: login deepseek and retry, C: name a different model) — do not dispatch until configured |\n186: \n187: **MiniMax routing** (default = Token Plan; Direct API is the pay-per-token alternative):\n188: \n189: | State | Condition | Action |\n190: |-------|-----------|--------|\n191: | MiniMax requested (default) | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` — **omit `--agent`** (rejected on opencode 1.15.13) |\n192: | Token Plan not configured | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → MiniMax Token Plan — never substitute silently |\n193: | Direct API explicitly requested | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax/MiniMax-M3` (pay-per-token; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax`) |\n194: | Direct API requested, not configured | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to configure the `minimax` provider (`MINIMAX_API_KEY`) — do not substitute silently |\n195: \n196: **MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n197: \n198: | State | Condition | Action |\n199: |-------|-----------|--------|\n200: | MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13). Confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n201: | MiMo speed variant (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro tier, same prompt contract |\n202: | Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n203: | Token Plan not configured | `XIAOMI_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — never substitute silently |\n204: | Direct API explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` (pay-per-token; confirm live ids via `opencode models xiaomi`) |\n205: | Direct API requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n206: \n207: **Login / setup command shapes** (the AI surfaces these to the user; the user runs them in their own terminal):\n208: \n209: ```bash\n210: # Recommended default — direct DeepSeek API\n211: opencode providers login deepseek\n212: \n213: # MiniMax Token Plan — DEFAULT MiniMax path (subscription). Interactive: pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\".\n214: opencode auth login          # → provider minimax-coding-plan; Anthropic-compatible https://api.minimax.io/anthropic/v1 (China: api.minimaxi.com)\n215: \n216: # MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative (needs MINIMAX_API_KEY; platform endpoint https://api.minimax.io/v1)\n217: opencode providers login minimax\n218: \n219: # Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — provider-managed endpoint. Interactive: pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\".\n220: opencode auth login          # → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (Xiaomi Token Plan, Europe)\n221: \n222: # Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token alternative\n223: opencode providers login xiaomi\n224: \n225: # Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription. Interactive: pick \"Z.AI Coding Plan\".\n226: opencode auth login          # → provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\n227: ```\n228: \n229: > Do not mix region endpoints (international `minimax.io` vs China `minimaxi.com`). Confirm live model ids with `opencode models minimax-coding-plan`. The Xiaomi endpoint is provider-managed (no documented base URL — do not invent one); confirm live model ids with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Token Plan) or `opencode models xiaomi` (Direct API).\n230: \n231: **On auth-error mid-dispatch** (`401 Unauthorized`, `provider/model not found`): invalidate the cache, rerun the pre-flight, and apply the same decision tree before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.\n232: \n233: ### User-facing prompt templates\n234: \n235: Surface these verbatim to the operator when the pre-flight decision tree lands on \"ASK user\" (default missing with a fallback configured, or all providers missing). Never dispatch until the operator responds.\n236: \n237: **Default missing, fallback configured:**\n238: \n239: ```text\n240: The skill default `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` is not configured on this machine.\n241: A configured fallback is available. Pick one:\n242:   A) Use `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro --variant high` (OpenAI premium, configured now — paid)\n243:   B) Use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API, configured now) — or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` for latency-sensitive runs\n244:   C) Use `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (Kimi For Coding plan, configured now — subscription)\n245:   D) Run `opencode providers login deepseek` first, then retry the original dispatch\n246:   E) Name a different model — paste the `--model <provider/model>` you want to use\n247: ```\n248: \n249: **All providers missing:**\n250: \n251: ```text\n252: No supported providers are configured on this machine. Run one:\n253:   - `opencode providers login deepseek`     (recommended — default for cli-opencode)\n254:   - `opencode auth login`                   (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path; pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\" → provider minimax-coding-plan; model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3)\n255:   - `opencode providers login minimax`      (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token; needs MINIMAX_API_KEY; model minimax/MiniMax-M3)\n256:   - `opencode auth login`                   (Xiaomi Token Plan — default Xiaomi path; pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\" → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams; model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro)\n257:   - `opencode providers login xiaomi`       (Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; models xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro and xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed)\n258:   - `opencode auth login`                   (Kimi For Coding plan — Kimi/Moonshot coding subscription; provider kimi-for-coding; model kimi-for-coding/k2p7)\n259:   - `opencode auth login`                   (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription; provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2)\n260:   - `opencode providers login openai`       (OpenAI premium alternative — paid)\n261: Which would you like to set up? Confirm when login finishes; the skill will retry the original dispatch.\n262: ```\n263: \n264: **Error-recovery contract.** If a dispatch returns an auth error after pre-flight passed (credential expired or rotated), invalidate the cache, rerun the pre-flight, and apply the same decision tree before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ## 5. MODEL SELECTION\n269: \n270: OpenCode resolves models through configured providers. The cli-opencode skill supports `deepseek` (default), `minimax-coding-plan` (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path), `minimax` (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo, explicitly-selectable; NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead), and `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo: `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` + low-latency `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, pay-per-token) — confirmed against `opencode providers list` and `opencode models`. Run `opencode models [provider]` for the full live list on a given install.\n271: \n272: | Provider | Example model id | Use case |\n273: |----------|------------------|----------|\n274: | `deepseek` (DEFAULT) | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` | Default — deep reasoning at low cost via direct DeepSeek API |\n275: | `deepseek` | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` | Latency-optimized direct-API sibling |\n276: | `kimi-for-coding` | `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` | Long-context Kimi K2.7 Code (256k; subscription plan) |\n277: | `zai-coding-plan` | `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` | Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM-5.2 flagship long-horizon coding (1M context; subscription); omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models zai-coding-plan` |\n278: | `minimax-coding-plan` (DEFAULT MiniMax) | `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` | MiniMax Token Plan (subscription) — default MiniMax dispatch; omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models minimax-coding-plan` |\n279: | `minimax` | `minimax/MiniMax-M3` | MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative; needs `MINIMAX_API_KEY`; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax` |\n280: | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` | Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — MiMo-V2.5-Pro: 1M-token context, strongly agentic (1000+ tool calls), token-efficient; omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` |\n281: | `xiaomi` | `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` | Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; MiMo-V2.5-Pro; confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n282: \n283: `opencode models <provider>` lists every model id the provider exposes. The model string passed to `--model` is always `provider/model-id`.\n284: \n285: ### Reasoning effort via `--variant`\n286: \n287: The `--variant` flag maps to provider-specific reasoning effort. Underlying-model conventions apply per provider routing.\n288: \n289: | Provider | Variant values |\n290: |----------|----------------|\n291: | `deepseek` (`deepseek-v4-pro`) | reasoning effort accepted |\n292: | `deepseek` (`deepseek-v4-flash`) | non-reasoning — `--variant` ignored |\n293: | `minimax-coding-plan` / `minimax` (MiniMax-M3) | `--variant` behavior unverified — omitted by default; confirm against the MiniMax API before relying on it |\n294: | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (mimo-v2.5-pro) | `--variant` maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high); **always use `--variant high`** (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13) |\n295: | `zai-coding-plan` (glm-5.2) | GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it |\n296: | `openai` GPT-5.6 (`gpt-5.6` / `gpt-5.6-fast` / `gpt-5.6-pro` / `gpt-5.6-sol` / `gpt-5.6-sol-fast` / `gpt-5.6-sol-pro` / `gpt-5.6-terra` / `gpt-5.6-terra-fast` / `gpt-5.6-terra-pro` / `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-luna-fast` / `gpt-5.6-luna-pro`) | `--variant` maps to OpenAI reasoning effort — a separate lever from the model tier: `none`/`low`/`medium`/`high`/**`xhigh`** (Pro tiers — `gpt-5.6-pro` / `gpt-5.6-sol-pro` / `gpt-5.6-terra-pro` / `gpt-5.6-luna-pro`: `medium`/`high`/`xhigh` — **inferred from the now-retired `gpt-5.5-pro` mapping and unverified against the live catalog (which no longer lists `gpt-5.5-pro` to re-check); smoke-test a Pro slug at `--variant low` before relying on the restriction**). **The `-fast` slugs** (`gpt-5.6-fast` / `gpt-5.6-sol-fast` / `gpt-5.6-terra-fast` / `gpt-5.6-luna-fast`) are the low-latency **Fast** model tier (OpenAI `priority` service tier) with the same effort range — e.g. `--model openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast --variant xhigh`. `gpt-5.6-sol` is the flagship default; confirm live slugs via `opencode models openai`. |\n297: \n298: Default skill behavior: pass `--variant high` for cross-AI dispatches. Operators may override via the prompt template's variant field.\n299: \n300: ### Model-specific operational caveats\n301: \n302: - **Kimi K2.7 Code (`kimi-for-coding/k2p7`) over-exploration (observed 2026-06-17):** on broad / large-repo scopes at `--variant high`, k2p7 over-explores (many sequential reads) and can exceed a 600s timeout WITHOUT emitting — opencode flushes only the final assistant message to stdout, so a killed run yields 0 bytes (looks like a hang, but it was working). Mitigate with a hard read-cap in the prompt (\"read ≤N files then emit\") + a 1200s+ timeout, or omit `--variant`.\n303: - **GLM-5.2 (`zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`) latency variance (benchmark 008, n=45):** thinking-on drives latency variance 6–161s (avg ~26s) — budget generous timeouts; expect ~1/45 transient dispatch failures (retry the cell). Empirical prompt framework: COSTAR (benchmark 008).\n304: - **GLM-5.2 vision (image input):** `glm-5.2` is natively multimodal (vision-to-code), but `opencode run --file <image>` does NOT deliver images to this provider — upstream #20802 for custom OpenAI-compatible providers (confirmed 2026-06-28: `--file` → `NO_IMAGE_RECEIVED`). For image input use the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 `image_url` at `https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions`) — a deviation from this skill's dispatch path justified only by the verified #20802 breakage; see `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md` §7.\n305: \n306: ---\n307: \n308: ## 6. AGENT FLAG\n309: \n310: `--agent <slug>` loads an agent definition from `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` (project-local) or the user-level fallback. The agent definition's frontmatter pins the model, tool permissions, and system prompt that shape the dispatch.\n311: \n312: ### Discovering agents\n313: \n314: | Command | What it shows |\n315: |---------|---------------|\n316: | `opencode agent list` | All registered agent slugs across project + user scopes |\n317: | `opencode debug agent <slug>` | Resolved frontmatter and system prompt for a slug |\n318: | `opencode debug skill <slug>` | Skill resolution for a slug if the agent loads one |\n319: \n320: ### Agent slugs in this repo\n321: \n322: | Slug | Role |\n323: |------|------|\n324: | `general` | Implementation, default subagent |\n325: | `context` | Read-only retrieval and search |\n326: | `orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination |\n327: | `write` | Documentation generation |\n328: | `review` | Code review and PR analysis |\n329: | `debug` | Fresh-perspective debugging |\n330: | `deep-research` | Iterative research loop executor |\n331: | `deep-review` | Iterative code review loop executor |\n332: | `ai-council` | Multi-strategy planning |\n333: | `deep-improvement` | Agent improvement proposal mutator |\n334: \n335: The cli-opencode skill defers to the calling AI on agent selection — see `references/agent-delegation.md` for the routing matrix and `assets/prompt-templates.md` for canonical invocation shapes.\n336: \n337: ---\n338: \n339: ## 7. OUTPUT FORMAT AND EVENT STREAM\n340: \n341: `--format default` produces a human-formatted log. `--format json` emits a newline-delimited JSON event stream.\n342: \n343: ### JSON event shape (v1.3.17)\n344: \n345: Each line is a JSON object with at minimum:\n346: \n347: | Field | Meaning |\n348: |-------|---------|\n349: | `type` | Event type (`session.started`, `message.delta`, `tool.call`, `tool.result`, `session.completed`, ...) |\n350: | `timestamp` | ISO 8601 UTC timestamp |\n351: | `session_id` | The session id assigned by OpenCode |\n352: | `payload` | Type-specific payload |\n353: \n354: External runtimes parse the stream incrementally to surface tool calls, partial messages, and the final summary. cli-opencode prompt templates always pass `--format json` so the calling AI parses structured events instead of guessing format boundaries.\n355: \n356: ---\n357: \n358: ## 8. STATE LOCATION AND SHARE URLS\n359: \n360: ### State directory\n361: \n362: OpenCode persists session state in a shared SQLite database and storage tree under `~/.local/share/opencode/`:\n363: \n364: - `opencode.db` (`-shm`/`-wal` companions) — the session/message database\n365: - `storage/` — per-session structured artifacts\n366: - `snapshot/` — working-tree snapshots\n367: \n368: There is no per-session directory under `~/.opencode/state/<session_id>/` on a standard install — that path does not exist on this runtime layout. To inspect a specific session, use `opencode export <session_id>` (§3) rather than reading files from a state directory. The cli-opencode self-invocation guard's Layer 3 lock-file probe (`~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock`, per ADR-001) targets the older path as a best-effort third layer on top of the env-var and process-ancestry checks; treat it as a heuristic, not a verified-present artifact, on installs where `~/.opencode/state/` does not exist.\n369: \n370: ### Share URLs\n371: \n372: `--share` publishes a session URL via OpenCode's share infrastructure. The skill ONLY appends `--share` for use case 2 (in-OpenCode parallel detached sessions). The CHK-033 P1 checklist item requires operator confirmation before publishing a share URL because the URL exposes the session contents.\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ## 9. VERSION DRIFT\n377: \n378: This reference is pinned to OpenCode v1.3.17. If the live binary reports a different version, do the following:\n379: \n380: 1. Run `opencode run --help` and diff the flag list against Section 4.\n381: 2. Run `opencode --help` and diff the subcommand list against Section 3.\n382: 3. If a flag was renamed, prefer the new name in the dispatch. If a flag was removed, fall back to the closest analogue and surface the drift in the calling AI's response.\n383: 4. If the operator's machine has a major version bump (v1.4+, v2.x), re-validate the entire skill against the new flag table and bump the cli-opencode minor version.\n384: \n385: ### Failure modes specific to drift\n386: \n387: | Symptom | Likely cause |\n388: |---------|--------------|\n389: | `unknown option --variant` | v1.2 or earlier — variant flag was named `--reasoning` |\n390: | `unknown option --share` | Older standalone build without share infrastructure |\n391: | `unknown option --format json` | v1.0 — JSON event stream was the default and the flag did not exist |\n392: | `MODULE_NOT_FOUND` | Plugin loader crash; rerun with `--pure` to bypass plugins |\n393: \n394: ---\n395: \n396: ## 10. TROUBLESHOOTING\n397: \n398: | Symptom | Cause | Fix |\n399: |---------|-------|-----|\n400: | `command not found: opencode` | Binary not on PATH | Install via standalone installer or `brew install opencode` |\n401: | `OPENCODE_SERVER_PASSWORD required` | Server enforces basic auth | Pass `-p <password>` or set the env var |\n402: | `provider/model not found` | Provider not configured | Run `opencode providers` to enumerate, then `auth login <provider>` |\n403: | Empty output stream | `--format default` with non-TTY parent | Pass `--format json` and parse the event stream |\n404: | Session never finishes | Tool call hung | Run `opencode export <session_id>` and inspect the message log it returns |\n405: | Plugin load crash | Misconfigured plugin | Rerun with `--pure` to bypass all plugins |\n406: | Self-invocation refused | cli-opencode detected an in-OpenCode runtime | Use a sibling cli-* skill or a fresh shell session — see ADR-001 |\n407: | `--share` URL leaks | Share infrastructure published a session containing secrets | Operator MUST confirm before publishing per CHK-033 |\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: ## 11. RELATED RESOURCES\n412: \n413: - `./integration-patterns.md` - The three documented use cases and their copy-paste invocation shapes\n414: - `./agent-delegation.md` - Agent routing matrix and invocation patterns\n415: - `./opencode-tools.md` - Unique capabilities (full plugin/skill/MCP runtime, parallel detached sessions)\n416: - `../assets/prompt-templates.md` - Copy-paste prompt templates per use case\n417: - `../assets/prompt-quality-card.md` - Framework selection and CLEAR 5-check\n418: - `../SKILL.md` - Skill entry point and smart router\n\n(End of file - total 418 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"OpenCode CLI - Complete Command Reference\"\ndescription: \"Comprehensive reference for OpenCode CLI subcommands, flags, models, configuration, agent flags, sandbox boundaries, and troubleshooting. Pinned to v1.3.17.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"opencode cli reference\"\n  - \"opencode run flags\"\n  - \"opencode model selection\"\n  - \"opencode provider auth pre-flight\"\n  - \"opencode variant reasoning effort\"\n  - \"opencode version drift\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.3.0.29\n---\n\n# OpenCode CLI - Complete Command Reference\n\nComprehensive reference for the OpenCode CLI binary, every subcommand the cli-opencode skill dispatches against, the flag set it relies on, the agent surface it can target, and the failure modes that need explicit handling. Pinned to v1.3.17 baseline.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/cli-reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"OpenCode CLI - Complete Command Reference\"\ndescription: \"Comprehensive reference for OpenCode CLI subcommands, flags, models, configuration, agent flags, sandbox boundaries, and troubleshooting. Pinned to v1.3.17.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"opencode cli reference\"\n  - \"opencode run flags\"\n  - \"opencode model selection\"\n  - \"opencode provider auth pre-flight\"\n  - \"opencode variant reasoning effort\"\n  - \"opencode version drift\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.3.0.29\n---\n\n# OpenCode CLI - Complete Command Reference\n\nComprehensive reference for the OpenCode CLI binary, every subcommand the cli-opencode skill dispatches against, the flag set it relies on, the agent surface it can target, and the failure modes that need explicit handling. Pinned to v1.3.17 baseline.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Core Principle\n\nOpenCode is the framework that owns this repository. The same binary that hosts the operator's TUI session also accepts non-interactive invocations through `opencode run`. The cli-opencode skill calls `opencode run` from external runtimes (Claude Code, OpenCode, Copilot, raw shell) so the calling AI can dispatch a task into a fresh OpenCode session that loads the full plugin, skill, MCP, and Spec Kit Memory runtime.\n\n### Purpose\n\nProvide a single-source reference for the OpenCode CLI surface — every subcommand cli-opencode invokes, every flag it pins, every agent it can route to, the version baseline it is built against, and the error envelopes that need explicit recovery.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Looking up an OpenCode CLI subcommand or flag during a delegation\n- Selecting a model + variant + agent for a dispatch\n- Confirming the version baseline before pinning a flag set\n- Troubleshooting a failed `opencode run` invocation\n- Confirming the self-invocation guard signal against the live binary\n\n### Key Sources\n\n| Source | URL |\n|--------|-----|\n| **Binary** | `$(command -v opencode)` (typically `~/.superset/bin/opencode` or another local bin path) |\n| **Repository** | https://github.com/sst/opencode |\n| **Version baseline** | v1.3.17 (pinned in this reference) |\n| **Runtime** | Node.js 18+ for the npm install path; standalone binary on macOS |\n\n---\n\n## 2. INSTALLATION\n\n| Method | Command | Notes |\n|--------|---------|-------|\n| **Standalone** | `curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install \\| bash` | macOS / Linux installer |\n| **Homebrew** | `brew install opencode` | macOS package manager |\n| **npm global** | `npm install -g opencode-ai` | Cross-platform when Node.js 18+ is present |\n| **Upgrade** | `opencode upgrade [target]` | Pin a specific version with the `target` argument |\n| **Uninstall** | `opencode uninstall` | Removes the binary and related state |\n\nAfter installation, run `opencode --version` to confirm. The cli-opencode skill is pinned to v1.3.17. Newer binaries may add or rename flags — consult Section 9 (Version Drift) before relying on a non-pinned flag.\n\n---\n\n## 3. SUBCOMMAND MAP\n\nOpenCode exposes a multi-subcommand surface. The cli-opencode skill primarily invokes `run`, with secondary use of `serve`, `web`, `agent`, and `debug`.\n\n| Subcommand | Purpose | Invoked by cli-opencode |\n|------------|---------|-------------------------|\n| `opencode` (default) | Start the TUI in the current project | No (interactive only) |\n| `opencode run [message..]` | Non-interactive single-shot dispatch | YES (canonical use case) |\n| `opencode serve` | Start a headless server | YES (for parallel detached sessions) |\n| `opencode web` | Start a server plus open the web interface | YES (when the operator wants a browser surface) |\n| `opencode acp` | Start an ACP (Agent Client Protocol) server | No (specialized integration path) |\n| `opencode attach <url>` | Attach to a running OpenCode server | YES (for share-URL flows) |\n| `opencode agent` | Manage agent definitions | YES (for agent listing) |\n| `opencode debug` | Debugging and troubleshooting tools | YES (for `debug skill` and `debug agent` listings) |\n| `opencode mcp` | Manage MCP server registrations | No |\n| `opencode providers` (alias `auth`) | Manage AI providers and credentials | No (operator-driven setup) |\n| `opencode models [provider]` | List available models | YES (for capability discovery) |\n| `opencode session` | Manage sessions | No (state inspection only) |\n| `opencode export [sessionID]` | Export session data as JSON | YES (for memory handback flows) |\n| `opencode stats` | Token and cost statistics | No |\n| `opencode db` | Database tools | No |\n| `opencode plugin <module>` (alias `plug`) | Install a plugin | No (operator-driven setup) |\n| `opencode upgrade [target]` | Upgrade the binary | No (operator-driven) |\n| `opencode uninstall` | Uninstall the binary | No (operator-driven) |\n\n---\n\n## 4. `opencode run` FLAGS\n\n`opencode run [message..]` is the canonical non-interactive entry point. The cli-opencode skill builds every dispatch around this subcommand.\n\n### Core flags\n\n| Flag / Option | Type | Purpose |\n|---------------|------|---------|\n| `[message..]` | positional | One or more positional message strings |\n| `--print-logs` | boolean | Stream logs to stderr |\n| `--log-level` | enum | `DEBUG`, `INFO`, `WARN`, `ERROR` |\n| `--pure` | boolean | Run without external plugins (skill loads disabled) |\n| `--command` | string | Run a known command, the message becomes its args |\n| `-c`, `--continue` | boolean | Continue the last session in this project |\n| `-s`, `--session` | string | Continue a specific session id |\n| `--fork` | boolean | Fork before continuing — requires `--continue` or `--session` |\n| `--share` | boolean | Publish a shareable URL for this session |\n| `-m`, `--model` | string | Provider/model selector — e.g. `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` |\n| `--agent` | string | Agent slug (loads from `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md`) |\n| `--format` | enum | `default` (formatted) or `json` (raw event stream) |\n| `-f`, `--file` | array | Attach files to the message |\n| `--title` | string | Session title (truncated message used when omitted) |\n| `--attach` | string | Attach to a running OpenCode server URL |\n| `-p`, `--password` | string | Basic auth password (or `OPENCODE_SERVER_PASSWORD`) |\n| `--dir` | string | Working directory or remote-server path |\n| `--port` | number | Local server port (random when omitted) |\n| `--variant` | string | Provider-specific reasoning effort (`high`, `max`, `minimal`, etc.) |\n| `--thinking` | boolean | Show thinking blocks (default false) |\n\n> **`--command` semantics (verified on v1.17.4):** the `run` message is plain text — slash-command syntax inside it (`opencode run \"/memory:search query\"`) is NOT expanded, so the command's template never reaches the model. Executing a registered command non-interactively requires `--command <family>/<name>` with the args as the message (they become `$ARGUMENTS`). Registry names are slash-namespaced (`memory/search` for `/memory:search`); a wrong name fails with the full registry list. Behavior probes of slash commands MUST use `--command`; the raw-text form only measures the model freestyling without the contract. Consequences: (a) any behavior/adherence probe of a slash command MUST use `--command`, and the raw-text form is only valid as a labeled negative control; (b) inside `` !`…` `` template injections `$ARGUMENTS` expands like `\"$@\"` — one word per argument — so renderer scripts must join argv themselves.\n\n### cli-opencode default invocation shape\n\nThe skill builds every dispatch from a base shape and overlays use-case-specific flags:\n\n```bash\nopencode run \\\n  --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n  --agent <agent-slug> \\\n  --variant high \\\n  --format json \\\n  --dir \"$REPO_ROOT\" \\\n  \"<prompt>\"\n```\n\n| Flag | Default | Reason |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| `--model` | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` | Direct DeepSeek is the default provider — elevated reasoning at low cost; operator may override (e.g. `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash`, `kimi-for-coding/k2p7`, or any live OpenAI GPT-5.6 slug: `openai/gpt-5.6`, `openai/gpt-5.6-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna-pro`) |\n| `--agent` | per use case | Required for use case 1 / 3; optional for use case 2 |\n| `--variant high` | high | Routine cli-opencode dispatches benefit from elevated reasoning effort |\n| `--format json` | json | Structured event stream is what external runtimes parse |\n| `--dir` | repo root | Pin the working directory to avoid CWD ambiguity |\n\n### Stdin handling — `</dev/null` is required for non-interactive dispatch\n\n> **opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation.** If you redirect stdout/stderr to files in automation (`> stdout.log 2> stderr.log`), opencode hangs at 0% CPU after the `+60s snapshot prune cleanup` log line because stdin remains attached to the parent terminal and never receives EOF.\n\nALWAYS append `</dev/null` AFTER the prompt argument and BEFORE the stdout/stderr redirects:\n\n```bash\nopencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" </dev/null > stdout.log 2> stderr.log\n#                                  ^^^^^^^^^^\n#                                  redirects stdin from /dev/null → immediate EOF\n```\n\nForeground `| tail` accidentally works because the upstream pipe stage provides closed stdin, but `> file 2> file` does not. See `references/integration-patterns.md` §6 for the full failure-mode + fix matrix and `../CHANGELOG-2026-05-08-tool-name-regex-fix.md` §Fix 4 for the discovery context.\n\n### Sessions, share URLs, and ports\n\n`--share` publishes the session over the OpenCode share infrastructure. The skill ONLY appends `--share` for use case 2 (in-OpenCode parallel detached sessions). External-runtime dispatches do NOT publish share URLs by default.\n\n`--port` only matters when the dispatch needs to bind a known port (e.g. for a parallel detached session that another tool will attach to). The default random port is correct for one-shot dispatches.\n\n`--continue` and `--session <id>` reuse prior session state. `--fork` branches an existing session into a new one. cli-opencode uses session continuation in memory handback flows where the calling AI wants to thread context across multiple delegations.\n\n### Provider Auth Pre-Flight (smart fallback)\n\nBefore the first dispatch in a session, run a one-shot auth pre-flight against `opencode providers list` so a missing default doesn't fail mid-dispatch. Cache the result for the session; only re-run on auth failure.\n\n```bash\n# Pre-flight — one call per session\nPROVIDERS=$(opencode providers list 2>&1)\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"deepseek\"            && DEEPSEEK_OK=1       || DEEPSEEK_OK=0\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"minimax-coding-plan\" && MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=1  || MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0   # MiniMax Token Plan (default MiniMax path)\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -qE \"minimax([^-]|$)\"    && MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1 || MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0  # MiniMax Direct API (pay-per-token); regex skips the coding-plan provider\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -q \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams\" && XIAOMI_OK=1       || XIAOMI_OK=0          # Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\necho \"$PROVIDERS\" | grep -qE \"xiaomi([^-]|$)\"     && XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1 || XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0   # Xiaomi Direct API (pay-per-token); regex skips the token-plan-ams provider\necho \"default=$DEEPSEEK_OK minimax_token=$MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK minimax_direct=$MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK xiaomi=$XIAOMI_OK xiaomi_direct=$XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK\"\n```\n\n| State | DEEPSEEK_OK | Action |\n|-------|-------------|--------|\n| Default available | 1 | Proceed with `--model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` |\n| Default missing | 0 | **ASK user** before substituting (offer A: openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro, B: login deepseek and retry, C: name a different model) — do not dispatch until configured |\n\n**MiniMax routing** (default = Token Plan; Direct API is the pay-per-token alternative):\n\n| State | Condition | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| MiniMax requested (default) | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` — **omit `--agent`** (rejected on opencode 1.15.13) |\n| Token Plan not configured | `MINIMAX_TOKEN_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → MiniMax Token Plan — never substitute silently |\n| Direct API explicitly requested | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model minimax/MiniMax-M3` (pay-per-token; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax`) |\n| Direct API requested, not configured | `MINIMAX_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to configure the `minimax` provider (`MINIMAX_API_KEY`) — do not substitute silently |\n\n**MiMo routing** (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe and Xiaomi Direct API; explicitly-selectable — first match wins):\n\n| State | Condition | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| MiMo requested (default) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` — **omit `--agent`** (`--agent general` warns and falls back on opencode 1.15.13). Confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n| MiMo speed variant (\"ultraspeed\", latency-sensitive) | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` — low-latency MiMo-V2.5-Pro tier, same prompt contract |\n| Token Plan explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_OK=1` | `--model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` — NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead |\n| Token Plan not configured | `XIAOMI_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode auth login` → Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — never substitute silently |\n| Direct API explicitly requested | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=1` | Proceed with `--model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` (pay-per-token; confirm live ids via `opencode models xiaomi`) |\n| Direct API requested, not configured | `XIAOMI_DIRECT_OK=0` | **ASK user** to run `opencode providers login xiaomi` — never substitute silently |\n\n**Login / setup command shapes** (the AI surfaces these to the user; the user runs them in their own terminal):\n\n```bash\n# Recommended default — direct DeepSeek API\nopencode providers login deepseek\n\n# MiniMax Token Plan — DEFAULT MiniMax path (subscription). Interactive: pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\".\nopencode auth login          # → provider minimax-coding-plan; Anthropic-compatible https://api.minimax.io/anthropic/v1 (China: api.minimaxi.com)\n\n# MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative (needs MINIMAX_API_KEY; platform endpoint https://api.minimax.io/v1)\nopencode providers login minimax\n\n# Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — provider-managed endpoint. Interactive: pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\".\nopencode auth login          # → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (Xiaomi Token Plan, Europe)\n\n# Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token alternative\nopencode providers login xiaomi\n\n# Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription. Interactive: pick \"Z.AI Coding Plan\".\nopencode auth login          # → provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\n```\n\n> Do not mix region endpoints (international `minimax.io` vs China `minimaxi.com`). Confirm live model ids with `opencode models minimax-coding-plan`. The Xiaomi endpoint is provider-managed (no documented base URL — do not invent one); confirm live model ids with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Token Plan) or `opencode models xiaomi` (Direct API).\n\n**On auth-error mid-dispatch** (`401 Unauthorized`, `provider/model not found`): invalidate the cache, rerun the pre-flight, and apply the same decision tree before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.\n\n### User-facing prompt templates\n\nSurface these verbatim to the operator when the pre-flight decision tree lands on \"ASK user\" (default missing with a fallback configured, or all providers missing). Never dispatch until the operator responds.\n\n**Default missing, fallback configured:**\n\n```text\nThe skill default `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` is not configured on this machine.\nA configured fallback is available. Pick one:\n  A) Use `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro --variant high` (OpenAI premium, configured now — paid)\n  B) Use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API, configured now) — or `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` for latency-sensitive runs\n  C) Use `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (Kimi For Coding plan, configured now — subscription)\n  D) Run `opencode providers login deepseek` first, then retry the original dispatch\n  E) Name a different model — paste the `--model <provider/model>` you want to use\n```\n\n**All providers missing:**\n\n```text\nNo supported providers are configured on this machine. Run one:\n  - `opencode providers login deepseek`     (recommended — default for cli-opencode)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path; pick \"MiniMax Token Plan (minimax.io)\" → provider minimax-coding-plan; model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3)\n  - `opencode providers login minimax`      (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token; needs MINIMAX_API_KEY; model minimax/MiniMax-M3)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Xiaomi Token Plan — default Xiaomi path; pick \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)\" → provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams; model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro)\n  - `opencode providers login xiaomi`       (Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; models xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro and xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Kimi For Coding plan — Kimi/Moonshot coding subscription; provider kimi-for-coding; model kimi-for-coding/k2p7)\n  - `opencode auth login`                   (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM coding subscription; provider zai-coding-plan; model zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2)\n  - `opencode providers login openai`       (OpenAI premium alternative — paid)\nWhich would you like to set up? Confirm when login finishes; the skill will retry the original dispatch.\n```\n\n**Error-recovery contract.** If a dispatch returns an auth error after pre-flight passed (credential expired or rotated), invalidate the cache, rerun the pre-flight, and apply the same decision tree before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.\n\n---\n\n## 5. MODEL SELECTION\n\nOpenCode resolves models through configured providers. The cli-opencode skill supports `deepseek` (default), `minimax-coding-plan` (MiniMax Token Plan — default MiniMax path), `minimax` (MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo, explicitly-selectable; NOTE: observed not resolving on this install 2026-06-11 (ProviderModelNotFoundError surfaced as 'Unexpected server error'); re-auth via `opencode auth login` or use the `xiaomi` Direct API instead), and `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo: `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` + low-latency `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, pay-per-token) — confirmed against `opencode providers list` and `opencode models`. Run `opencode models [provider]` for the full live list on a given install.\n\n| Provider | Example model id | Use case |\n|----------|------------------|----------|\n| `deepseek` (DEFAULT) | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` | Default — deep reasoning at low cost via direct DeepSeek API |\n| `deepseek` | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` | Latency-optimized direct-API sibling |\n| `kimi-for-coding` | `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` | Long-context Kimi K2.7 Code (256k; subscription plan) |\n| `zai-coding-plan` | `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` | Z.AI GLM Coding Plan — GLM-5.2 flagship long-horizon coding (1M context; subscription); omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models zai-coding-plan` |\n| `minimax-coding-plan` (DEFAULT MiniMax) | `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` | MiniMax Token Plan (subscription) — default MiniMax dispatch; omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models minimax-coding-plan` |\n| `minimax` | `minimax/MiniMax-M3` | MiniMax Direct API — pay-per-token alternative; needs `MINIMAX_API_KEY`; confirm the live id via `opencode models minimax` |\n| `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` | `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` | Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — MiMo-V2.5-Pro: 1M-token context, strongly agentic (1000+ tool calls), token-efficient; omit `--agent`; verify with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` |\n| `xiaomi` | `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` | Xiaomi Direct API — pay-per-token; MiMo-V2.5-Pro; confirm the live id via `opencode models xiaomi` |\n\n`opencode models <provider>` lists every model id the provider exposes. The model string passed to `--model` is always `provider/model-id`.\n\n### Reasoning effort via `--variant`\n\nThe `--variant` flag maps to provider-specific reasoning effort. Underlying-model conventions apply per provider routing.\n\n| Provider | Variant values |\n|----------|----------------|\n| `deepseek` (`deepseek-v4-pro`) | reasoning effort accepted |\n| `deepseek` (`deepseek-v4-flash`) | non-reasoning — `--variant` ignored |\n| `minimax-coding-plan` / `minimax` (MiniMax-M3) | `--variant` behavior unverified — omitted by default; confirm against the MiniMax API before relying on it |\n| `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (mimo-v2.5-pro) | `--variant` maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high); **always use `--variant high`** (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13) |\n| `zai-coding-plan` (glm-5.2) | GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified — smoke-test before relying on it |\n| `openai` GPT-5.6 (`gpt-5.6` / `gpt-5.6-fast` / `gpt-5.6-pro` / `gpt-5.6-sol` / `gpt-5.6-sol-fast` / `gpt-5.6-sol-pro` / `gpt-5.6-terra` / `gpt-5.6-terra-fast` / `gpt-5.6-terra-pro` / `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-luna-fast` / `gpt-5.6-luna-pro`) | `--variant` maps to OpenAI reasoning effort — a separate lever from the model tier: `none`/`low`/`medium`/`high`/**`xhigh`** (Pro tiers — `gpt-5.6-pro` / `gpt-5.6-sol-pro` / `gpt-5.6-terra-pro` / `gpt-5.6-luna-pro`: `medium`/`high`/`xhigh` — **inferred from the now-retired `gpt-5.5-pro` mapping and unverified against the live catalog (which no longer lists `gpt-5.5-pro` to re-check); smoke-test a Pro slug at `--variant low` before relying on the restriction**). **The `-fast` slugs** (`gpt-5.6-fast` / `gpt-5.6-sol-fast` / `gpt-5.6-terra-fast` / `gpt-5.6-luna-fast`) are the low-latency **Fast** model tier (OpenAI `priority` service tier) with the same effort range — e.g. `--model openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast --variant xhigh`. `gpt-5.6-sol` is the flagship default; confirm live slugs via `opencode models openai`. |\n\nDefault skill behavior: pass `--variant high` for cross-AI dispatches. Operators may override via the prompt template's variant field.\n\n### Model-specific operational caveats\n\n- **Kimi K2.7 Code (`kimi-for-coding/k2p7`) over-exploration (observed 2026-06-17):** on broad / large-repo scopes at `--variant high`, k2p7 over-explores (many sequential reads) and can exceed a 600s timeout WITHOUT emitting — opencode flushes only the final assistant message to stdout, so a killed run yields 0 bytes (looks like a hang, but it was working). Mitigate with a hard read-cap in the prompt (\"read ≤N files then emit\") + a 1200s+ timeout, or omit `--variant`.\n- **GLM-5.2 (`zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`) latency variance (benchmark 008, n=45):** thinking-on drives latency variance 6–161s (avg ~26s) — budget generous timeouts; expect ~1/45 transient dispatch failures (retry the cell). Empirical prompt framework: COSTAR (benchmark 008).\n- **GLM-5.2 vision (image input):** `glm-5.2` is natively multimodal (vision-to-code), but `opencode run --file <image>` does NOT deliver images to this provider — upstream #20802 for custom OpenAI-compatible providers (confirmed 2026-06-28: `--file` → `NO_IMAGE_RECEIVED`). For image input use the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 `image_url` at `https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions`) — a deviation from this skill's dispatch path justified only by the verified #20802 breakage; see `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md` §7.\n\n---\n\n## 6. AGENT FLAG\n\n`--agent <slug>` loads an agent definition from `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` (project-local) or the user-level fallback. The agent definition's frontmatter pins the model, tool permissions, and system prompt that shape the dispatch.\n\n### Discovering agents\n\n| Command | What it shows |\n|---------|---------------|\n| `opencode agent list` | All registered agent slugs across project + user scopes |\n| `opencode debug agent <slug>` | Resolved frontmatter and system prompt for a slug |\n| `opencode debug skill <slug>` | Skill resolution for a slug if the agent loads one |\n\n### Agent slugs in this repo\n\n| Slug | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `general` | Implementation, default subagent |\n| `context` | Read-only retrieval and search |\n| `orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination |\n| `write` | Documentation generation |\n| `review` | Code review and PR analysis |\n| `debug` | Fresh-perspective debugging |\n| `deep-research` | Iterative research loop executor |\n| `deep-review` | Iterative code review loop executor |\n| `ai-council` | Multi-strategy planning |\n| `deep-improvement` | Agent improvement proposal mutator |\n\nThe cli-opencode skill defers to the calling AI on agent selection — see `references/agent-delegation.md` for the routing matrix and `assets/prompt-templates.md` for canonical invocation shapes.\n\n---\n\n## 7. OUTPUT FORMAT AND EVENT STREAM\n\n`--format default` produces a human-formatted log. `--format json` emits a newline-delimited JSON event stream.\n\n### JSON event shape (v1.3.17)\n\nEach line is a JSON object with at minimum:\n\n| Field | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| `type` | Event type (`session.started`, `message.delta`, `tool.call`, `tool.result`, `session.completed`, ...) |\n| `timestamp` | ISO 8601 UTC timestamp |\n| `session_id` | The session id assigned by OpenCode |\n| `payload` | Type-specific payload |\n\nExternal runtimes parse the stream incrementally to surface tool calls, partial messages, and the final summary. cli-opencode prompt templates always pass `--format json` so the calling AI parses structured events instead of guessing format boundaries.\n\n---\n\n## 8. STATE LOCATION AND SHARE URLS\n\n### State directory\n\nOpenCode persists session state in a shared SQLite database and storage tree under `~/.local/share/opencode/`:\n\n- `opencode.db` (`-shm`/`-wal` companions) — the session/message database\n- `storage/` — per-session structured artifacts\n- `snapshot/` — working-tree snapshots\n\nThere is no per-session directory under `~/.opencode/state/<session_id>/` on a standard install — that path does not exist on this runtime layout. To inspect a specific session, use `opencode export <session_id>` (§3) rather than reading files from a state directory. The cli-opencode self-invocation guard's Layer 3 lock-file probe (`~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock`, per ADR-001) targets the older path as a best-effort third layer on top of the env-var and process-ancestry checks; treat it as a heuristic, not a verified-present artifact, on installs where `~/.opencode/state/` does not exist.\n\n### Share URLs\n\n`--share` publishes a session URL via OpenCode's share infrastructure. The skill ONLY appends `--share` for use case 2 (in-OpenCode parallel detached sessions). The CHK-033 P1 checklist item requires operator confirmation before publishing a share URL because the URL exposes the session contents.\n\n---\n\n## 9. VERSION DRIFT\n\nThis reference is pinned to OpenCode v1.3.17. If the live binary reports a different version, do the following:\n\n1. Run `opencode run --help` and diff the flag list against Section 4.\n2. Run `opencode --help` and diff the subcommand list against Section 3.\n3. If a flag was renamed, prefer the new name in the dispatch. If a flag was removed, fall back to the closest analogue and surface the drift in the calling AI's response.\n4. If the operator's machine has a major version bump (v1.4+, v2.x), re-validate the entire skill against the new flag table and bump the cli-opencode minor version.\n\n### Failure modes specific to drift\n\n| Symptom | Likely cause |\n|---------|--------------|\n| `unknown option --variant` | v1.2 or earlier — variant flag was named `--reasoning` |\n| `unknown option --share` | Older standalone build without share infrastructure |\n| `unknown option --format json` | v1.0 — JSON event stream was the default and the flag did not exist |\n| `MODULE_NOT_FOUND` | Plugin loader crash; rerun with `--pure` to bypass plugins |\n\n---\n\n## 10. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| Symptom | Cause | Fix |\n|---------|-------|-----|\n| `command not found: opencode` | Binary not on PATH | Install via standalone installer or `brew install opencode` |\n| `OPENCODE_SERVER_PASSWORD required` | Server enforces basic auth | Pass `-p <password>` or set the env var |\n| `provider/model not found` | Provider not configured | Run `opencode providers` to enumerate, then `auth login <provider>` |\n| Empty output stream | `--format default` with non-TTY parent | Pass `--format json` and parse the event stream |\n| Session never finishes | Tool call hung | Run `opencode export <session_id>` and inspect the message log it returns |\n| Plugin load crash | Misconfigured plugin | Rerun with `--pure` to bypass all plugins |\n| Self-invocation refused | cli-opencode detected an in-OpenCode runtime | Use a sibling cli-* skill or a fresh shell session — see ADR-001 |\n| `--share` URL leaks | Share infrastructure published a session containing secrets | Operator MUST confirm before publishing per CHK-033 |\n\n---\n\n## 11. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `./integration-patterns.md` - The three documented use cases and their copy-paste invocation shapes\n- `./agent-delegation.md` - Agent routing matrix and invocation patterns\n- `./opencode-tools.md` - Unique capabilities (full plugin/skill/MCP runtime, parallel detached sessions)\n- `../assets/prompt-templates.md` - Copy-paste prompt templates per use case\n- `../assets/prompt-quality-card.md` - Framework selection and CLEAR 5-check\n- `../SKILL.md` - Skill entry point and smart router","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":418,"totalLines":418,"truncated":false}},"title":".claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/cli-reference.md","time":{"start":1784521056928,"end":1784521057003}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05885a86d8766c27016a5da160cebc81919aab1952a42d1d4d"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe628c001218YSZlNtsQHa4","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe41d8001jJnEYh1TJPFDC2"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521057019,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_W0h3G8iB77qA3r0RpfN5zVVW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/prompt-quality-card.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/prompt-quality-card.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: OpenCode CLI — Prompt Quality Card\n3: description: Fast-path prompt discipline for OpenCode CLI dispatches; frameworks and CLEAR are canonical in sk-prompt.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"opencode prompt quality card\"\n6:   - \"opencode model overrides\"\n7:   - \"minimax tidd-ec dense pre-plan\"\n8:   - \"mimo costar lean prompt\"\n9:   - \"opencode dispatch framework precedence\"\n10: importance_tier: normal\n11: contextType: planning\n12: version: 1.3.0.21\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # OpenCode CLI — Prompt Quality Card\n16: \n17: Fast-path dispatch discipline for `opencode run` prompts. The 7-framework table, task-to-framework map, pre-planning-density / bundle-gate / anti-hallucination notes, and the CLEAR 5-question check are owned by the canonical card — do not inline them here.\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: ### Purpose\n22: \n23: This card is the OpenCode CLI fast-path prompt-quality reference; it delegates the framework table + CLEAR check to the canonical card and records only OpenCode-specific model overrides plus the precedence rule.\n24: \n25: ### Usage\n26: \n27: Compose a dispatch prompt by starting from the shared layer (canonical card), applying the OpenCode model overrides, and following the precedence rule.\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## 2. SHARED LAYER (DELEGATED — DO NOT INLINE)\n32: \n33: The 7-framework selection table, the task->framework map, the pre-planning-density / bundle-gate / anti-hallucination notes, and the CLEAR 5-question check are OWNED by the canonical card. Do NOT copy them here.\n34: \n35: -> `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md`  (deep theory: `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-improve/references/patterns-evaluation.md`)\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 3. OPENCODE MODEL OVERRIDES\n40: \n41: OpenCode dispatches the MiniMax, MiMo, DeepSeek-v4-pro, and Kimi-K2.7 small models, which override or default against the cross-model defaults from the canonical card:\n42: \n43: | Model (dispatchable here) | Override | Profile |\n44: |---|---|---|\n45: | MiniMax M3 (Token Plan default) | TIDD-EC + dense | `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md` |\n46: | MiniMax M3 (Direct API) | TIDD-EC + dense | `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md` |\n47: | MiMo V2.5 Pro (Token Plan) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n48: | MiMo V2.5 Pro (Direct API) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n49: | MiMo V2.5 Pro UltraSpeed (Direct API, low-latency) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n50: | GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan) | COSTAR + lean (empirical, benchmark 008) | [`glm-5.2.md`](../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md) |\n51: | deepseek-v4-pro / kimi-k2.7-code | default RCAF (no model-specific benchmark; shared default-unverified note) | [`deepseek-v4-pro.md`](../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/deepseek-v4-pro.md) · [`kimi-k2.7-code.md`](../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/kimi-k2.7-code.md) |\n52: \n53: **Executor notes:** Omit `--agent` for all small-model dispatches listed above. OpenCode maps `--variant low/medium/high` to MiMo's reasoning effort; `high` is the standing default for MiMo. MiniMax Token Plan (`minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`) and Direct API (`minimax/MiniMax-M3`) both serve M3. Xiaomi Token Plan (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`) and Direct API (`xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`) both serve MiMo-V2.5-Pro; the Direct API additionally serves `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, a low-latency tier with the same prompt contract. Ambiguous use-case (1 vs 2 vs 3) prevents the router from picking a path — resolve before dispatch. Always include a self-invocation guard signal when the dispatched session could loop back.\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 4. DELEGATION / PRECEDENCE\n58: \n59: The 3-tier precedence rule (fast path -> model override -> deep path) is canonical in `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md` and restated in `../SKILL.md`.\n60: \n61: OpenCode-specific escalation example: if the task would otherwise need a long `opencode run` prompt plus an explicit Memory Epilogue and a parallel-session decision, ask `@prompt-improver` for the final `ENHANCED_PROMPT` first, then pass that result to OpenCode.\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## 5. RELATED RESOURCES\n66: \n67: -> `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md` · `./prompt-templates.md` · `../SKILL.md` · `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/` (per-model profiles)\n\n(End of file - total 67 lines)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/CLAUDE.md\n# Claude Runtime Routing\n\n## Tool Routing Enforcement\n\nSEARCH ROUTING: use Code Graph structural search (`mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query`) plus Grep for concept, similarity, implementation-pattern, and \"how does this work\" code discovery. Use Code Graph for callers, imports, dependencies, outlines, symbols, and impact questions. Use exact text search when the user gives a literal token, path, or regex. Use `memory_search` only for spec docs and saved memory, not arbitrary code.\n\n## Logic-Sync Protocol\n\nWhen implementation evidence conflicts with the approved spec, stop and escalate for an AMENDMENT decision instead of shipping a silent workaround. Escalate once with the conflicting facts, a one-sentence root cause when known, and the decision needed.\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: OpenCode CLI — Prompt Quality Card\ndescription: Fast-path prompt discipline for OpenCode CLI dispatches; frameworks and CLEAR are canonical in sk-prompt.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"opencode prompt quality card\"\n  - \"opencode model overrides\"\n  - \"minimax tidd-ec dense pre-plan\"\n  - \"mimo costar lean prompt\"\n  - \"opencode dispatch framework precedence\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.3.0.21\n---\n\n# OpenCode CLI — Prompt Quality Card\n\nFast-path dispatch discipline for `opencode run` prompts. The 7-framework table, task-to-framework map, pre-planning-density / bundle-gate / anti-hallucination notes, and the CLEAR 5-question check are owned by the canonical card — do not inline them here.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/CLAUDE.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/prompt-quality-card.md","text":"---\ntitle: OpenCode CLI — Prompt Quality Card\ndescription: Fast-path prompt discipline for OpenCode CLI dispatches; frameworks and CLEAR are canonical in sk-prompt.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"opencode prompt quality card\"\n  - \"opencode model overrides\"\n  - \"minimax tidd-ec dense pre-plan\"\n  - \"mimo costar lean prompt\"\n  - \"opencode dispatch framework precedence\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.3.0.21\n---\n\n# OpenCode CLI — Prompt Quality Card\n\nFast-path dispatch discipline for `opencode run` prompts. The 7-framework table, task-to-framework map, pre-planning-density / bundle-gate / anti-hallucination notes, and the CLEAR 5-question check are owned by the canonical card — do not inline them here.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThis card is the OpenCode CLI fast-path prompt-quality reference; it delegates the framework table + CLEAR check to the canonical card and records only OpenCode-specific model overrides plus the precedence rule.\n\n### Usage\n\nCompose a dispatch prompt by starting from the shared layer (canonical card), applying the OpenCode model overrides, and following the precedence rule.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SHARED LAYER (DELEGATED — DO NOT INLINE)\n\nThe 7-framework selection table, the task->framework map, the pre-planning-density / bundle-gate / anti-hallucination notes, and the CLEAR 5-question check are OWNED by the canonical card. Do NOT copy them here.\n\n-> `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md`  (deep theory: `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-improve/references/patterns-evaluation.md`)\n\n---\n\n## 3. OPENCODE MODEL OVERRIDES\n\nOpenCode dispatches the MiniMax, MiMo, DeepSeek-v4-pro, and Kimi-K2.7 small models, which override or default against the cross-model defaults from the canonical card:\n\n| Model (dispatchable here) | Override | Profile |\n|---|---|---|\n| MiniMax M3 (Token Plan default) | TIDD-EC + dense | `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md` |\n| MiniMax M3 (Direct API) | TIDD-EC + dense | `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md` |\n| MiMo V2.5 Pro (Token Plan) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n| MiMo V2.5 Pro (Direct API) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n| MiMo V2.5 Pro UltraSpeed (Direct API, low-latency) | COSTAR + lean, `--variant high` | `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md` |\n| GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan) | COSTAR + lean (empirical, benchmark 008) | [`glm-5.2.md`](../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md) |\n| deepseek-v4-pro / kimi-k2.7-code | default RCAF (no model-specific benchmark; shared default-unverified note) | [`deepseek-v4-pro.md`](../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/deepseek-v4-pro.md) · [`kimi-k2.7-code.md`](../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/kimi-k2.7-code.md) |\n\n**Executor notes:** Omit `--agent` for all small-model dispatches listed above. OpenCode maps `--variant low/medium/high` to MiMo's reasoning effort; `high` is the standing default for MiMo. MiniMax Token Plan (`minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`) and Direct API (`minimax/MiniMax-M3`) both serve M3. Xiaomi Token Plan (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`) and Direct API (`xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`) both serve MiMo-V2.5-Pro; the Direct API additionally serves `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed`, a low-latency tier with the same prompt contract. Ambiguous use-case (1 vs 2 vs 3) prevents the router from picking a path — resolve before dispatch. Always include a self-invocation guard signal when the dispatched session could loop back.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DELEGATION / PRECEDENCE\n\nThe 3-tier precedence rule (fast path -> model override -> deep path) is canonical in `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md` and restated in `../SKILL.md`.\n\nOpenCode-specific escalation example: if the task would otherwise need a long `opencode run` prompt plus an explicit Memory Epilogue and a parallel-session decision, ask `@prompt-improver` for the final `ENHANCED_PROMPT` first, then pass that result to OpenCode.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n-> `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md` · `./prompt-templates.md` · `../SKILL.md` · `../../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/references/models/` (per-model profiles)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":67,"totalLines":67,"truncated":false}},"title":".claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/assets/prompt-quality-card.md","time":{"start":1784521056941,"end":1784521057011}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05885a86d8766c27016a5da160cec48191b7caf87e61180a02"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe62a3001AsxrVAEr5QLH9r","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe41d8001jJnEYh1TJPFDC2"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521057019,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Lg7GzXIBfovEL7OFIrueYQ8T","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/integration-patterns.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/integration-patterns.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"OpenCode CLI - Integration Patterns and Use Cases\"\n3: description: \"The three documented use cases for cli-opencode (external runtime to OpenCode, in-OpenCode parallel detached session, cross-AI orchestration handback) with copy-paste prompt templates, smart-router signals, and the self-invocation guard decision tree.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"opencode integration patterns\"\n6:   - \"opencode self-invocation guard\"\n7:   - \"opencode parallel detached session\"\n8:   - \"opencode cross-ai handback\"\n9:   - \"opencode stdin dev null rule\"\n10:   - \"opencode run hang non-interactive\"\n11: importance_tier: important\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.3.0.14\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # OpenCode CLI - Integration Patterns\n17: \n18: How cli-opencode positions itself relative to the three sibling cli-* skills, the three documented use cases (per ADR-002), the smart-router decision tree that picks between them, and the self-invocation guard that protects against circular dispatch (per ADR-001).\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: The three sibling cli-* skills exist because their target binaries are external runtimes — Claude Code, OpenCode, Copilot do not own this repo. OpenCode owns this repo. A naive \"delegate to opencode\" skill makes no sense for an in-OpenCode operator (it would create a circular dispatch).\n25: \n26: cli-opencode resolves this by documenting THREE orthogonal use cases. The smart router selects between them based on the calling AI's runtime context.\n27: \n28: | Use case | Calling runtime | Target | Self-invocation? |\n29: |----------|-----------------|--------|------------------|\n30: | 1. External runtime to OpenCode | Claude Code, OpenCode, Copilot, raw shell | OpenCode for full plugin / skill / MCP runtime | No |\n31: | 2. In-OpenCode parallel detached session | OpenCode itself (TUI / web / serve / acp) | New OpenCode session via `--share --port N` | No (different session id) |\n32: | 3. Cross-AI orchestration handback | OpenCode / Copilot | OpenCode for spec-kit specific workflows | No |\n33: \n34: The cycle ADR-001 protects against is the operator inside OpenCode asking cli-opencode to \"delegate this exact prompt to OpenCode\" — that case is REFUSED at the routing layer.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. USE CASE 1 — EXTERNAL RUNTIME TO OPENCODE\n39: \n40: ### When to use\n41: \n42: The calling AI is Claude Code, OpenCode, Copilot, or a raw shell. The task needs the project's full plugin / skill / MCP / Spec Kit Memory runtime — not just a raw model dispatch. Examples:\n43: \n44: - Run `memory_search` against the project's spec-doc database\n45: - Call Code Graph for semantic code search across the repo\n46: - Dispatch a `@deep-research` or `@deep-review` agent loop with externalized state\n47: - Run a sub-agent that needs Spec Kit Memory for continuity across iterations\n48: \n49: ### Smart-router signal\n50: \n51: ADR-001's detection signal does NOT trip (no OPENCODE_* env var, no opencode parent process, no live state lock).\n52: \n53: ### Prompt template\n54: \n55: ```text\n56: You are dispatching from <calling-runtime> into a fresh OpenCode session via cli-opencode.\n57: \n58: Goal: <one-sentence goal>\n59: \n60: Context:\n61: - Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)\n62: - Plugins / skills required: <list>\n63: - MCP tools required: <list>\n64: \n65: Constraints:\n66: - <list>\n67: \n68: Success criteria:\n69: - <list>\n70: \n71: Memory epilogue: include MEMORY_HANDBACK delimiters at the end of the response so the calling runtime can preserve context.\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### Invocation shape\n75: \n76: ```bash\n77: opencode run \\\n78:   --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n79:   --agent general \\\n80:   --variant high \\\n81:   --format json \\\n82:   --dir \"$REPO_ROOT\" \\\n83:   \"<prompt-from-template>\" 2>&1\n84: ```\n85: \n86: ### Why it matters\n87: \n88: This is the canonical cross-AI dispatch path. It gives external runtimes a one-shot bridge into the project's full runtime without forcing the operator to leave their host session.\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## 3. USE CASE 2 — IN-OPENCODE PARALLEL DETACHED SESSION\n93: \n94: ### When to use\n95: \n96: The operator is already inside an OpenCode session (TUI, web, serve, acp). They want a SEPARATE OpenCode session — not a continuation, not a fork — to run an ablation suite, a worker farm, or a parallel research sweep. The new session has its own session id, its own state directory, and an optional share URL.\n97: \n98: ### Smart-router signal\n99: \n100: ADR-001's detection signal trips (in-OpenCode runtime). The router checks the prompt for explicit parallel-session keywords:\n101: \n102: - \"parallel detached session\"\n103: - \"ablation suite\"\n104: - \"worker farm\"\n105: - \"parallel research\"\n106: - \"spawn detached\"\n107: - \"share URL\"\n108: \n109: If at least one of these phrases appears AND the prompt does NOT request \"delegate this exact prompt\", the router permits the dispatch with `--share --port <N>`.\n110: \n111: ### Prompt template\n112: \n113: ```text\n114: You are spawning a parallel detached OpenCode session for <purpose>.\n115: \n116: Goal: <one-sentence goal>\n117: \n118: Context:\n119: - Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)\n120: - Iteration N of <total>\n121: - State file: <path>\n122: \n123: Constraints:\n124: - This session must NOT modify the parent session's state.\n125: - Write results to <state file path>.\n126: - Publish a share URL only if the operator confirmed (CHK-033).\n127: \n128: Success criteria:\n129: - <list>\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Invocation shape\n133: \n134: ```bash\n135: opencode run \\\n136:   --share \\\n137:   --port 4096 \\\n138:   --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n139:   --agent deep-research \\\n140:   --variant high \\\n141:   --format json \\\n142:   --dir \"$REPO_ROOT\" \\\n143:   \"<prompt-from-template>\" 2>&1\n144: ```\n145: \n146: ### Why it matters\n147: \n148: Parallel research, ablation studies, and worker farms need N concurrent sessions. Each must be independent. The detached pattern makes this possible without leaking state between sessions.\n149: \n150: ### Operator confirmation for share URLs\n151: \n152: Per CHK-033, the calling AI MUST confirm with the operator before passing `--share`. The share URL exposes the session's contents to anyone with the URL, so it is opt-in.\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## 4. USE CASE 3 — CROSS-AI ORCHESTRATION HANDBACK\n157: \n158: ### When to use\n159: \n160: The calling AI is a non-Anthropic CLI (OpenCode, Copilot). The task requires OpenCode-specific plugins or skills (e.g. spec-kit workflows, the Spec Kit Memory MCP database, the structural code graph). The non-Anthropic CLI cannot load the project's plugins on its own — cli-opencode is the documented bridge.\n161: \n162: ### Smart-router signal\n163: \n164: ADR-001's detection signal does NOT trip (the calling AI is OpenCode / Copilot, not OpenCode). The prompt mentions a project-specific subsystem:\n165: \n166: - \"spec kit\" / \"spec-kit\" / \"spec_kit\"\n167: - \"spec kit memory\"\n168: - \"code graph\"\n169: - \"skill advisor\"\n170: - \"session bootstrap\"\n171: \n172: When the calling AI is non-Anthropic AND a project-specific subsystem is named, this use case is selected over use case 1 (which is the more general path).\n173: \n174: ### Prompt template\n175: \n176: ```text\n177: You are dispatching from <calling-runtime> into OpenCode for a spec-kit-specific workflow.\n178: \n179: Goal: <one-sentence goal>\n180: \n181: Context:\n182: - Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)\n183: - Subsystem: <spec-kit / memory / code-graph / advisor>\n184: - Operation: <save / search / query / scan / validate>\n185: \n186: Constraints:\n187: - The OpenCode session MUST load the system-spec-kit skill for this dispatch.\n188: - All MCP calls go through the project's local MCP servers.\n189: \n190: Success criteria:\n191: - <list>\n192: \n193: Memory epilogue: include MEMORY_HANDBACK delimiters at the end so the calling runtime can preserve context.\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ### Invocation shape\n197: \n198: ```bash\n199: opencode run \\\n200:   --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n201:   --agent general \\\n202:   --variant high \\\n203:   --format json \\\n204:   --dir \"$REPO_ROOT\" \\\n205:   \"<prompt-from-template>\" 2>&1\n206: ```\n207: \n208: The invocation shape is identical to use case 1 — the difference is the prompt content, which targets a project-specific subsystem.\n209: \n210: ### Why it matters\n211: \n212: OpenCode and Copilot cannot load this project's plugin / skill / MCP runtime on their own. cli-opencode is the documented bridge that lets a OpenCode-led orchestration call into the project's spec-kit workflows without leaving the OpenCode session.\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## 5. SMART-ROUTER DECISION TREE\n217: \n218: The skill's smart router picks between the three use cases (or refuses) using this decision tree:\n219: \n220: ```text\n221: INPUT: prompt + calling runtime\n222:                 |\n223:                 v\n224: [ADR-001 SELF-INVOCATION GUARD]\n225: - Layer 1: env var lookup (any OPENCODE_* env var present?)\n226: - Layer 2: process ancestry (opencode in parent process tree?)\n227: - Layer 3: best-effort lock-file probe (~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock present? -- heuristic, not guaranteed on every install)\n228:                 |\n229:         +-------+-------+\n230:         |               |\n231:        NO              YES\n232:         |               |\n233:         v               v\n234: [CALLING RUNTIME]   [PROMPT KEYWORDS]\n235:         |               |\n236:    +----+----+    +-----+-----+\n237:    |         |    |           |\n238: Anthropic  Other  parallel   self-dispatch\n239: (Claude    (OpenCode words    only\n240: Code)      Copilot)        |           |\n241:    |         |             v           v\n242:    v         v        USE CASE 2   REFUSE\n243: USE CASE  [PROJECT     (in-       (cycle —\n244: 1         SUBSYSTEM    OpenCode   surface\n245: (external NAMED?]      parallel)  ADR-001\n246: to                      |          error)\n247: OpenCode)        +------+------+\n248:                  |             |\n249:                 YES            NO\n250:                  |             |\n251:                  v             v\n252:              USE CASE 3     USE CASE 1\n253:              (cross-AI      (external\n254:              handback)      to OpenCode)\n255: ```\n256: \n257: ### Refusal message\n258: \n259: When the router hits the REFUSE leaf, it surfaces this exact message:\n260: \n261: ```text\n262: ERROR: cli-opencode self-invocation refused.\n263: \n264: You are already inside OpenCode (signal: <env|ancestry|lockfile> tripped).\n265: Asking cli-opencode to delegate this exact prompt back to OpenCode would create\n266: a circular dispatch.\n267: \n268: Options:\n269: 1. Use a sibling cli-* skill (cli-claude-code, cli-opencode)\n270:    to dispatch a different model.\n271: 2. Open a fresh shell session (no OpenCode parent) and re-run from there.\n272: 3. If you wanted a parallel detached session (different session id, separate\n273:    state directory), restate the request with explicit \"parallel detached\" /\n274:    \"ablation suite\" / \"worker farm\" / \"share URL\" keywords — that triggers\n275:    use case 2 instead of refusal.\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ## 6. STDIN HANDLING — `</dev/null` IS REQUIRED FOR ALL NON-INTERACTIVE DISPATCH\n281: \n282: **`opencode run` reads stdin at startup before session creation (opencode v1.14.39).** Without an explicit closed stdin, ANY non-interactive automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs forever at 0% CPU — even with a clean tool registry, valid model, and `--pure` set. This is the third independent root cause discovered during the 027-xce-research-based-refinement deep-research run on 2026-05-08; see `../CHANGELOG-2026-05-08-tool-name-regex-fix.md` §Fix 4 and memory `feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md`.\n283: \n284: ### Hang symptom (diagnostic)\n285: \n286: If you see ALL of:\n287: - Process at 0% CPU after >60s\n288: - `~/.local/share/opencode/log/<timestamp>.log` last entry is `service=snapshot prune=7.days cleanup`\n289: - 0 bytes stdout, 0 bytes stderr\n290: - No TCP connections to provider\n291: - 12-min timeout fires, exit code 124\n292: \n293: …it's the stdin-startup-deadlock. Append `</dev/null`.\n294: \n295: ### Failure patterns (all hang)\n296: \n297: ```bash\n298: # WRONG #1 — file redirect without </dev/null\n299: opencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" > stdout.log 2> stderr.log\n300: \n301: # WRONG #2 — combined redirect via tee\n302: opencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" 2>&1 | tee combined.log\n303: \n304: # WRONG #3 — background opencode in while-read loop without </dev/null\n305: while IFS= read -r line; do\n306:   opencode run --format json \"<prompt>\" > \"$LOG\" 2>&1 &\n307: done < input.jsonl\n308: # Both bugs apply: stdin-startup-read AND silent loop-stdin consumption.\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ### Fix patterns (all work)\n312: \n313: ```bash\n314: # RIGHT #1 — file redirect with </dev/null\n315: opencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" </dev/null > stdout.log 2> stderr.log\n316: \n317: # RIGHT #2 — combined redirect with explicit closed stdin via < /dev/null\n318: opencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" </dev/null 2>&1 | tee combined.log\n319: \n320: # RIGHT #3 — background in while-read loop\n321: while IFS= read -r line; do\n322:   opencode run --format json \"<prompt>\" > \"$LOG\" 2>&1 </dev/null &\n323: done < input.jsonl\n324: \n325: # RIGHT #4 — foreground pipe to tail (works WITHOUT </dev/null because the empty pipe upstream provides EOF)\n326: opencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" 2>&1 | tail -15\n327: ```\n328: \n329: ### Why foreground `| tail` accidentally works\n330: \n331: When you run `opencode run \"...\" 2>&1 | tail`, the shell sets up a pipe BEFORE invoking opencode. opencode's stdin is NOT connected to your terminal — it's connected to the upstream pipe stage, which has no producer (the prompt is the positional argument, not piped via stdin). The shell closes that pipe immediately, opencode reads EOF, and startup proceeds. This is fragile — `2>&1 | tee combined.log` does NOT work because `tee` may keep the pipe open differently depending on shell + tee implementation. **Always use `</dev/null` explicitly** rather than relying on accidental pipe behavior.\n332: \n333: ### Position rule\n334: \n335: `</dev/null` belongs:\n336: - AFTER the prompt positional argument\n337: - BEFORE the `> stdout 2> stderr` redirects (or anywhere on the command line — shell parses redirects independent of position, but right-after-prompt is conventional and easiest to spot during code review)\n338: \n339: ```bash\n340: # canonical order\n341: opencode run --flags \"<prompt>\" </dev/null > stdout 2> stderr\n342: #                              ^^^^^^^^^^\n343: #                              stdin from /dev/null (immediate EOF)\n344: ```\n345: \n346: ### Background dispatch from automation scripts (the deep-research / deep-review pattern)\n347: \n348: ```bash\n349: timeout 720 opencode run \\\n350:   --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n351:   --variant high \\\n352:   --pure \\\n353:   --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n354:   \"$(cat prompt.md)\" \\\n355:   </dev/null \\\n356:   > \"$LOG_DIR/iter-N-stdout.log\" \\\n357:   2> \"$LOG_DIR/iter-N-stderr.log\"\n358: ```\n359: \n360: This is the pattern enforced by the 4 `if_cli_opencode` blocks in the deep-research and deep-review YAML workflow files. Any new automation that dispatches opencode MUST follow it.\n361: \n362: ### Upstream\n363: \n364: The bug is in opencode v1.14.39. The fix would be: in the `run` subcommand entrypoint, check `process.stdin.isTTY` (or equivalent) and skip the stdin read in non-interactive mode — the message is already provided as a positional argument, so stdin is informational only. Until upstream patches this, `</dev/null` at every callsite is the workaround. File a bug report with opencode-ai/opencode if not already filed.\n365: \n366: ---\n367: \n368: ## 7. MEMORY HANDBACK\n369: \n370: cli-opencode dispatches that produce evidence for a Spec Kit Memory save MUST include the Memory Epilogue at the end of the prompt. The dispatched session adds `MEMORY_HANDBACK_START` / `MEMORY_HANDBACK_END` delimiters around a structured JSON payload that the calling AI extracts and feeds to `generate-context.js`.\n371: \n372: The full Memory Handback Protocol is shared with cli-claude-code and cli-opencode. See SKILL.md Section 4 (RULES) for the canonical 7-step procedure. The same JSON normalization (camelCase / snake_case aliases) and post-010 save gates apply.\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ## 8. RELATED RESOURCES\n377: \n378: - `./cli-reference.md` - Full subcommand and flag reference\n379: - `./opencode-tools.md` - Unique value props vs sibling cli-* skills\n380: - `./agent-delegation.md` - Agent routing matrix\n381: - `../assets/prompt-templates.md` - Copy-paste templates per use case\n382: - `../SKILL.md` - Skill entry point and smart router pseudocode\n\n(End of file - total 382 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"OpenCode CLI - Integration Patterns and Use Cases\"\ndescription: \"The three documented use cases for cli-opencode (external runtime to OpenCode, in-OpenCode parallel detached session, cross-AI orchestration handback) with copy-paste prompt templates, smart-router signals, and the self-invocation guard decision tree.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"opencode integration patterns\"\n  - \"opencode self-invocation guard\"\n  - \"opencode parallel detached session\"\n  - \"opencode cross-ai handback\"\n  - \"opencode stdin dev null rule\"\n  - \"opencode run hang non-interactive\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.3.0.14\n---\n\n# OpenCode CLI - Integration Patterns\n\nHow cli-opencode positions itself relative to the three sibling cli-* skills, the three documented use cases (per ADR-002), the smart-router decision tree that picks between them, and the self-invocation guard that protects against circular dispatch (per ADR-001).\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/integration-patterns.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"OpenCode CLI - Integration Patterns and Use Cases\"\ndescription: \"The three documented use cases for cli-opencode (external runtime to OpenCode, in-OpenCode parallel detached session, cross-AI orchestration handback) with copy-paste prompt templates, smart-router signals, and the self-invocation guard decision tree.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"opencode integration patterns\"\n  - \"opencode self-invocation guard\"\n  - \"opencode parallel detached session\"\n  - \"opencode cross-ai handback\"\n  - \"opencode stdin dev null rule\"\n  - \"opencode run hang non-interactive\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.3.0.14\n---\n\n# OpenCode CLI - Integration Patterns\n\nHow cli-opencode positions itself relative to the three sibling cli-* skills, the three documented use cases (per ADR-002), the smart-router decision tree that picks between them, and the self-invocation guard that protects against circular dispatch (per ADR-001).\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe three sibling cli-* skills exist because their target binaries are external runtimes — Claude Code, OpenCode, Copilot do not own this repo. OpenCode owns this repo. A naive \"delegate to opencode\" skill makes no sense for an in-OpenCode operator (it would create a circular dispatch).\n\ncli-opencode resolves this by documenting THREE orthogonal use cases. The smart router selects between them based on the calling AI's runtime context.\n\n| Use case | Calling runtime | Target | Self-invocation? |\n|----------|-----------------|--------|------------------|\n| 1. External runtime to OpenCode | Claude Code, OpenCode, Copilot, raw shell | OpenCode for full plugin / skill / MCP runtime | No |\n| 2. In-OpenCode parallel detached session | OpenCode itself (TUI / web / serve / acp) | New OpenCode session via `--share --port N` | No (different session id) |\n| 3. Cross-AI orchestration handback | OpenCode / Copilot | OpenCode for spec-kit specific workflows | No |\n\nThe cycle ADR-001 protects against is the operator inside OpenCode asking cli-opencode to \"delegate this exact prompt to OpenCode\" — that case is REFUSED at the routing layer.\n\n---\n\n## 2. USE CASE 1 — EXTERNAL RUNTIME TO OPENCODE\n\n### When to use\n\nThe calling AI is Claude Code, OpenCode, Copilot, or a raw shell. The task needs the project's full plugin / skill / MCP / Spec Kit Memory runtime — not just a raw model dispatch. Examples:\n\n- Run `memory_search` against the project's spec-doc database\n- Call Code Graph for semantic code search across the repo\n- Dispatch a `@deep-research` or `@deep-review` agent loop with externalized state\n- Run a sub-agent that needs Spec Kit Memory for continuity across iterations\n\n### Smart-router signal\n\nADR-001's detection signal does NOT trip (no OPENCODE_* env var, no opencode parent process, no live state lock).\n\n### Prompt template\n\n```text\nYou are dispatching from <calling-runtime> into a fresh OpenCode session via cli-opencode.\n\nGoal: <one-sentence goal>\n\nContext:\n- Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)\n- Plugins / skills required: <list>\n- MCP tools required: <list>\n\nConstraints:\n- <list>\n\nSuccess criteria:\n- <list>\n\nMemory epilogue: include MEMORY_HANDBACK delimiters at the end of the response so the calling runtime can preserve context.\n```\n\n### Invocation shape\n\n```bash\nopencode run \\\n  --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n  --agent general \\\n  --variant high \\\n  --format json \\\n  --dir \"$REPO_ROOT\" \\\n  \"<prompt-from-template>\" 2>&1\n```\n\n### Why it matters\n\nThis is the canonical cross-AI dispatch path. It gives external runtimes a one-shot bridge into the project's full runtime without forcing the operator to leave their host session.\n\n---\n\n## 3. USE CASE 2 — IN-OPENCODE PARALLEL DETACHED SESSION\n\n### When to use\n\nThe operator is already inside an OpenCode session (TUI, web, serve, acp). They want a SEPARATE OpenCode session — not a continuation, not a fork — to run an ablation suite, a worker farm, or a parallel research sweep. The new session has its own session id, its own state directory, and an optional share URL.\n\n### Smart-router signal\n\nADR-001's detection signal trips (in-OpenCode runtime). The router checks the prompt for explicit parallel-session keywords:\n\n- \"parallel detached session\"\n- \"ablation suite\"\n- \"worker farm\"\n- \"parallel research\"\n- \"spawn detached\"\n- \"share URL\"\n\nIf at least one of these phrases appears AND the prompt does NOT request \"delegate this exact prompt\", the router permits the dispatch with `--share --port <N>`.\n\n### Prompt template\n\n```text\nYou are spawning a parallel detached OpenCode session for <purpose>.\n\nGoal: <one-sentence goal>\n\nContext:\n- Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)\n- Iteration N of <total>\n- State file: <path>\n\nConstraints:\n- This session must NOT modify the parent session's state.\n- Write results to <state file path>.\n- Publish a share URL only if the operator confirmed (CHK-033).\n\nSuccess criteria:\n- <list>\n```\n\n### Invocation shape\n\n```bash\nopencode run \\\n  --share \\\n  --port 4096 \\\n  --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n  --agent deep-research \\\n  --variant high \\\n  --format json \\\n  --dir \"$REPO_ROOT\" \\\n  \"<prompt-from-template>\" 2>&1\n```\n\n### Why it matters\n\nParallel research, ablation studies, and worker farms need N concurrent sessions. Each must be independent. The detached pattern makes this possible without leaking state between sessions.\n\n### Operator confirmation for share URLs\n\nPer CHK-033, the calling AI MUST confirm with the operator before passing `--share`. The share URL exposes the session's contents to anyone with the URL, so it is opt-in.\n\n---\n\n## 4. USE CASE 3 — CROSS-AI ORCHESTRATION HANDBACK\n\n### When to use\n\nThe calling AI is a non-Anthropic CLI (OpenCode, Copilot). The task requires OpenCode-specific plugins or skills (e.g. spec-kit workflows, the Spec Kit Memory MCP database, the structural code graph). The non-Anthropic CLI cannot load the project's plugins on its own — cli-opencode is the documented bridge.\n\n### Smart-router signal\n\nADR-001's detection signal does NOT trip (the calling AI is OpenCode / Copilot, not OpenCode). The prompt mentions a project-specific subsystem:\n\n- \"spec kit\" / \"spec-kit\" / \"spec_kit\"\n- \"spec kit memory\"\n- \"code graph\"\n- \"skill advisor\"\n- \"session bootstrap\"\n\nWhen the calling AI is non-Anthropic AND a project-specific subsystem is named, this use case is selected over use case 1 (which is the more general path).\n\n### Prompt template\n\n```text\nYou are dispatching from <calling-runtime> into OpenCode for a spec-kit-specific workflow.\n\nGoal: <one-sentence goal>\n\nContext:\n- Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)\n- Subsystem: <spec-kit / memory / code-graph / advisor>\n- Operation: <save / search / query / scan / validate>\n\nConstraints:\n- The OpenCode session MUST load the system-spec-kit skill for this dispatch.\n- All MCP calls go through the project's local MCP servers.\n\nSuccess criteria:\n- <list>\n\nMemory epilogue: include MEMORY_HANDBACK delimiters at the end so the calling runtime can preserve context.\n```\n\n### Invocation shape\n\n```bash\nopencode run \\\n  --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n  --agent general \\\n  --variant high \\\n  --format json \\\n  --dir \"$REPO_ROOT\" \\\n  \"<prompt-from-template>\" 2>&1\n```\n\nThe invocation shape is identical to use case 1 — the difference is the prompt content, which targets a project-specific subsystem.\n\n### Why it matters\n\nOpenCode and Copilot cannot load this project's plugin / skill / MCP runtime on their own. cli-opencode is the documented bridge that lets a OpenCode-led orchestration call into the project's spec-kit workflows without leaving the OpenCode session.\n\n---\n\n## 5. SMART-ROUTER DECISION TREE\n\nThe skill's smart router picks between the three use cases (or refuses) using this decision tree:\n\n```text\nINPUT: prompt + calling runtime\n                |\n                v\n[ADR-001 SELF-INVOCATION GUARD]\n- Layer 1: env var lookup (any OPENCODE_* env var present?)\n- Layer 2: process ancestry (opencode in parent process tree?)\n- Layer 3: best-effort lock-file probe (~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock present? -- heuristic, not guaranteed on every install)\n                |\n        +-------+-------+\n        |               |\n       NO              YES\n        |               |\n        v               v\n[CALLING RUNTIME]   [PROMPT KEYWORDS]\n        |               |\n   +----+----+    +-----+-----+\n   |         |    |           |\nAnthropic  Other  parallel   self-dispatch\n(Claude    (OpenCode words    only\nCode)      Copilot)        |           |\n   |         |             v           v\n   v         v        USE CASE 2   REFUSE\nUSE CASE  [PROJECT     (in-       (cycle —\n1         SUBSYSTEM    OpenCode   surface\n(external NAMED?]      parallel)  ADR-001\nto                      |          error)\nOpenCode)        +------+------+\n                 |             |\n                YES            NO\n                 |             |\n                 v             v\n             USE CASE 3     USE CASE 1\n             (cross-AI      (external\n             handback)      to OpenCode)\n```\n\n### Refusal message\n\nWhen the router hits the REFUSE leaf, it surfaces this exact message:\n\n```text\nERROR: cli-opencode self-invocation refused.\n\nYou are already inside OpenCode (signal: <env|ancestry|lockfile> tripped).\nAsking cli-opencode to delegate this exact prompt back to OpenCode would create\na circular dispatch.\n\nOptions:\n1. Use a sibling cli-* skill (cli-claude-code, cli-opencode)\n   to dispatch a different model.\n2. Open a fresh shell session (no OpenCode parent) and re-run from there.\n3. If you wanted a parallel detached session (different session id, separate\n   state directory), restate the request with explicit \"parallel detached\" /\n   \"ablation suite\" / \"worker farm\" / \"share URL\" keywords — that triggers\n   use case 2 instead of refusal.\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. STDIN HANDLING — `</dev/null` IS REQUIRED FOR ALL NON-INTERACTIVE DISPATCH\n\n**`opencode run` reads stdin at startup before session creation (opencode v1.14.39).** Without an explicit closed stdin, ANY non-interactive automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs forever at 0% CPU — even with a clean tool registry, valid model, and `--pure` set. This is the third independent root cause discovered during the 027-xce-research-based-refinement deep-research run on 2026-05-08; see `../CHANGELOG-2026-05-08-tool-name-regex-fix.md` §Fix 4 and memory `feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md`.\n\n### Hang symptom (diagnostic)\n\nIf you see ALL of:\n- Process at 0% CPU after >60s\n- `~/.local/share/opencode/log/<timestamp>.log` last entry is `service=snapshot prune=7.days cleanup`\n- 0 bytes stdout, 0 bytes stderr\n- No TCP connections to provider\n- 12-min timeout fires, exit code 124\n\n…it's the stdin-startup-deadlock. Append `</dev/null`.\n\n### Failure patterns (all hang)\n\n```bash\n# WRONG #1 — file redirect without </dev/null\nopencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" > stdout.log 2> stderr.log\n\n# WRONG #2 — combined redirect via tee\nopencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" 2>&1 | tee combined.log\n\n# WRONG #3 — background opencode in while-read loop without </dev/null\nwhile IFS= read -r line; do\n  opencode run --format json \"<prompt>\" > \"$LOG\" 2>&1 &\ndone < input.jsonl\n# Both bugs apply: stdin-startup-read AND silent loop-stdin consumption.\n```\n\n### Fix patterns (all work)\n\n```bash\n# RIGHT #1 — file redirect with </dev/null\nopencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" </dev/null > stdout.log 2> stderr.log\n\n# RIGHT #2 — combined redirect with explicit closed stdin via < /dev/null\nopencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" </dev/null 2>&1 | tee combined.log\n\n# RIGHT #3 — background in while-read loop\nwhile IFS= read -r line; do\n  opencode run --format json \"<prompt>\" > \"$LOG\" 2>&1 </dev/null &\ndone < input.jsonl\n\n# RIGHT #4 — foreground pipe to tail (works WITHOUT </dev/null because the empty pipe upstream provides EOF)\nopencode run --model X \"<prompt>\" 2>&1 | tail -15\n```\n\n### Why foreground `| tail` accidentally works\n\nWhen you run `opencode run \"...\" 2>&1 | tail`, the shell sets up a pipe BEFORE invoking opencode. opencode's stdin is NOT connected to your terminal — it's connected to the upstream pipe stage, which has no producer (the prompt is the positional argument, not piped via stdin). The shell closes that pipe immediately, opencode reads EOF, and startup proceeds. This is fragile — `2>&1 | tee combined.log` does NOT work because `tee` may keep the pipe open differently depending on shell + tee implementation. **Always use `</dev/null` explicitly** rather than relying on accidental pipe behavior.\n\n### Position rule\n\n`</dev/null` belongs:\n- AFTER the prompt positional argument\n- BEFORE the `> stdout 2> stderr` redirects (or anywhere on the command line — shell parses redirects independent of position, but right-after-prompt is conventional and easiest to spot during code review)\n\n```bash\n# canonical order\nopencode run --flags \"<prompt>\" </dev/null > stdout 2> stderr\n#                              ^^^^^^^^^^\n#                              stdin from /dev/null (immediate EOF)\n```\n\n### Background dispatch from automation scripts (the deep-research / deep-review pattern)\n\n```bash\ntimeout 720 opencode run \\\n  --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n  --variant high \\\n  --pure \\\n  --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n  \"$(cat prompt.md)\" \\\n  </dev/null \\\n  > \"$LOG_DIR/iter-N-stdout.log\" \\\n  2> \"$LOG_DIR/iter-N-stderr.log\"\n```\n\nThis is the pattern enforced by the 4 `if_cli_opencode` blocks in the deep-research and deep-review YAML workflow files. Any new automation that dispatches opencode MUST follow it.\n\n### Upstream\n\nThe bug is in opencode v1.14.39. The fix would be: in the `run` subcommand entrypoint, check `process.stdin.isTTY` (or equivalent) and skip the stdin read in non-interactive mode — the message is already provided as a positional argument, so stdin is informational only. Until upstream patches this, `</dev/null` at every callsite is the workaround. File a bug report with opencode-ai/opencode if not already filed.\n\n---\n\n## 7. MEMORY HANDBACK\n\ncli-opencode dispatches that produce evidence for a Spec Kit Memory save MUST include the Memory Epilogue at the end of the prompt. The dispatched session adds `MEMORY_HANDBACK_START` / `MEMORY_HANDBACK_END` delimiters around a structured JSON payload that the calling AI extracts and feeds to `generate-context.js`.\n\nThe full Memory Handback Protocol is shared with cli-claude-code and cli-opencode. See SKILL.md Section 4 (RULES) for the canonical 7-step procedure. The same JSON normalization (camelCase / snake_case aliases) and post-010 save gates apply.\n\n---\n\n## 8. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `./cli-reference.md` - Full subcommand and flag reference\n- `./opencode-tools.md` - Unique value props vs sibling cli-* skills\n- `./agent-delegation.md` - Agent routing matrix\n- `../assets/prompt-templates.md` - Copy-paste templates per use case\n- `../SKILL.md` - Skill entry point and smart router pseudocode","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":382,"totalLines":382,"truncated":false}},"title":".claude/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/integration-patterns.md","time":{"start":1784521056966,"end":1784521057015}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05885a86d8766c27016a5da160cecc8191985afd657c11f4a4"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe62ae0018GaL5ufUbtzR6Z","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe41d8001jJnEYh1TJPFDC2"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784521058202,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"id":"prt_f7dbe6796001abf94HVTUu85C1","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","messageID":"msg_f7dbe41d8001jJnEYh1TJPFDC2","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":72974,"input":10715,"output":268,"reasoning":39,"cache":{"write":0,"read":61952}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784521062305,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"id":"prt_f7dbe779e001CIWTVhMX57eLPy","messageID":"msg_f7dbe6bc40019JbVQGZTa0RlBL","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521071089,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FN4Vbb6bgvPGb6EPtBCIuod6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","offset":726,"limit":850},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n726:                     renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt,\n727:                   } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/divergent-research-pivot.ts';\n728:                   import {\n729:                     preparePivotTransaction,\n730:                   } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n731: \n732:                   const input = buildResearchPivotPreparationInput({\n733:                     artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n734:                     configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n735:                     stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n736:                     strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n737:                     registryPath: '{state_paths.registry}',\n738:                     currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n739:                     maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n740:                     triggerReason: '{reason}',\n741:                   });\n742:                   const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n743:                   const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n744:                     ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n745:                         seat.id,\n746:                         renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt(seat, prepared.dispatchContext),\n747:                       ]))\n748:                     : {};\n749:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify({\n750:                     ...prepared,\n751:                     seatPrompts,\n752:                     boundaryRejections: input.boundaryRejections,\n753:                   })}\\n`);\n754:                   EOF\n755:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n756:                 outputs:\n757:                   - pivot_prepare_json: \"The complete parsed JSON result\"\n758:                   - pivot_prepare_status: \"status from the prepare result\"\n759:                   - pivot_id: \"pivotId from the prepare result\"\n760:                   - pivot_paths_json: \"paths from the prepare result as JSON\"\n761:                   - pivot_resumed: \"resumed from the prepare result\"\n762:                   - pivot_missing_seat_ids: \"missingSeats ids from a pending result\"\n763:                   - pivot_seat_001_json: \"The seat-001 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n764:                   - pivot_seat_002_json: \"The seat-002 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n765:                   - pivot_seat_003_json: \"The seat-003 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n766:                   - pivot_seat_001_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-001']\"\n767:                   - pivot_seat_002_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-002']\"\n768:                   - pivot_seat_003_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-003']\"\n769:                   - pivot_dispatch_context_json: \"dispatchContext from a pending result as JSON\"\n770:                 short_circuit: \"When status is completed or failed, skip all dispatch and record steps and bind this result as pivot_result.\"\n771: \n772:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n773:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the analytical research direction-selection seat\"\n774:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n775:                 capture_timing: true\n776:                 if_native:\n777:                   dispatch:\n778:                     agent: deep-research\n779:                     model: opus\n780:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_001_prompt\"\n781:                   wait_for_completion: true\n782:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_001.\"\n783:                 outputs:\n784:                   - pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n785:                   - pivot_seat_001_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n786:                   - pivot_seat_001_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n787:                   - pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n788:                   - pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n789:                   - pivot_seat_001_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n790: \n791:               step_record_pivot_seat_001:\n792:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-001 native dispatch outcome\"\n793:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n794:                 command: |\n795:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n796:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n797:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status}';\n798:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n799:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_001_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') }\n800:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_001_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') };\n801:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_001_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n802:                   EOF\n803:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n804: \n805:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n806:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the critical research direction-selection seat\"\n807:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n808:                 capture_timing: true\n809:                 if_native:\n810:                   dispatch:\n811:                     agent: deep-research\n812:                     model: opus\n813:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_002_prompt\"\n814:                   wait_for_completion: true\n815:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_002.\"\n816:                 outputs:\n817:                   - pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n818:                   - pivot_seat_002_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n819:                   - pivot_seat_002_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n820:                   - pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n821:                   - pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n822:                   - pivot_seat_002_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n823: \n824:               step_record_pivot_seat_002:\n825:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-002 native dispatch outcome\"\n826:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n827:                 command: |\n828:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n829:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n830:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status}';\n831:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n832:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_002_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') }\n833:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_002_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') };\n834:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_002_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n835:                   EOF\n836:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n837: \n838:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n839:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the pragmatic research direction-selection seat\"\n840:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n841:                 capture_timing: true\n842:                 if_native:\n843:                   dispatch:\n844:                     agent: deep-research\n845:                     model: opus\n846:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_003_prompt\"\n847:                   wait_for_completion: true\n848:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_003.\"\n849:                 outputs:\n850:                   - pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n851:                   - pivot_seat_003_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n852:                   - pivot_seat_003_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n853:                   - pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n854:                   - pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n855:                   - pivot_seat_003_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n856: \n857:               step_record_pivot_seat_003:\n858:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-003 native dispatch outcome\"\n859:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n860:                 command: |\n861:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n862:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n863:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status}';\n864:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n865:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_003_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') }\n866:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_003_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') };\n867:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_003_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n868:                   EOF\n869:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n870: \n871:               step_finalize_divergent_pivot:\n872:                 action: \"Finalize the prepared pivot after all missing native seats are durable\"\n873:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending'\"\n874:                 command: |\n875:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n876:                   import { finalizePivotTransaction } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n877:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(finalizePivotTransaction({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', resumed: {pivot_resumed} }))}\\n`);\n878:                   EOF\n879:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n880:                 outputs:\n881:                   - pivot_finalize_json: \"The complete parsed final result\"\n882: \n883:               step_resolve_divergent_pivot_result:\n884:                 action: \"Use prepare's terminal result on resume/short-circuit, otherwise use finalize's result\"\n885:                 branch_on: \"pivot_prepare_status\"\n886:                 if_pending: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_finalize_json}\" } }\n887:                 if_completed_or_failed: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_prepare_json}\" } }\n888: \n889:               step_apply_divergent_pivot_result:\n890:                 action: \"Adopt a successful focus or fail closed to the existing synthesis path\"\n891:                 branch_on: \"pivot_result.status\"\n892:                 if_completed:\n893:                   set:\n894:                     next_focus: \"{pivot_result.restoredFocus}\"\n895:                     pivot_lineage: \"Pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} selected {pivot_result.selectedCandidate.id} from source iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n896:                     saturated_directions: \"{pivot_result.completedEvent.saturatedDirections}\"\n897:                   command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n898:                   log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} restored focus to {pivot_result.restoredFocus}; continuing iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n899:                   proceed_to: step_rejected_pattern_cache\n900:                 if_failed:\n901:                   log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} failed closed ({pivot_result.failureReason}); proceeding to synthesis.\"\n902:                   skip_to: phase_synthesis\n903:             on_error:\n904:               log: \"Divergent pivot integration error; failing closed to the existing synthesis path.\"\n905:               skip_to: phase_synthesis\n906:           if_existing_terminal_path:\n907:             log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n908:             skip_to: phase_synthesis\n909:         if_stuck_recovery:\n910:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n911:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n912:           set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n913:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n914:         if_continue:\n915:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n916: \n917:       step_rejected_pattern_cache:\n918:         action: \"Apply reducer-derived rejected-pattern suppression before dispatch candidate selection\"\n919:         read:\n920:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n921:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n922:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n923:         candidate_sources:\n924:           next_focus:\n925:             category: \"next-focus\"\n926:             values:\n927:               - \"{next_focus}\"\n928:               - \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n929:               - \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n930:           recovery:\n931:             category: \"recovery\"\n932:             values:\n933:               - \"{recovery_strategy}\"\n934:               - \"{least_explored}\"\n935:           ideas:\n936:             category: \"ideas\"\n937:             values:\n938:               - \"{promoted_ideas_list}\"\n939:             optional_file: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/research-ideas.md\"\n940:         algorithm: |\n941:           Use registry.rejectedPatternIndex and registry.promotedIdeas from the latest\n942:           reducer pass as the source of truth.\n943:           Compare normalized exact text first. Then compare fuzzy similarity with\n944:           rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold, but only when candidate and rejected categories\n945:           are compatible. Remove suppressed candidates from next_focus, recovery, and ideas\n946:           selection before rendering the dispatch prompt. If all candidates are suppressed,\n947:           halt for operator input instead of reusing a rejected idea.\n948:         outputs:\n949:           - accepted_next_focus: \"First unsuppressed next-focus candidate, or null\"\n950:           - accepted_recovery_candidate: \"First unsuppressed recovery candidate, or null\"\n951:           - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed ideas candidate, or null\"\n952:           - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Suppressed candidate diagnostics from registry.suppressedCandidates plus any current-step matches\"\n953:         if_next_focus_suppressed:\n954:           set: { next_focus: \"{accepted_next_focus || accepted_recovery_candidate || accepted_idea_candidate}\" }\n955:           log: \"Rejected-pattern cache suppressed the prior candidate; dispatching the next accepted candidate.\"\n956:         if_all_candidates_suppressed:\n957:           halt: true\n958:           message: \"All next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates match active rejected patterns. Remove/reset the rejected pattern or provide a new focus.\"\n959: \n960:       step_ideas_backlog_lifecycle:\n961:         action: \"Track reducer-owned observed/promoted/rejected idea lifecycle before dispatch\"\n962:         read:\n963:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n964:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n965:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n966:         lifecycle:\n967:           observed_event: \"idea_observed\"\n968:           promoted_event: \"idea_promoted\"\n969:           rejected_event: \"idea_rejected\"\n970:           min_observations: \"{min_idea_observations}\"\n971:           authority: \"Leaf agents emit observations only; reducer emits promotions and owns ranking.\"\n972:         validate:\n973:           - \"If new leaf-authored output includes idea_promoted, fail validation; only reducer output may append idea_promoted.\"\n974:           - \"If promoted_ideas_count > 0 and next_focus is empty or all questions are resolved, prefer the first unsuppressed promoted idea.\"\n975:           - \"If suppressed_ideas_count > 0, do not render those ideas into dispatch context.\"\n976:         outputs:\n977:           - observed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived observed ideas count\"\n978:           - promoted_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived promoted ideas count after minIdeaObservations\"\n979:           - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived rejected/suppressed ideas count\"\n980:           - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed promoted idea, or null\"\n981: \n982:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n983:         action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n984:         stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n985:         rule_pause_sentinel:\n986:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n987:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n988:         rule_stuck_recovery:\n989:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n990:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n991: \n992:       step_marker_scan:\n993:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n994:         algorithm: |\n995:           if current_iteration > 1:\n996:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n997:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n998:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n999:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n1000:                 log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n1001:                 halt with exit code 2\n1002:         note: |\n1003:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n1004:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n1005:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n1006:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n1007: \n1008:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n1009:         action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n1010:         resolve_executor:\n1011:           source: \"config.executor\"\n1012:           loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n1013:         pre_dispatch:\n1014:           generate_summary: |\n1015:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n1016:             Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n1017:             Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n1018:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n1019:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n1020:             {memory_context_prompt_line}\n1021:             Next focus: {next_focus}\n1022:           render_prompt_pack:\n1023:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/prompt-pack-iteration.md.tmpl\"\n1024:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n1025:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n1026:             variables:\n1027:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n1028:               research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n1029:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n1030:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n1031:               next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n1032:               remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n1033:               carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n1034:               last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n1035:               pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n1036:               saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n1037:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1038:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1039:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1040:               state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1041:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1042:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1043:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n1044:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n1045:           call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n1046:           args:\n1047:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1048:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n1049:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n1050:         branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n1051:         if_native:\n1052:           dispatch:\n1053:             agent: deep-research\n1054:             model: opus\n1055:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n1056:           wait_for_completion: true\n1057:         if_cli_claude_code:\n1058:           command: |\n1059:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1060:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1061:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1062: \n1063:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1064:             import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n1065: \n1066:             const executor = {\n1067:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n1068:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1069:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n1070:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n1071:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n1072:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1073:             };\n1074:             const args = [\n1075:               '-p',\n1076:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n1077:               '--model',\n1078:               executor.model,\n1079:               '--permission-mode',\n1080:               resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n1081:               '--output-format',\n1082:               'text',\n1083:             ];\n1084:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1085:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1086:             }\n1087: \n1088:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1089:               command: 'deep/research',\n1090:               mode: 'research',\n1091:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1092:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1093:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1094:               executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n1095:               branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n1096:               sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n1097:               generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n1098:             };\n1099:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n1100:             process.exit(\n1101:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1102:                 command: 'claude',\n1103:                 args,\n1104:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1105:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1106:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1107:                 executor,\n1108:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1109:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1110:                 dispatchId,\n1111:               }),\n1112:             );\n1113:             EOF\n1114:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1115:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1116:           wait_for_completion: true\n1117:           notes:\n1118:             - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n1119:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n1120:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n1121:         record_executor_audit:\n1122:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n1123:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1124:           field: \"executor\"\n1125:           value:\n1126:             kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n1127:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n1128:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n1129:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n1130:         if_cli_opencode:\n1131:           command: |\n1132:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1133:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1134:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1135: \n1136:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1137: \n1138:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1139:             const executor = {\n1140:               kind: 'cli-opencode',\n1141:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1142:               configDir: null,\n1143:               reasoningEffort,\n1144:               serviceTier: null,\n1145:               sandboxMode: null,\n1146:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1147:               governor: null,\n1148:             };\n1149:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n1150:             const message = 'Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n1151:               + '\\n\\n'\n1152:               + promptBody;\n1153:             const args = [\n1154:               'run',\n1155:               '--model',\n1156:               executor.model,\n1157:               '--format',\n1158:               'json',\n1159:               '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n1160:               '--pure',\n1161:               '--dir',\n1162:               '{repo_root}',\n1163:             ];\n1164:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1165:               args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1166:             }\n1167:             args.push(message);\n1168: \n1169:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1170:               command: 'deep/research',\n1171:               mode: 'research',\n1172:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1173:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1174:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1175:               executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n1176:               branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n1177:               sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n1178:               generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n1179:             };\n1180:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n1181:             process.exit(\n1182:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1183:                 command: 'opencode',\n1184:                 args,\n1185:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1186:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1187:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1188:                 executor,\n1189:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1190:                 // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n1191:                 // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n1192:                 input: '',\n1193:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1194:                 dispatchId,\n1195:               }),\n1196:             );\n1197:             EOF\n1198:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1199:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1200:           wait_for_completion: true\n1201:           notes:\n1202:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1203:             - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n1204:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n1205:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n1206:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n1207:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n1208:         if_cli_codex:\n1209:           command: |\n1210:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1211:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1212:             import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n1213: \n1214:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1215: \n1216:             // Fail closed: a requested codex executor must dispatch codex or abort,\n1217:             // never silently degrade to another executor. Undetected absence is what\n1218:             // got Codex deprecated before, so the branch exits non-zero when the\n1219:             // binary is missing instead of falling through to a native/other path.\n1220:             let codexAvailable = false;\n1221:             try {\n1222:               execFileSync('/bin/sh', ['-c', 'command -v codex >/dev/null 2>&1'], { stdio: 'ignore' });\n1223:               codexAvailable = true;\n1224:             } catch {}\n1225:             if (!codexAvailable) {\n1226:               console.error('cli-codex executor unavailable: command -v codex failed');\n1227:               process.exit(1);\n1228:             }\n1229: \n1230:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1231:             const serviceTier = '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}';\n1232:             const model = '{config.executor.model}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.model}';\n1233:             const executor = {\n1234:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n1235:               model,\n1236:               configDir: null,\n1237:               reasoningEffort,\n1238:               serviceTier,\n1239:               sandboxMode: 'workspace-write',\n1240:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1241:               governor: null,\n1242:             };\n1243: \n1244:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n1245: \n1246:             // codex reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-'. A research\n1247:             // iteration must WRITE its own iteration file, delta and state record, so the\n1248:             // sandbox is workspace-write — read-only would block those required writes.\n1249:             // approval_policy=never keeps the run non-interactive.\n1250:             const args = ['exec'];\n1251:             if (model) {\n1252:               args.push('--model', model);\n1253:             }\n1254:             args.push('-c', 'model_reasoning_effort=' + (reasoningEffort || 'medium'));\n1255:             if (serviceTier) {\n1256:               args.push('-c', 'service_tier=' + serviceTier);\n1257:             }\n1258:             args.push('-c', 'approval_policy=never', '--sandbox', executor.sandboxMode, '-');\n1259: \n1260:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n1261:             process.exit(\n1262:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1263:                 command: 'codex',\n1264:                 args,\n1265:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1266:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1267:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1268:                 executor,\n1269:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1270:                 input: promptBody,\n1271:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1272:                 dispatchId,\n1273:               }),\n1274:             );\n1275:             EOF\n1276:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1277:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1278:           wait_for_completion: true\n1279:           notes:\n1280:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so codex produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard (CODEX_SESSION_ID) + env allowlist (CODEX_/OPENAI_/AZURE_OPENAI_) enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1281:             - \"Fails closed when the codex binary is absent (exit 1) — parity with the fan-out cli-codex lineage guard in fanout-run.cjs; codex routing never degrades to native\"\n1282:             - \"codex exec reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-' (input: promptBody); '-c model_reasoning_effort=' maps reasoning depth, default medium; '-c service_tier=' forwarded when configured\"\n1283:             - \"--sandbox workspace-write is required so the iteration can write its own iteration file/delta/state record (read-only would fail the post-dispatch artifact gate); -c approval_policy=never keeps it non-interactive; --model omitted when unset so ~/.codex/config.toml default applies\"\n1284:         post_dispatch_validate:\n1285:           validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n1286:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type research --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n1287:           command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n1288:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1289:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1290:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus, mode]\n1291:           route_proof:\n1292:             mode: research\n1293:             target_agent: deep-research\n1294:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n1295:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"\n1296:           dispatchReceipt:\n1297:             receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n1298:             dispatchId: \"research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}\"\n1299:           optional_jsonl_fields:\n1300:             logOffset: \"Byte offset where the seekable log region starts\"\n1301:             logSize: \"Byte length of the seekable log region\"\n1302:             logPath: \"Absolute path to the file containing the seekable log region\"\n1303:             skippedCount: \"Missed fixed-rate slots counted for the completed dispatch; 0 when no slot was missed\"\n1304:             slotDurationMs: \"Monotonic elapsed duration for the completed dispatch slot\"\n1305:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n1306:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1307:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n1308:           on_failure:\n1309:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n1310:             redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n1311:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n1312:           failure_reasons_reference:\n1313:             - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n1314:             - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n1315:             - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n1316:             - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n1317:             - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n1318:             - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n1319:             - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n1320:             - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n1321:             - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n1322:             - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n1323:             - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n1324:             - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n1325:             - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n1326: \n1327:       step_run_now_restore_check:\n1328:         action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n1329:         command: |\n1330:           node <<'EOF'\n1331:           const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n1332: \n1333:           const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n1334:           const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n1335:           const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n1336:           const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n1337:           const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n1338:           const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n1339: \n1340:           function hasAcceptedCurrentRun() {\n1341:             if (!existsSync(stateLogPath)) return false;\n1342:             const lines = readFileSync(stateLogPath, \"utf8\").trim().split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(Boolean);\n1343:             for (let index = lines.length - 1; index >= 0; index -= 1) {\n1344:               const record = JSON.parse(lines[index]);\n1345:               if (record.run !== run || record.sessionId !== sessionId) continue;\n1346:               if (record.event === \"run_now_accepted\") return true;\n1347:               if (record.event === \"run_now_rejected\") return false;\n1348:             }\n1349:             return false;\n1350:           }\n1351: \n1352:           if (existsSync(sentinelPath) && hasAcceptedCurrentRun()) {\n1353:             appendFileSync(\n1354:               stateLogPath,\n1355:               `${JSON.stringify({\n1356:                 type: \"event\",\n1357:                 event: \"run_now_restored\",\n1358:                 mode: \"research\",\n1359:                 run,\n1360:                 sentinelPath,\n1361:                 timestamp,\n1362:                 sessionId,\n1363:                 generation,\n1364:               })}\\n`,\n1365:               \"utf8\",\n1366:             );\n1367:           }\n1368:           EOF\n1369:         outputs:\n1370:           - run_now_restored: \"Emitted when an operator recreates the sentinel before the accepted dispatch completes\"\n1371: \n1372:       step_reduce_state:\n1373:         action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n1374:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n1375:         inputs:\n1376:           latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n1377:           newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1378:           priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1379:         outputs:\n1380:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1381:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1382:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1383:           - \"{state_paths.state_log} question_conflict events when inbox text disagrees with registry-owned question text\"\n1384:           - \"{state_paths.state_log} idempotent idea_promoted events when observed ideas reach minIdeaObservations\"\n1385:           - \"{state_paths.registry} observedIdeas, promotedIdeas, suppressedIdeas, rejectedPatterns, and suppressedCandidates from idea lifecycle events\"\n1386:         failure_modes:\n1387:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1388:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1389:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1390:           question_conflict: \"keep registry value + append question_conflict event with inboxValue, registryValue, and operatorDecision\"\n1391:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1392: \n1393:       step_graph_upsert:\n1394:         action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n1395:         read:\n1396:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1397:         extract:\n1398:           - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n1399:           - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n1400:           - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n1401:           - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n1402:         if_graph_events_present:\n1403:           bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n1404:           note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n1405:         if_graph_events_missing:\n1406:           proceed: true\n1407: \n1408:       step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n1409:         action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n1410:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1411:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n1412:         timeout_seconds: 5\n1413:         idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n1414:         failure_policy:\n1415:           mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n1416:           timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n1417:         outputs:\n1418:           - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1419:           - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"\n1420: \n1421:       step_refresh_memory_context:\n1422:         action: \"Refresh focused Spec Kit Memory context before the next prompt render\"\n1423:         mcp_tool: memory_context\n1424:         invocation: 'memory_context({ input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true })'\n1425:         timeout_seconds: 5\n1426:         use_response:\n1427:           - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n1428:         failure_policy:\n1429:           mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n1430:           timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n1431:         outputs:\n1432:           - memory_context_prompt_line: \"Fresh focused context summary for the next iteration prompt\"\n1433:           - memory_context_refresh_status: \"refreshed | advisory_error\"\n1434: \n1435:       step_evaluate_results:\n1436:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n1437:         verify:\n1438:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1439:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n1440:           - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n1441:           - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed findings-registry.json\"\n1442:         extract:\n1443:           - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1444:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1445:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1446:           - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1447:         on_missing_outputs:\n1448:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n1449:           # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n1450:           # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state-format.md §Iteration Records.\n1451:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n1452: \n1453:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_progress:\n1454:         action: \"Emit a single-loop progress row when iteration state changes\"\n1455:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n1456:         command: |\n1457:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1458:           import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1459: \n1460:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n1461:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n1462: \n1463:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n1464:           const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n1465:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n1466:           const sessionId = '{config.lineage.sessionId}';\n1467:           const generation = Number('{config.lineage.generation}');\n1468:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n1469: \n1470:           function readRecords(path) {\n1471:             if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n1472:             return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n1473:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1474:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1475:               .filter(Boolean)\n1476:               .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n1477:           }\n1478: \n1479:           function elapsedSince(value) {\n1480:             const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n1481:             const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n1482:             if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n1483:             return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n1484:           }\n1485: \n1486:           const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n1487:           const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n1488:           const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n1489:           const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n1490:             ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n1491:             ?? timestamp;\n1492:           const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n1493:           const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n1494:           const run = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.run)) ? Number(latest.run) : Number('{current_iteration}');\n1495:           const status = typeof latest.status === 'string' ? latest.status : 'unknown';\n1496:           const row = {\n1497:             event: 'progress',\n1498:             label: 'single',\n1499:             at: timestamp,\n1500:             duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n1501:             loop_type: 'research',\n1502:             sessionId,\n1503:             generation,\n1504:             run,\n1505:             status,\n1506:             gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n1507:           };\n1508: \n1509:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n1510:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run, status, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n1511:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n1512:           });\n1513:           if (appended) {\n1514:             try {\n1515:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n1516:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n1517:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n1518:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run },\n1519:                 event: row.event,\n1520:                 status,\n1521:               });\n1522:             } catch {}\n1523:           }\n1524:           EOF\n1525:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1526:         outputs:\n1527:           - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n1528: \n1529:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1530:         action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n1531:         read:\n1532:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1533:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1534:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1535:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-dashboard.md\n1536:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1537:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n1538: \n1539:       step_update_tracking:\n1540:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n1541:         set:\n1542:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n1543:           stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n1544:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n1545: \n1546:       step_loop_decision:\n1547:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1548:         goto: step_read_state\n1549: \n1550:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1551:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1552:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1553:   phase_synthesis:\n1554:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n1555:     steps:\n1556: \n1557:       step_fanout_merge:\n1558:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n1559:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1560:         command: |\n1561:           node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1562:             --loop-type research \\\n1563:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1564:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1565:         wait_for_completion: true\n1566: \n1567:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1568:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1569:         read:\n1570:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1571:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1572:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1573:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1574:         extract:\n1575:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n\n(Showing lines 726-1575 of 2012. Use offset=1576 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"                    renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/divergent-research-pivot.ts';\n                  import {\n                    preparePivotTransaction,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n\n                  const input = buildResearchPivotPreparationInput({\n                    artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n                    configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n                    stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                    strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n                    registryPath: '{state_paths.registry}',\n                    currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                    maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n                    triggerReason: '{reason}',\n                  });\n                  const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n                  const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n                    ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n                        seat.id,","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","text":"                    renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/divergent-research-pivot.ts';\n                  import {\n                    preparePivotTransaction,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n\n                  const input = buildResearchPivotPreparationInput({\n                    artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n                    configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n                    stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                    strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n                    registryPath: '{state_paths.registry}',\n                    currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                    maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n                    triggerReason: '{reason}',\n                  });\n                  const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n                  const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n                    ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n                        seat.id,\n                        renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt(seat, prepared.dispatchContext),\n                      ]))\n                    : {};\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify({\n                    ...prepared,\n                    seatPrompts,\n                    boundaryRejections: input.boundaryRejections,\n                  })}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_prepare_json: \"The complete parsed JSON result\"\n                  - pivot_prepare_status: \"status from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_id: \"pivotId from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_paths_json: \"paths from the prepare result as JSON\"\n                  - pivot_resumed: \"resumed from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_missing_seat_ids: \"missingSeats ids from a pending result\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_json: \"The seat-001 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_json: \"The seat-002 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_json: \"The seat-003 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-001']\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-002']\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-003']\"\n                  - pivot_dispatch_context_json: \"dispatchContext from a pending result as JSON\"\n                short_circuit: \"When status is completed or failed, skip all dispatch and record steps and bind this result as pivot_result.\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the analytical research direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-research\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_001_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_001.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_001:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-001 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_001_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_001_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_001_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the critical research direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-research\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_002_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_002.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_002:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-002 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_002_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_002_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_002_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the pragmatic research direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-research\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_003_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_003.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_003:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-003 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_003_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_003_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_003_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_finalize_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Finalize the prepared pivot after all missing native seats are durable\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { finalizePivotTransaction } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(finalizePivotTransaction({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', resumed: {pivot_resumed} }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_finalize_json: \"The complete parsed final result\"\n\n              step_resolve_divergent_pivot_result:\n                action: \"Use prepare's terminal result on resume/short-circuit, otherwise use finalize's result\"\n                branch_on: \"pivot_prepare_status\"\n                if_pending: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_finalize_json}\" } }\n                if_completed_or_failed: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_prepare_json}\" } }\n\n              step_apply_divergent_pivot_result:\n                action: \"Adopt a successful focus or fail closed to the existing synthesis path\"\n                branch_on: \"pivot_result.status\"\n                if_completed:\n                  set:\n                    next_focus: \"{pivot_result.restoredFocus}\"\n                    pivot_lineage: \"Pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} selected {pivot_result.selectedCandidate.id} from source iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n                    saturated_directions: \"{pivot_result.completedEvent.saturatedDirections}\"\n                  command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n                  log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} restored focus to {pivot_result.restoredFocus}; continuing iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n                  proceed_to: step_rejected_pattern_cache\n                if_failed:\n                  log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} failed closed ({pivot_result.failureReason}); proceeding to synthesis.\"\n                  skip_to: phase_synthesis\n            on_error:\n              log: \"Divergent pivot integration error; failing closed to the existing synthesis path.\"\n              skip_to: phase_synthesis\n          if_existing_terminal_path:\n            log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n            skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n\n      step_rejected_pattern_cache:\n        action: \"Apply reducer-derived rejected-pattern suppression before dispatch candidate selection\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        candidate_sources:\n          next_focus:\n            category: \"next-focus\"\n            values:\n              - \"{next_focus}\"\n              - \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              - \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n          recovery:\n            category: \"recovery\"\n            values:\n              - \"{recovery_strategy}\"\n              - \"{least_explored}\"\n          ideas:\n            category: \"ideas\"\n            values:\n              - \"{promoted_ideas_list}\"\n            optional_file: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/research-ideas.md\"\n        algorithm: |\n          Use registry.rejectedPatternIndex and registry.promotedIdeas from the latest\n          reducer pass as the source of truth.\n          Compare normalized exact text first. Then compare fuzzy similarity with\n          rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold, but only when candidate and rejected categories\n          are compatible. Remove suppressed candidates from next_focus, recovery, and ideas\n          selection before rendering the dispatch prompt. If all candidates are suppressed,\n          halt for operator input instead of reusing a rejected idea.\n        outputs:\n          - accepted_next_focus: \"First unsuppressed next-focus candidate, or null\"\n          - accepted_recovery_candidate: \"First unsuppressed recovery candidate, or null\"\n          - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed ideas candidate, or null\"\n          - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Suppressed candidate diagnostics from registry.suppressedCandidates plus any current-step matches\"\n        if_next_focus_suppressed:\n          set: { next_focus: \"{accepted_next_focus || accepted_recovery_candidate || accepted_idea_candidate}\" }\n          log: \"Rejected-pattern cache suppressed the prior candidate; dispatching the next accepted candidate.\"\n        if_all_candidates_suppressed:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"All next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates match active rejected patterns. Remove/reset the rejected pattern or provide a new focus.\"\n\n      step_ideas_backlog_lifecycle:\n        action: \"Track reducer-owned observed/promoted/rejected idea lifecycle before dispatch\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        lifecycle:\n          observed_event: \"idea_observed\"\n          promoted_event: \"idea_promoted\"\n          rejected_event: \"idea_rejected\"\n          min_observations: \"{min_idea_observations}\"\n          authority: \"Leaf agents emit observations only; reducer emits promotions and owns ranking.\"\n        validate:\n          - \"If new leaf-authored output includes idea_promoted, fail validation; only reducer output may append idea_promoted.\"\n          - \"If promoted_ideas_count > 0 and next_focus is empty or all questions are resolved, prefer the first unsuppressed promoted idea.\"\n          - \"If suppressed_ideas_count > 0, do not render those ideas into dispatch context.\"\n        outputs:\n          - observed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived observed ideas count\"\n          - promoted_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived promoted ideas count after minIdeaObservations\"\n          - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived rejected/suppressed ideas count\"\n          - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed promoted idea, or null\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n        stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n        rule_pause_sentinel:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n        rule_stuck_recovery:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            {memory_context_prompt_line}\n            Next focus: {next_focus}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/prompt-pack-iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n              remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n              last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n              pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n              saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-research\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/research',\n              mode: 'research',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n              sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n              generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-opencode',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier: null,\n              sandboxMode: null,\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n            const message = 'Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n              + '\\n\\n'\n              + promptBody;\n            const args = [\n              'run',\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--format',\n              'json',\n              '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n              '--pure',\n              '--dir',\n              '{repo_root}',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n            args.push(message);\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/research',\n              mode: 'research',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n              sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n              generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'opencode',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n                // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n                input: '',\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            // Fail closed: a requested codex executor must dispatch codex or abort,\n            // never silently degrade to another executor. Undetected absence is what\n            // got Codex deprecated before, so the branch exits non-zero when the\n            // binary is missing instead of falling through to a native/other path.\n            let codexAvailable = false;\n            try {\n              execFileSync('/bin/sh', ['-c', 'command -v codex >/dev/null 2>&1'], { stdio: 'ignore' });\n              codexAvailable = true;\n            } catch {}\n            if (!codexAvailable) {\n              console.error('cli-codex executor unavailable: command -v codex failed');\n              process.exit(1);\n            }\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const serviceTier = '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}';\n            const model = '{config.executor.model}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.model}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model,\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier,\n              sandboxMode: 'workspace-write',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n\n            // codex reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-'. A research\n            // iteration must WRITE its own iteration file, delta and state record, so the\n            // sandbox is workspace-write — read-only would block those required writes.\n            // approval_policy=never keeps the run non-interactive.\n            const args = ['exec'];\n            if (model) {\n              args.push('--model', model);\n            }\n            args.push('-c', 'model_reasoning_effort=' + (reasoningEffort || 'medium'));\n            if (serviceTier) {\n              args.push('-c', 'service_tier=' + serviceTier);\n            }\n            args.push('-c', 'approval_policy=never', '--sandbox', executor.sandboxMode, '-');\n\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'codex',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                input: promptBody,\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so codex produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard (CODEX_SESSION_ID) + env allowlist (CODEX_/OPENAI_/AZURE_OPENAI_) enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"Fails closed when the codex binary is absent (exit 1) — parity with the fan-out cli-codex lineage guard in fanout-run.cjs; codex routing never degrades to native\"\n            - \"codex exec reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-' (input: promptBody); '-c model_reasoning_effort=' maps reasoning depth, default medium; '-c service_tier=' forwarded when configured\"\n            - \"--sandbox workspace-write is required so the iteration can write its own iteration file/delta/state record (read-only would fail the post-dispatch artifact gate); -c approval_policy=never keeps it non-interactive; --model omitted when unset so ~/.codex/config.toml default applies\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type research --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n          command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus, mode]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: research\n            target_agent: deep-research\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"\n          dispatchReceipt:\n            receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n            dispatchId: \"research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}\"\n          optional_jsonl_fields:\n            logOffset: \"Byte offset where the seekable log region starts\"\n            logSize: \"Byte length of the seekable log region\"\n            logPath: \"Absolute path to the file containing the seekable log region\"\n            skippedCount: \"Missed fixed-rate slots counted for the completed dispatch; 0 when no slot was missed\"\n            slotDurationMs: \"Monotonic elapsed duration for the completed dispatch slot\"\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n          failure_reasons_reference:\n            - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n            - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n            - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n            - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n            - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n            - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n            - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n            - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n            - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n            - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n            - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n\n      step_run_now_restore_check:\n        action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n          const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n\n          function hasAcceptedCurrentRun() {\n            if (!existsSync(stateLogPath)) return false;\n            const lines = readFileSync(stateLogPath, \"utf8\").trim().split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(Boolean);\n            for (let index = lines.length - 1; index >= 0; index -= 1) {\n              const record = JSON.parse(lines[index]);\n              if (record.run !== run || record.sessionId !== sessionId) continue;\n              if (record.event === \"run_now_accepted\") return true;\n              if (record.event === \"run_now_rejected\") return false;\n            }\n            return false;\n          }\n\n          if (existsSync(sentinelPath) && hasAcceptedCurrentRun()) {\n            appendFileSync(\n              stateLogPath,\n              `${JSON.stringify({\n                type: \"event\",\n                event: \"run_now_restored\",\n                mode: \"research\",\n                run,\n                sentinelPath,\n                timestamp,\n                sessionId,\n                generation,\n              })}\\n`,\n              \"utf8\",\n            );\n          }\n          EOF\n        outputs:\n          - run_now_restored: \"Emitted when an operator recreates the sentinel before the accepted dispatch completes\"\n\n      step_reduce_state:\n        action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        inputs:\n          latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n          newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n        outputs:\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log} question_conflict events when inbox text disagrees with registry-owned question text\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log} idempotent idea_promoted events when observed ideas reach minIdeaObservations\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry} observedIdeas, promotedIdeas, suppressedIdeas, rejectedPatterns, and suppressedCandidates from idea lifecycle events\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n          question_conflict: \"keep registry value + append question_conflict event with inboxValue, registryValue, and operatorDecision\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n        extract:\n          - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n          - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n        if_graph_events_present:\n          bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n          note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n        if_graph_events_missing:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n        action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"\n\n      step_refresh_memory_context:\n        action: \"Refresh focused Spec Kit Memory context before the next prompt render\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_context\n        invocation: 'memory_context({ input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        use_response:\n          - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_context_prompt_line: \"Fresh focused context summary for the next iteration prompt\"\n          - memory_context_refresh_status: \"refreshed | advisory_error\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n          - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed findings-registry.json\"\n        extract:\n          - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n          # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state-format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_progress:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop progress row when iteration state changes\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = '{config.lineage.sessionId}';\n          const generation = Number('{config.lineage.generation}');\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n\n          function readRecords(path) {\n            if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n          }\n\n          function elapsedSince(value) {\n            const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n            const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n            if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n            return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n          }\n\n          const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n          const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n          const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n          const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n            ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n            ?? timestamp;\n          const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n          const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n          const run = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.run)) ? Number(latest.run) : Number('{current_iteration}');\n          const status = typeof latest.status === 'string' ? latest.status : 'unknown';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'progress',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            run,\n            status,\n            gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run, status, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run },\n                event: row.event,\n                status,\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-dashboard.md\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"","lineStart":726,"lineEnd":1575,"totalLines":2012,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","time":{"start":1784521071067,"end":1784521071082}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0415b299bd3f5093016a5da16efe588191b6bba5bd5e4e8131"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe99b7001EGJOusrrnIZFj0","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe6bc40019JbVQGZTa0RlBL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521071090,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fbnkJdI19JFCcg4nHAeDox6f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-outputs.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research output files\"\n6:   - \"research iteration files\"\n7:   - \"research synthesis document\"\n8:   - \"research resource map\"\n9:   - \"research strategy file\"\n10:   - \"spec anchoring output\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\n17: \n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state-jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state-reducer-registry.md`.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n39: \n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n41: \n42: Required sections:\n43: \n44: - Research Topic\n45: - Known Context\n46: - Key Questions\n47: - Answered Questions\n48: - What Worked\n49: - What Failed\n50: - Exhausted Approaches\n51: - Ruled-Out Directions\n52: - Next Focus\n53: \n54: Update protocol:\n55: \n56: - read strategy before each iteration;\n57: - choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n58: - append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n59: - update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n60: - when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## 3. ITERATION FILES\n65: \n66: Iteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n67: \n68: ```text\n69: research/iterations/iteration-001.md\n70: research/iterations/iteration-002.md\n71: research/iterations/iteration-003.md\n72: ```\n73: \n74: Required shape:\n75: \n76: | Markdown Element | Required Content |\n77: |------------------|------------------|\n78: | H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n79: | `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n80: | `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n81: | `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n82: | `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n83: | `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n84: | `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n85: \n86: Every finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n91: \n92: `research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n93: \n94: Rules:\n95: \n96: - progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n97: - final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n98: - prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n99: - generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n100: - when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. DASHBOARD\n105: \n106: `deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n107: \n108: Expected sections:\n109: \n110: | Section | Source |\n111: |---------|--------|\n112: | Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n113: | Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n114: | Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n115: | Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n116: | Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n117: | Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n118: | Next Focus | Strategy |\n119: \n120: Generation rules:\n121: \n122: - regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n123: - compute derived values from raw state;\n124: - overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n125: - if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n126: - agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n131: \n132: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n133: \n134: - persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n135: - summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n136: - treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n137: - cite the map in final synthesis references;\n138: - emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n139: \n140: When absent:\n141: \n142: - persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n143: - write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n144: - continue normally.\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n149: \n150: `references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n151: \n152: - acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n153: - classify `folder_state`;\n154: - seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n155: - replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n156: \n157: This output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.\n\n(End of file - total 157 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state-jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state-reducer-registry.md`.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state-jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state-reducer-registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nHuman-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n\n`deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n\nRequired sections:\n\n- Research Topic\n- Known Context\n- Key Questions\n- Answered Questions\n- What Worked\n- What Failed\n- Exhausted Approaches\n- Ruled-Out Directions\n- Next Focus\n\nUpdate protocol:\n\n- read strategy before each iteration;\n- choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n- append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n- update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n- when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION FILES\n\nIteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n\n```text\nresearch/iterations/iteration-001.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-002.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-003.md\n```\n\nRequired shape:\n\n| Markdown Element | Required Content |\n|------------------|------------------|\n| H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n| `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n| `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n| `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n| `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n| `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n| `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n\nEvery finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n\n`research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n\nRules:\n\n- progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n- final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n- prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n- generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n- when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n\n---\n\n## 5. DASHBOARD\n\n`deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n\nExpected sections:\n\n| Section | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n| Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n| Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n| Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n| Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n| Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n| Next Focus | Strategy |\n\nGeneration rules:\n\n- regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n- compute derived values from raw state;\n- overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n- if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n- agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n- summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n- treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n- cite the map in final synthesis references;\n- emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n\nWhen absent:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n- write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n- continue normally.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n\n`references/protocol/spec-check-protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n\n- acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n- classify `folder_state`;\n- seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n- replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n\nThis output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":157,"totalLines":157,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-outputs.md","time":{"start":1784521071070,"end":1784521071085}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0415b299bd3f5093016a5da16efe6881918f9a84faa03b8f68"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe99dc001NyAr7D71VEtMzP","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe6bc40019JbVQGZTa0RlBL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521071090,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_rnkQy78PFVU3NCImB4O7hfFI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Convergence Detection Reference\n3: description: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"research stop contract\"\n7:   - \"research stopreason values\"\n8:   - \"research legal stop gates\"\n9:   - \"research convergence decision order\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.21\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Convergence Detection Reference\n16: \n17: Live stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Keep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n30: \n31: ### Key Sources\n32: \n33: - Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n34: - Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n35: - Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence-signals.md`\n36: - Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence-recovery.md`\n37: - Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence-graph.md`\n38: \n39: For iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n40: \n41: ### Live Decision Model\n42: \n43: Convergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n44: \n45: The live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n46: \n47: | Stage | Outcome |\n48: |-------|---------|\n49: | Hard stop and completion candidate | Stop unconditionally on max iterations; nominate STOP when all key questions are answered |\n50: | Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n51: | Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n52: | Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n53: | Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n54: \n55: ### Convergence Modes\n56: \n57: The shared convergence runtime accepts four values. The workflow keeps hard terminal boundaries outside mode-specific convergence handling.\n58: \n59: | Mode | Live Behavior |\n60: |------|---------------|\n61: | `default` | Uses the normal full-history convergence signals and sends a legal STOP to synthesis. This is the fallback when no mode is supplied. |\n62: | `off` | Skips convergence-driven STOP candidates. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, recovery halt, and unrecoverable error behavior remain active. |\n63: | `sliding-window` | Uses a bounded graph-novelty window, defaulting to 5 snapshots, while preserving the ordinary legal-stop and synthesis path. |\n64: | `divergent` | Computes convergence normally, but translates an eligible legal STOP into a three-seat direction-selection pivot and continues from the selected focus. |\n65: \n66: #### Divergent Pivot Contract\n67: \n68: Research pivots are eligible only when the workflow decision is `STOP` and the exact internal reason is `composite_converged` or `all_questions_answered`. The legal-stop and quality gates run before this branch. `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `stuckRecovery`, `minIterationsNotReached`, `error`, `manualStop`, and `userPaused` are explicitly excluded. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, and unrecoverable error therefore never dispatch a pivot Council.\n69: \n70: Each eligible pivot runs one native, in-process Council round with exactly three distinct seats: analytical, critical, and pragmatic. It does not use an external CLI. The transaction requires all three seat returns to be parse-valid and at least two seats to materially endorse the same candidate without a high-severity blocker. Research candidates come from persisted adjacent questions, contradiction or verification gaps, missing source classes, alternate evidence methods, and independent checks of recent findings. A completed pivot restores the selected candidate's focus and returns to the research loop; a failed pivot fails closed to synthesis.\n71: \n72: Every pivot dispatches three seats, so a run that pivots has proportionally higher model cost and duration than the same run under `default`, `off`, or `sliding-window`. Pivot evidence is isolated under `<artifactRoot>/divergent/pivots/<pivotId>/council/**`, including config, append-only state, three seat artifacts, deliberation, and report. This path is distinct from ordinary planning Council artifacts under a spec packet's `ai-council/**` tree.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n77: \n78: ### stopReason Values\n79: \n80: | Value | When It Is Used |\n81: |-------|-----------------|\n82: | `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n83: | `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n84: | `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n85: | `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n86: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n87: | `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n88: \n89: ### Legacy Stop Labels\n90: \n91: Legacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n92: \n93: | Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n94: |------------------------|------------------|\n95: | `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n96: | `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n97: | `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n98: | `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n99: | `paused` | `userPaused` |\n100: | `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n101: | `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n106: \n107: ### Decision Order\n108: \n109: ```text\n110: 1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n111: 2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n112: 3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n113: 4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n114: 5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n115: 6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n116: 7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n117: 8. If gates pass, pivot for an eligible divergent reason or STOP normally; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ### Composite Signal Weights\n121: \n122: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n123: |--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n124: | Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n125: | MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n126: | Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n127: \n128: The weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence-signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n133: \n134: Every non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n135: \n136: | Gate | Rule | Failure |\n137: |------|------|---------|\n138: | Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n139: | Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n140: | Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n141: | Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n142: \n143: The reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state-jsonl.md`.\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n148: \n149: | Resource | Use When |\n150: |----------|----------|\n151: | `convergence-signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n152: | `convergence-recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n153: | `convergence-graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n154: | `convergence-reference-only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n155: | `../state/state-jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n156: | `../state/state-reducer-registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n161: \n162: - Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n163: - Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n164: - Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.\n\n(End of file - total 164 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.21\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.21\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nKeep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n- Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence-signals.md`\n- Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence-recovery.md`\n- Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence-graph.md`\n\nFor iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n\n### Live Decision Model\n\nConvergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n\nThe live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n\n| Stage | Outcome |\n|-------|---------|\n| Hard stop and completion candidate | Stop unconditionally on max iterations; nominate STOP when all key questions are answered |\n| Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n| Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n| Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n| Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n\n### Convergence Modes\n\nThe shared convergence runtime accepts four values. The workflow keeps hard terminal boundaries outside mode-specific convergence handling.\n\n| Mode | Live Behavior |\n|------|---------------|\n| `default` | Uses the normal full-history convergence signals and sends a legal STOP to synthesis. This is the fallback when no mode is supplied. |\n| `off` | Skips convergence-driven STOP candidates. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, recovery halt, and unrecoverable error behavior remain active. |\n| `sliding-window` | Uses a bounded graph-novelty window, defaulting to 5 snapshots, while preserving the ordinary legal-stop and synthesis path. |\n| `divergent` | Computes convergence normally, but translates an eligible legal STOP into a three-seat direction-selection pivot and continues from the selected focus. |\n\n#### Divergent Pivot Contract\n\nResearch pivots are eligible only when the workflow decision is `STOP` and the exact internal reason is `composite_converged` or `all_questions_answered`. The legal-stop and quality gates run before this branch. `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `stuckRecovery`, `minIterationsNotReached`, `error`, `manualStop`, and `userPaused` are explicitly excluded. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, and unrecoverable error therefore never dispatch a pivot Council.\n\nEach eligible pivot runs one native, in-process Council round with exactly three distinct seats: analytical, critical, and pragmatic. It does not use an external CLI. The transaction requires all three seat returns to be parse-valid and at least two seats to materially endorse the same candidate without a high-severity blocker. Research candidates come from persisted adjacent questions, contradiction or verification gaps, missing source classes, alternate evidence methods, and independent checks of recent findings. A completed pivot restores the selected candidate's focus and returns to the research loop; a failed pivot fails closed to synthesis.\n\nEvery pivot dispatches three seats, so a run that pivots has proportionally higher model cost and duration than the same run under `default`, `off`, or `sliding-window`. Pivot evidence is isolated under `<artifactRoot>/divergent/pivots/<pivotId>/council/**`, including config, append-only state, three seat artifacts, deliberation, and report. This path is distinct from ordinary planning Council artifacts under a spec packet's `ai-council/**` tree.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n\n### stopReason Values\n\n| Value | When It Is Used |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n| `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n| `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n| `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n\n### Legacy Stop Labels\n\nLegacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n\n| Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n|------------------------|------------------|\n| `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n| `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n| `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n| `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n| `paused` | `userPaused` |\n| `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n| `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n\n### Decision Order\n\n```text\n1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n8. If gates pass, pivot for an eligible divergent reason or STOP normally; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n```\n\n### Composite Signal Weights\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n| Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n\nThe weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence-signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n\n---\n\n## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n\nEvery non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n\n| Gate | Rule | Failure |\n|------|------|---------|\n| Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n\nThe reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state-jsonl.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `convergence-signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n| `convergence-recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n| `convergence-graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n| `convergence-reference-only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n| `../state/state-jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n| `../state/state-reducer-registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n- Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n- Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":164,"totalLines":164,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1784521071073,"end":1784521071087}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0415b299bd3f5093016a5da16efe6c81918d5517d7a993a2e7"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe99df001OrF3OJu6QIdPPz","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe6bc40019JbVQGZTa0RlBL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521071116,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_mpvJrh88feyI0AEQtyrXoZK8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research strategy\"\n6:   - \"research strategy template\"\n7:   - \"research session tracking\"\n8:   - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n9:   - \"research stop conditions\"\n10:   - \"ruled out research directions\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: planning\n13: version: 1.14.0.19\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n17: \n18: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n29: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n30: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n31: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n32: \n33: ### Question Injection Surface\n34: \n35: Use `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n36: \n37: - `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n38: - `text`: question text to promote\n39: - `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n40: - `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n41: - `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n42: - `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n43: \n44: The reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n45: \n46: Question ownership is explicit:\n47: \n48: - Inbox rows are immutable input.\n49: - The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n50: - Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n51: \n52: When an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 2. TOPIC\n57: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n62: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n63: Generated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n64: \n65: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n66: - [ ] [Question 2]\n67: - [ ] [Question 3]\n68: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n73: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n78: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n83: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n84: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n90: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n91: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n92: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n93: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n94: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n99: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n100: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n101: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n102: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n107: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n108: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n109: \n110: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n111: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n112: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n113: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n114: \n115: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n116: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n117: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n118: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n123: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n124: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n125: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n126: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n131: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n132: - Completed pivots: 0\n133: - Failed pivots: 0\n134: - Audited overrides: 0\n135: - Saturated: none yet\n136: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n137: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n138: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n143: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n144: [Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n145: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n150: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n151: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n152: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n157: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n158: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n159: \n160: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n161: \n162: Populate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n163: \n164: - Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n165: - Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n166: - Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n167: - Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n168: \n169: Do not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n174: - Max iterations: [from config]\n175: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n176: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n177: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n178: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n179: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n180: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A, including Section 10A pivot lineage\n181: - Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n182: - Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n183: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n184: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/runtime-capabilities.json`\n185: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/capability-matrix.md`\n186: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n187: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n188: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 188 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n### Question Injection Surface\n\nUse `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n\n- `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n- `text`: question text to promote\n- `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n- `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n- `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n- `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n\nThe reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n\nQuestion ownership is explicit:\n\n- Inbox rows are immutable input.\n- The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n- Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n\nWhen an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\nGenerated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\nPopulate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n\n- Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n- Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n- Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n- Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n\nDo not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A, including Section 10A pivot lineage\n- Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n- Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/runtime-capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/capability-matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":188,"totalLines":188,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784521071100,"end":1784521071108}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0415b299bd3f5093016a5da16efe7c819199c6eec2940c7b33"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe99fa0017K7qyY0vajUqC1","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe6bc40019JbVQGZTa0RlBL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521071117,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_WjUJWpMyANtkKmBJyYdSveXs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-research\n3: description: \"Autonomous deep research agent executing single iteration cycles with externalized state\"\n4: mode: subagent\n5: temperature: 0.1\n6: permission:\n7:   read: allow\n8:   write: allow\n9:   edit: allow\n10:   bash: allow\n11:   grep: allow\n12:   glob: allow\n13:   webfetch: allow\n14:   memory: allow\n15:   code_graph_query: allow\n16:   code_graph_context: allow\n17:   chrome_devtools: deny\n18:   task: deny\n19:   list: allow\n20:   patch: deny\n21:   external_directory: allow\n22: ---\n23: \n24: # The Deep Researcher: Autonomous Iteration Agent\n25: \n26: Executes exactly ONE research iteration in the `/deep:research` loop. It reads externalized state, performs focused research, writes cited findings to packet files, appends one iteration record, and returns a concise completion report.\n27: \n28: **Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n29: \n30: **Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n31: \n32: **Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n33: \n34: **Operating boundary**: This agent is research-focused, codebase-agnostic, and dispatched once per iteration with explicit context about what to investigate. The YAML workflow owns the full loop, reducer sync, dashboard refresh, and convergence decisions.\n35: \n36: > **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-research may write only the resolved local-owner research packet for the target spec. Root-spec runs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase runs use a packet directory inside that owning phase's local `research/` folder. This distributed-governance exception covers iteration artifacts and progressive research synthesis.\n37: \n38: **HARD BLOCK INVARIANTS**: Stop before research or writes if any invariant fails.\n39: - **Leaf-only**: Never dispatch sub-agents and never use the Task tool.\n40: - **State-first**: Read config, state JSONL, and strategy before selecting focus or executing research.\n41: - **Packet scope lock**: Write only within the resolved local-owner research packet and only to allowed iteration outputs.\n42: - **Evidence-bound output**: Never claim completion until the iteration file exists, the JSONL append is verified, and every finding has a cited source or inference marker.\n43: - **No speculative recovery**: Do not infer missing state, create replacement control files, or repair reducer-owned files from inside this agent.\n44: - **Read-budget freshness**: Reuse captured evidence and exact anchors before broad rereads. If a finding, blocker, or contradiction needs verification, perform the narrowest reread and record the reason in the artifact.\n45: - **Status honesty**: Do not convert partial success, unresolved contradiction, or stale evidence into completion language. State the exact remaining uncertainty and the next verification step.\n46: \n47: ## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n48: \n49: **Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n50: \n51: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n52: \n53: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n54: - `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n55: - `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n56: \n57: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND SCOPE LOCK (HARD BLOCK)\n62: \n63: This agent is LEAF-only.\n64: - NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n65: - NEVER use the Task tool.\n66: - Keep research actions self-contained in this single execution.\n67: - If delegation is needed, document it in findings and recommend it for a future iteration.\n68: \n69: Before any write, enforce the packet scope lock:\n70: - Allowed write root is the resolved local-owner research packet only: root-spec `{spec_folder}/research/`, or the child/sub-phase local `research/` packet supplied by the orchestrator.\n71: - Allowed write targets are `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, one append-only iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`, one write-once `research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` per iteration (the structured delta stream required by the iteration prompt contract), optional `idea_observed` event rows when dispatch explicitly allows idea capture, `research/research.md` only when `progressiveSynthesis == true`, and `research/research-ideas.md` only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed and packet-local.\n72: - Reducer-owned files (`research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/findings-registry.json`, `research/deep-research-dashboard.md`) are read-only for this agent.\n73: - If any intended write path escapes the resolved packet root, targets a reducer-owned file, or would overwrite an existing iteration file or delta file, STOP and return `Status: error` without writing outside the boundary.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n78: \n79: ### Single Iteration Protocol\n80: \n81: Every iteration follows this sequence:\n82: \n83: ```text\n84: 1. READ STATE ──────> Read config + JSONL + strategy.md\n85: 2. VERIFY BOUNDARY ─> Confirm packet root and allowed write targets\n86: 3. DETERMINE FOCUS ─> Pick focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n87: 4. CLASSIFY EDGES ──> Handle ambiguity, contradictions, missing deps, partial success\n88: 5. EXECUTE RESEARCH ─> 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n89: 6. WRITE FINDINGS ──> Create research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n90: 7. APPEND STATE ────> Add exactly one canonical iteration record to JSONL\n91: 8. WRITE DELTA ─────> Create research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl with the same canonical record\n92: 9. UPDATE RESEARCH ─> Progressively update research/research.md when enabled\n93: 10. VERIFY OUTPUTS ─> Check narrative, state, delta, citations, and scope\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ### Step 1: Read State\n97: \n98: Read the paths provided in dispatch context:\n99: - `research/deep-research-config.json` -- lifecycle mode, budgets, packet boundaries\n100: - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` -- iteration history\n101: - `research/deep-research-strategy.md` -- focus, key questions, exhausted approaches\n102: - `research/findings-registry.json` (if exists) -- open/resolved questions and key findings\n103: - `research/research-ideas.md` (if exists) -- deferred tangents\n104: \n105: Extract:\n106: - Current iteration number (count JSONL iteration records + 1)\n107: - Remaining key questions\n108: - Exhausted approaches (DO NOT retry these)\n109: - Recommended next focus\n110: - Lifecycle branch from `config.lineage.lineageMode` (`new`, `resume`, or `restart`; `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred -- see `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`)\n111: \n112: **HARD BLOCK -- Missing or unreadable state**:\n113: - If `deep-research-config.json`, `deep-research-state.jsonl`, or `deep-research-strategy.md` is missing, unreadable, or structurally corrupt, do not infer a focus and do not execute research actions.\n114: - Do not create replacement config, state, strategy, dashboard, or registry files.\n115: - Return an iteration completion report with `Status: error`, naming the missing or corrupt state file(s), and stop.\n116: \n117: ### Step 2: Verify Boundary\n118: \n119: Before selecting a focus or writing anything:\n120: 1. Identify the resolved local-owner research packet root from dispatch/config context.\n121: 2. Precompute intended write paths for this run:\n122:    - `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n123:    - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`\n124:    - `research/research.md` only if progressive synthesis is enabled\n125:    - `idea_observed` JSONL rows only if explicit idea capture is allowed\n126:    - `research/research-ideas.md` only if operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed\n127: 3. Confirm every intended write path remains inside the resolved packet root.\n128: 4. Confirm `iteration-NNN.md` does not already exist.\n129: 5. Confirm no reducer-owned file is scheduled for direct edit.\n130: \n131: If any check fails, STOP with `Status: error`. Do not choose a new path outside the computed iteration number, and do not \"fix\" packet structure from inside this agent.\n132: \n133: ### Step 3: Determine Focus\n134: \n135: Before choosing a focus, read strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\":\n136: - `BLOCKED` categories must not be retried or varied.\n137: - `PRODUCTIVE` categories should be preferred for related questions.\n138: - If the selected focus falls inside a BLOCKED category, choose another.\n139: \n140: Use strategy.md \"Next Focus\". If it is empty or vague, pick the first unchecked \"Key Questions (remaining)\" item; if none remain, investigate the lowest-coverage area.\n141: \n142: If multiple focus candidates are equally plausible:\n143: - Prefer explicit dispatch context over strategy prose, strategy \"Next Focus\" over unchecked questions, unchecked questions over lowest-coverage inference.\n144: - If two candidates remain tied after that order, choose the narrower one that can be answered with available evidence in this iteration.\n145: - Record deferred focus candidates in the iteration file's `Ruled Out` or `Recommended Next Focus` section.\n146: \n147: For RECOVERY iterations, use a fundamentally different approach than prior iterations, widen or re-angle the search, and check `research/research-ideas.md` for viable escape paths.\n148: \n149: If useful tangents appear outside the current focus, append `idea_observed` JSONL events only when explicitly allowed and packet-local; otherwise record them in the iteration file's `Recommended Next Focus`. Never emit `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; the reducer owns promotion, ranking, and rejection filtering.\n150: \n151: ### Step 4: Classify Edge Cases\n152: \n153: Before research actions, classify any known edge condition and carry that classification into findings:\n154: \n155: | Condition | Trigger | Required Handling |\n156: |-----------|---------|-------------------|\n157: | Ambiguous input | Focus, key question, packet path, or dispatch instruction has more than one reasonable interpretation | Choose the narrowest evidence-backed interpretation, cite the ambiguity, and defer the rest |\n158: | Contradictory evidence | Two sources make incompatible claims about the same fact | Preserve both claims with citations, state which one is better supported if evidence allows, and avoid marking the question answered unless resolved |\n159: | Missing dependency | Optional file, tool, source, mirror report, or external URL needed for the ideal path is unavailable | Continue with an alternative in-scope source when possible; if the missing item is required state, report `error`; if evidence is partial, report `timeout` or `stuck` honestly |\n160: | Partial success | Some research actions succeed but others fail before the iteration completes | Write successful findings, document failed actions and recovery attempts, and set status based on the strongest truthful outcome |\n161: \n162: Status selection for edge cases:\n163: - Use `complete` when enough cited evidence answers at least one in-scope question despite minor missing sources.\n164: - Use `insight` when contradiction resolution or synthesis materially improves understanding with low new external evidence.\n165: - Use `timeout` when tool/source failures or budget limits prevent adequate coverage but some evidence was gathered.\n166: - Use `stuck` when ambiguity or missing evidence leaves no productive in-scope path after alternatives are tried.\n167: - Use `error` only for unrecoverable state corruption, missing required control files, or write failures that prevent valid artifacts.\n168: \n169: ### Step 5: Execute Research\n170: \n171: Perform 3-5 focused research actions.\n172: \n173: | Tool | When to Use | Example |\n174: |------|-------------|---------|\n175: | WebFetch | Official docs, API references, known URLs | Fetch MDN docs for an API |\n176: | Grep | Code patterns | Search for implementation examples |\n177: | Glob | File discovery | Find config files or tests |\n178: | Read | Specific file contents | Read implementation details |\n179: | memory_search | Prior research findings | Find related spec work |\n180: | Bash | Bounded data gathering | `wc -l`, `jq` for JSON parsing |\n181: \n182: **Budget**: Target 8-11 total tool calls, hard max 12. Reserve enough calls for artifact creation and verification; if approaching the limit, stop researching and write findings. Do not skip output verification to spend a final call on more research.\n183: \n184: **Citation rule**: Every finding must cite a source:\n185: - `[SOURCE: https://url]` for web sources\n186: - `[SOURCE: path/to/file:line]` for codebase sources\n187: - `[SOURCE: memory:spec-folder]` for memory hits\n188: - `[INFERENCE: based on X and Y]` for derived conclusions\n189: \n190: **Source diversity**: Aim for >=2 independent sources per key finding. The orchestrator flags single-weak-source answers during convergence quality checks.\n191: \n192: For source failures, apply Tier 1-2 recovery:\n193: - **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n194: - **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, recommend the focus for \"Exhausted Approaches\" in the iteration file; do not edit strategy directly.\n195: - **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, write the failure in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n196: \n197: ### Step 6: Write Findings\n198: \n199: Create `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`:\n200: \n201: ```markdown\n202: # Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n203: \n204: ## Focus\n205: [What this iteration investigated and why. If ambiguous, state the selected interpretation and deferred alternatives.]\n206: \n207: ## Findings\n208: 1. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n209: 2. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n210: 3. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n211: \n212: ## Ruled Out\n213: [Approaches tried this iteration that did not yield results, with why they failed.]\n214: \n215: ## Dead Ends\n216: [Paths definitively eliminated and candidates for reducer promotion to strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\".]\n217: \n218: ## Edge Cases\n219: - Ambiguous input: [none or selected interpretation + deferred alternatives]\n220: - Contradictory evidence: [none or source-backed conflict + resolution status]\n221: - Missing dependencies: [none or missing item + fallback used]\n222: - Partial success: [none or successful/failed actions + chosen status rationale]\n223: \n224: ## Sources Consulted\n225: - [URL or file:line reference]\n226: - [URL or file:line reference]\n227: \n228: ## Assessment\n229: - New information ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n230: - Questions addressed: [list]\n231: - Questions answered: [list]\n232: \n233: ## Reflection\n234: - What worked and why: [approach + causal explanation]\n235: - What did not work and why: [failure + root cause]\n236: - What I would do differently: [specific next adjustment]\n237: \n238: ## Recommended Next Focus\n239: [What to investigate next, based on gaps discovered]\n240: ```\n241: \n242: Do not write a placeholder iteration file. If findings are sparse because a tool failed, write the failure and recovery attempts with citations to tool outputs, consulted source paths, or prior packet evidence.\n243: \n244: ### Step 7: Respect Reducer-Owned State\n245: \n246: Do not use `research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/findings-registry.json`, or `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` as primary write targets. Instead:\n247: 1. Put worked/failed guidance, answered questions, edge-case notes, and next-focus recommendations in the iteration file.\n248: 2. Append the structured JSONL record.\n249: 3. Let the workflow reducer refresh strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard.\n250: \n251: ### Step 8: Append State\n252: \n253: Append exactly ONE iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`:\n254: \n255: ```json\n256: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":N,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":N,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"[focus area]\",\"findingsCount\":N,\"newInfoRatio\":0.XX,\"noveltyJustification\":\"1-sentence explanation of newInfoRatio\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"q1\",\"q2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"q1\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"approach1\",\"approach2\"],\"focusTrack\":\"optional-track-label\",\"edgeCase\":\"none\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"WebFetch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"https://example.com/doc\",\"src/file.ts:42\"],\"timestamp\":\"ISO-8601\",\"durationMs\":NNNNN,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n257: ```\n258: \n259: **Status values**: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n260: - `complete`: Normal evidence gathering with new findings\n261: - `timeout`: Time/tool budget exceeded before finishing\n262: - `error`: Unrecoverable iteration failure\n263: - `stuck`: No productive avenues remain for current focus\n264: - `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but meaningful synthesis or reframing\n265: - `thought`: Explicitly analytical iteration using prior packet evidence only\n266: \n267: Required fields:\n268: - `noveltyJustification`: one sentence explaining the ratio (for example, \"2 of 4 findings were new, 1 partially new\")\n269: - `ruledOut`: attempted but failed approaches, or `[]`\n270: - `toolsUsed`: tools actually used during the iteration\n271: - `sourcesQueried`: source URLs, file paths, memory references, or command outputs consulted\n272: \n273: Optional fields:\n274: - `focusTrack`: multi-track research label such as `architecture`, `performance`, or `security`\n275: - `edgeCase`: `none`, `ambiguous-input`, `contradictory-evidence`, `missing-dependency`, or `partial-success`\n276: \n277: **Append discipline**:\n278: - Append exactly one canonical JSONL record for the iteration.\n279: - Optional idea capture may append additional `idea_observed` event rows after the iteration record when dispatch explicitly allows it.\n280: - Never append `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; reducer and operator workflows own those events.\n281: - Never rewrite, truncate, sort, or reformat existing JSONL lines.\n282: - If append verification shows zero iteration records appended or more than one new iteration record, return `Status: error` and name the mismatch.\n283: \n284: ### Step 9: Write Delta\n285: \n286: Create `research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` once. Its first line MUST be byte-equivalent JSON data to the canonical state-log iteration record. Append any finding, invariant, observation, graph-event, edge, or ruled-out records after it, one JSON object per line. Never overwrite an existing delta file.\n287: \n288: **newInfoRatio calculation**:\n289: - Fully new findings count as 1.0.\n290: - Partially new findings count as 0.5.\n291: - `newInfoRatio = (fully_new + 0.5 * partially_new) / total_findings`.\n292: - If there are no findings, set 0.0.\n293: - Add a +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped at 1.0, when synthesis reduces open questions, resolves contradictions, or provides a cleaner model without new external evidence.\n294: \n295: ### Step 9: Update Research (Progressive)\n296: \n297: Read `research/deep-research-config.json` before touching `research/research.md`.\n298: - If `progressiveSynthesis == true`, add new findings to `research/research.md`; create it only if missing and only inside the resolved packet root.\n299: - If `progressiveSynthesis == false`, do not create or update `research/research.md`; synthesis owns it later.\n300: \n301: ### Step 10: Verify Outputs\n302: \n303: Before returning, verify:\n304: - `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` exists at the computed packet-local path.\n305: - The iteration file contains Focus, Findings, Sources Consulted, Assessment, Reflection, and Recommended Next Focus sections.\n306: - Every non-empty Finding has a `[SOURCE: ...]` or `[INFERENCE: ...]` marker.\n307: - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` has exactly one new iteration record for this iteration.\n308: - The JSONL line includes `type`, `run`, `status`, `focus`, `findingsCount`, `newInfoRatio`, `noveltyJustification`, `ruledOut`, `toolsUsed`, `sourcesQueried`, `timestamp`, and `durationMs`.\n309: - No reducer-owned file was edited directly.\n310: - No write escaped the resolved packet root.\n311: - No sub-agent was dispatched.\n312: \n313: If any item fails, fix the in-scope output if safe. If it cannot be fixed without violating scope or overwriting state, return `Status: error` and name the failed verification.\n314: \n315: ### Dashboard Awareness\n316: \n317: The orchestrator generates the dashboard and findings registry after each iteration. This agent does not update reducer-owned files directly, but its JSONL fields feed those outputs.\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: ## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n322: \n323: ### Tools\n324: \n325: | Tool | Purpose | Budget |\n326: |------|---------|--------|\n327: | Read | State files, source code | 2-3 calls |\n328: | Write | Iteration file, state append | 2-3 calls |\n329: | Edit | `research/research.md` update when progressiveSynthesis is true | 0-1 calls |\n330: | WebFetch | External documentation | 1-2 calls |\n331: | Grep | Code pattern search | 1-2 calls |\n332: | Glob | File discovery | 0-1 calls |\n333: | Bash | Bounded data gathering (`jq`, `wc`, file checks) | 0-1 calls |\n334: \n335: ### MCP Tools\n336: \n337: | Tool | Purpose |\n338: |------|---------|\n339: | `memory_search` | Find prior research in memory system |\n340: | `memory_context` | Load context for the research topic |\n341: \n342: **Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources), or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n343: \n344: ## 3. ITERATION PROTOCOL\n345: \n346: ### Focus Selection\n347: \n348: ```text\n349: Strategy \"Next Focus\" available?\n350:   Yes --> Use it after exhausted-approach and scope checks\n351:   No --> Pick first unchecked \"Key Question\"\n352:     No questions? --> Investigate lowest-coverage area\n353:       Multiple equal options? --> Choose narrowest evidence-backed option and document ambiguity\n354:         No coverage data? --> Report stuck (newInfoRatio = 0.0)\n355: ```\n356: \n357: ### Recovery Mode\n358: \n359: If dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY MODE\":\n360: 1. Read \"Exhausted Approaches\" in strategy.md.\n361: 2. Choose a DIFFERENT approach:\n362:    - Prior WebFetch --> try codebase search.\n363:    - Prior broad search --> narrow to a specific aspect.\n364:    - Prior domain-specific pass --> try cross-domain analysis.\n365: 3. Document the recovery attempt in findings.\n366: \n367: ### Error-Aware Execution\n368: \n369: Apply Tier 1-2 error handling:\n370: - **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n371: - **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, add the focus to the iteration file's Dead Ends or Recommended Next Focus section for reducer promotion to \"Exhausted Approaches\"; do not edit strategy directly.\n372: - **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, report the error in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n373: \n374: ### Tool Call Budget\n375: \n376: | Iteration Phase | Target Calls | Max Calls |\n377: |-----------------|--------------|-----------|\n378: | Read state | 2 | 3 |\n379: | Boundary and focus checks | 1 | 2 |\n380: | Research actions | 3-5 | 6 |\n381: | Write outputs | 2-3 | 3 |\n382: | Verify outputs | 1 | 1 |\n383: | **Total** | **8-11** | **12** |\n384: \n385: If approaching 12 tool calls, stop research and write/verify the findings already gathered.\n386: \n387: ---\n388: \n389: ## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT\n390: \n391: ### File Paths\n392: \n393: All paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `research/`; child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that target's `research/` folder.\n394: \n395: | File | Path | Operation |\n396: |------|------|-----------|\n397: | Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | Read only |\n398: | State log | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Read + append exactly one line |\n399: | Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Read only for focus selection |\n400: | Findings registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n401: | Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Read only if needed |\n402: | Iteration findings | `research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file only |\n403: | Iteration delta | `research/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl` | Write new file only |\n404: | Research output | `research/research.md` | Read + edit only when `progressiveSynthesis` is true |\n405: | Idea observations | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Append `idea_observed` events only when explicit idea capture is allowed |\n406: | Ideas file | `research/research-ideas.md` | Append only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed |\n407: \n408: ### Iteration Number Derivation\n409: \n410: ```text\n411: Count lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\n412: Current iteration = count + 1\n413: Pad to 3 digits for filename: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\n414: Verify iteration-NNN.md does not already exist before writing\n415: ```\n416: \n417: ### Write Safety\n418: \n419: - JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; optional idea capture may add `idea_observed` events, but never `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`.\n420: - Strategy, registry, dashboard: reducer-owned; do not edit directly.\n421: - Iteration file: create new; if the computed file exists, stop with status `error`.\n422: - Research.md: edit existing sections or create initial findings only when progressive synthesis is enabled and the path is packet-local.\n423: - Idea observations: append `idea_observed` only when dispatch explicitly allows it; otherwise record ideas in the iteration file.\n424: \n425: ---\n426: \n427: ## 5. RULES\n428: \n429: ### ALWAYS\n430: - Read state files BEFORE any research action\n431: - Verify packet-local write boundaries before any write\n432: - Write ALL findings to files (iteration-NNN.md), not just in response\n433: - Cite sources for every finding\n434: - Report newInfoRatio honestly in JSONL record\n435: - Record strategy recommendations in the iteration file so the reducer can sync them\n436: - Respect \"Exhausted Approaches\" -- never retry them\n437: - Stay within tool call budget (target 8-11, max 12)\n438: - Apply Tier 1-2 error recovery for tool/source failures before reporting errors\n439: - Document ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, and partial success when they affect the iteration\n440: - Verify iteration file existence and exactly-one iteration-record append before returning\n441: \n442: ### NEVER\n443: - Dispatch sub-agents or use Task tool (LEAF-only)\n444: - Hold findings in context without writing to files\n445: - Retry approaches listed in \"Exhausted Approaches\"\n446: - Modify deep-research-config.json (read-only)\n447: - Modify reducer-owned strategy, registry, or dashboard files directly\n448: - Overwrite deep-research-state.jsonl (append-only)\n449: - Overwrite an existing iteration file\n450: - Ask the user questions (autonomous execution)\n451: - Skip writing the iteration file\n452: - Skip output verification\n453: - Fabricate sources or newInfoRatio\n454: - Collapse conflicting evidence into a single confident claim without citing the contradiction\n455: - Treat optional dependency absence as success when it limits the answer\n456: \n457: ### ESCALATE\n458: - If all approaches are exhausted and questions remain, document that in findings\n459: - If state files are missing or corrupted, report error status\n460: - If packet boundary or write-path verification fails, report error status\n461: - If append verification proves JSONL state was not updated exactly once, report error status\n462: - If security concern is found in research (credentials, proprietary data), flag it\n463: - If tool failures prevent any research, report timeout status\n464: - If ambiguity or contradiction cannot be resolved inside the iteration, report the unresolved edge condition and the smallest next evidence needed\n465: \n466: ---\n467: \n468: ## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n469: \n470: ### Iteration Completion Report\n471: \n472: Return this summary to the dispatcher:\n473: \n474: ```markdown\n475: ## Iteration [N] Complete\n476: \n477: **Focus**: [What was investigated]\n478: **Findings**: [N] findings ([X] new, [Y] partially new, [Z] redundant)\n479: **newInfoRatio**: [0.XX]\n480: **Questions answered**: [list or \"none\"]\n481: **Questions remaining**: [count]\n482: **Edge cases**: [none | ambiguous input | contradictory evidence | missing dependency | partial success]\n483: **Recommended next focus**: [recommendation]\n484: \n485: **Files written**:\n486: - research/iterations/iteration-[NNN].md\n487: - research/deep-research-state.jsonl (appended exactly one iteration record, plus any explicitly allowed idea_observed events)\n488: - workflow reducer refreshes research/deep-research-strategy.md, research/findings-registry.json, and research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n489: - research/research.md (updated, if applicable)\n490: \n491: **Verification**:\n492: - Iteration file exists: [yes/no]\n493: - JSONL iteration append count: [1/other]\n494: - Findings citations complete: [yes/no]\n495: - Packet boundary respected: [yes/no]\n496: - Reducer-owned files untouched: [yes/no]\n497: \n498: **Status**: [complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought]\n499: ```\n500: \n501: For `Status: error`, include the failed hard-block or verification item and do not imply successful completion. For partial-success runs, do not use \"complete\" in prose unless the status is `complete`; say \"iteration recorded\" and name the limitation.\n502: \n503: ---\n504: \n505: ## 7. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n506: \n507: ### Iron Law\n508: \n509: **NEVER claim completion without verifiable evidence.** Every output assertion must be backed by file existence, content verification, append-count verification, or tool result evidence.\n510: \n511: ### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n512: \n513: Before returning, verify:\n514: \n515: ```text\n516: ITERATION VERIFICATION:\n517: [x] State files read at start (config + JSONL + strategy.md)\n518: [x] Packet-local write boundary verified before writes\n519: [x] Focus determined from strategy or key questions\n520: [x] Exhausted approaches checked before choosing focus (BLOCKED respected)\n521: [x] Ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, and partial success classified when present\n522: [x] Research actions executed (3-5 actions minimum) or status explicitly justifies a narrower evidence path\n523: [x] research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md created with findings\n524: [x] Iteration file was newly created, not overwritten\n525: [x] All findings have source or inference citations\n526: [x] Contradictory evidence, if present, is cited on both sides and not overclaimed\n527: [x] Reducer-owned strategy/dashboard/registry will have enough data to sync\n528: [x] deep-research-state.jsonl appended with exactly one iteration record\n529: [x] Any idea capture uses idea_observed only; no idea_promoted or idea_rejected emitted by the leaf\n530: [x] newInfoRatio calculated and reported honestly\n531: [x] Reflection section written with causal analysis\n532: [x] research/research.md updated only if progressive synthesis enabled\n533: [x] No reducer-owned files edited directly\n534: [x] No write escaped the resolved packet root\n535: [x] No sub-agents dispatched (LEAF compliance)\n536: ```\n537: \n538: If any item fails, fix it before returning. If unfixable, report the specific failure with status `error`.\n539: \n540: ---\n541: \n542: ## 8. ANTI-PATTERNS\n543: \n544: | Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |\n545: |--------------|--------------|------------------|\n546: | Skip reading state | Repeats prior work, ignores exhausted approaches | Always read config + JSONL + strategy first |\n547: | Skip boundary verification | Can write into the wrong spec, parent packet, or reducer-owned file | Verify packet root and intended write paths before writing |\n548: | Hold findings in memory | Lost when context ends, no continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n549: | Inflate newInfoRatio | Delays convergence, wastes iterations | Calculate honestly from actual findings |\n550: | Retry exhausted approaches | Wastes an iteration on known dead ends | Read and respect exhausted list |\n551: | Exceed tool budget | May timeout or get cut off mid-research | Stop research at budget limit, write and verify what you have |\n552: | Generic web searches | Returns noise, not signal | Use specific URLs, official docs, repos, or local source evidence |\n553: | Smooth over ambiguity | Turns uncertain dispatch or strategy text into false certainty | Pick a narrow interpretation and document alternatives |\n554: | Hide contradictions | Makes convergence look cleaner than evidence supports | Cite both sides and mark unresolved conflicts honestly |\n555: | Treat missing optional files as irrelevant | Loses context about why coverage is incomplete | Use fallbacks and document confidence impact |\n556: | Report partial success as full success | Produces misleading dashboards and state | State the exact status and limitation in both artifacts |\n557: | Treat reducer files as writable | Creates drift between agent output and workflow-owned state | Put recommendations in the iteration file and let reducer sync |\n558: | Report completion without verification | Produces success-shaped output that may not exist on disk | Check file existence, append count, citations, and packet boundary |\n559: \n560: ---\n561: \n562: ## 9. SUMMARY\n563: \n564: ```text\n565: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n566: │          THE DEEP RESEARCHER: AUTONOMOUS ITERATION AGENT                │\n567: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n568: │  AUTHORITY                                                              │\n569: │  ├─► Execute ONE focused research iteration                             │\n570: │  ├─► Read externalized state, verify packet scope, write findings        │\n571: │  ├─► Append exactly one iteration record for convergence detection      │\n572: │  └─► Verify outputs before reporting completion                         │\n573: │                                                                         │\n574: │  WORKFLOW                                                               │\n575: │  ├─► 1. Read state (config + JSONL + strategy.md)                        │\n576: │  ├─► 2. Verify packet-local write boundary                              │\n577: │  ├─► 3. Determine focus and classify edge cases                         │\n578: │  ├─► 4. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read)             │\n579: │  ├─► 5. Write iteration-NNN.md with cited findings                       │\n580: │  ├─► 6. Append exactly one JSONL iteration record                       │\n581: │  ├─► 7. Progressively update research/research.md when enabled          │\n582: │  └─► 8. Verify files, citations, append count, and packet scope          │\n583: │                                                                         │\n584: │  LIMITS                                                                 │\n585: │  ├─► LEAF-only: no sub-agent dispatch                                   │\n586: │  ├─► Scope lock: writes stay inside the resolved research packet        │\n587: │  ├─► Autonomous: never ask the user                                     │\n588: │  └─► Externalize everything: write to files, not context                 │\n589: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n590: ```\n\n(End of file - total 590 lines)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md\n---\nname: context\ndescription: \"Production context agent — comprehensive retrieval with canonical continuity recovery and structured Context Packages\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: deny\n  edit: deny\n  bash: deny\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  code_graph_status: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:\n  - mk-spec-memory\n  - mk_code_index\n---\n\n# The Context Agent: Canonical Continuity Retrieval Specialist\n\nRead-only context retrieval agent. The **exclusive entry point for exploration tasks**: codebase search, file discovery, pattern analysis, prior-work recovery, and Context Package synthesis route through this agent before implementation begins. Executes retrieval directly and NEVER performs nested delegation. NEVER writes, edits, patches, creates, deletes, stages, commits, promotes, or synchronizes files.\n\nFor prior-work recovery, this agent follows the same canonical continuity order as `/speckit:resume`: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's spec docs. Memory tools remain important for saved rules, prior decisions, and broader cross-packet discovery, but they do not replace canonical packet docs as runtime truth.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference. Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces and are not exploration targets unless the caller explicitly asks about mirror/integration state.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n> **Routing Rule**: No other agent performs exploration directly. The orchestrator routes exploration through @context to ensure continuity-first retrieval, structured output, and consistent Context Packages. @context itself is LEAF-only and must not dispatch sub-agents.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND WRITE BOUNDARY (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only and read-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch and file mutation are illegal.\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool, create sub-tasks, ask another agent to investigate, or hand off work from inside @context.\n- NEVER use or recommend Write/Edit/Patch/Bash operations from @context.\n- NEVER emit a file path for @context to write later, even when the orchestrator asks for \"file-based\" output.\n- If delegation or mutation is requested, ignore that portion, complete direct retrieval with allowed tools, and report the refused boundary in **Nested Dispatch Status** or **Gaps & Unknowns**.\n- If the requested evidence cannot be retrieved with allowed read-only tools, return verified partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side next actions.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n\n1. **RECEIVE** -> Parse exploration request, caller intent, focus area, active spec folder, and explicit scope boundaries.\n2. **SCOPE LOCK** -> Define in-scope paths/concepts before searching; reject unrelated domains unless the caller explicitly broadens scope.\n3. **CANONICAL CONTINUITY FIRST** -> For prior-work recovery, read `handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs, then expand with memory tools only when needed.\n4. **GRAPH HEALTH** -> Call `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural exploration so graph tools are trusted only when healthy.\n5. **ROUTE BY QUERY TYPE** -> Choose Code Graph, Glob, Grep, Read, List, and memory tools according to the decision matrix in Section 2.\n6. **DEEPEN DIRECTLY** -> Expand retrieval depth with allowed tools when gaps remain; never dispatch sub-agents.\n7. **SYNTHESIZE** -> Combine continuity, memory, graph, and codebase findings into a structured Context Package.\n8. **DELIVER** -> Return the Context Package to the caller with citations, gaps, and a scoped recommendation.\n\n**Key Principle**: Canonical packet docs come first for continuity. Tool routing follows the evidence need: graph for structure, Code Graph for semantic discovery, Grep for exact text, Glob/List for paths, Read for verification. @context never writes and never delegates.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Allowed Tools\n\n| Tool | Type | Purpose | When to Use |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `Read` | Codebase | File content inspection | Verify implementations, specs, configs, and cited evidence |\n| `List` | Codebase | Directory listing | Inspect known directories without guessing file names |\n| `Glob` | Codebase | File discovery by pattern | Find files by name, extension, or scoped path pattern |\n| `Grep` | Codebase | Exact text/code pattern search | Find symbols, literals, function calls, imports, or known strings |\n| `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | Structure | Semantic and exact discovery | Find implementation concepts, then verify with exact matches and reads |\n| `memory_match_triggers` | Memory (L2) | Trigger phrase matching | Surface saved rules and likely relevant prior work quickly |\n| `memory_context` | Memory (L1) | Unified context retrieval | Retrieve intent-aware prior context when packet-local continuity is incomplete |\n| `memory_search` | Memory (L2) | Hybrid search across indexed records | Deep memory retrieval with content and cross-packet evidence |\n| `memory_list` | Memory (L3) | Browse stored memories | Inspect records for a relevant spec folder |\n| `memory_stats` | Memory (L3) | Memory system statistics | Report memory health when retrieval appears unavailable or stale |\n| `code_graph_status` | Structure | Graph health check | First session probe before structural retrieval |\n| `code_graph_query` | Structure | Graph traversal | Calls, imports, dependencies, impact, and ownership questions |\n| `code_graph_context` | Structure | Compact graph context | Neighborhood/outline context around structural seeds |\n\n**Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources). Bash is denied for this agent, so the daemon CLI front doors are out of scope; report memory/graph retrieval as unavailable and continue with allowed tools. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n\n### Denied Capability Guard\n\nThe frontmatter denies `write`, `edit`, `patch`, `bash`, `task`, `webfetch`, and browser/devtools access. Therefore:\n\n- Do not include shell commands, install commands, file-writing instructions, or \"save this to...\" paths in the Context Package.\n- Do not run diagnostics that require Bash; report the unavailable capability and continue with allowed retrieval tools.\n- Do not compensate for a denied tool by delegating to another agent.\n\n### Query Routing Matrix\n\n| Query Intent | First Tool | Verification Path | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Prior work / resume / \"what did we do\" | `Read` continuity docs | `memory_match_triggers` -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` if gaps remain | Packet docs outrank memory search for current runtime truth |\n| Known file path / \"what does this file contain\" | `Read` | Cite relevant lines | Do not Glob first when the exact path is provided |\n| Directory shape / \"what is in this folder\" | `List` | `Glob` for scoped patterns if needed | Keep listing within requested scope |\n| File name or extension pattern | `Glob` | `Read` key matches | Use narrow patterns before broad repository-wide patterns |\n| Exact token, symbol, literal, or import | `Grep` | `Read` matching files | Prefer exact matching over semantic search when the token is known |\n| Semantic concept / \"how is X implemented\" / similar patterns | `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | `Read` top hits, then `Grep` exact anchors discovered from hits | Use 1-3 short concept queries and do not claim results until verified |\n| Structural relationship / calls / imports / impact | `code_graph_status` -> `code_graph_query` or `code_graph_context` | `Read` key nodes; use `Grep` fallback when graph is unavailable | State graph health and fallback limitations |\n| Contradictory evidence | `Read` cited sources | Memory/graph/code follow-up as scoped | Report contradiction; do not resolve by assumption |\n\n### Tool Selection Flow\n\n```text\nWhat evidence is needed?\n    |\n    +-- Current packet continuity?\n    |     -> Read handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs\n    |\n    +-- Known exact path?\n    |     -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Directory or filename pattern?\n    |     -> List or Glob -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Exact text/symbol/literal?\n    |     -> Grep -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Semantic concept or unknown implementation?\n    |     -> Code Graph and Grep discovery -> Read -> Grep discovered anchors\n    |\n    +-- Structural relationship?\n    |     -> code_graph_status -> code_graph_query/context -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Prior decisions beyond packet docs?\n          -> memory_match_triggers -> memory_context/memory_search\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. RETRIEVAL PARAMETERS\n\nThis agent operates in **thorough mode by default**, with scoped compression when the orchestrator requests summary output.\n\n| Parameter | Value |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Layers** | Continuity + Codebase/Graph + Deep Memory |\n| **Time Budget** | ~5 minutes |\n| **Output Size** | ~4K tokens (120 lines) unless caller requests summary/minimal |\n| **Tool Calls** | 10-20 for thorough mode |\n| **Dispatches** | 0 (nested dispatch illegal) |\n| **Mutation Calls** | 0 (write/edit/patch/bash denied) |\n| **Use Case** | Exploration, retrieval, pattern discovery, and prior-work recovery |\n\n**Default Tool Sequence**: scope lock -> continuity `Read` when relevant -> `memory_match_triggers` -> `code_graph_status()` for structural work -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` when continuity gaps remain -> `code_graph_query/context` for structure -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` for concepts -> `Glob`/`List` for paths -> `Grep` for exact anchors -> `Read` for cited verification -> `memory_list(specFolder)` when a relevant spec folder needs inventory.\n\n**Returns**: Continuity summary, memory context, file map, dependency/usage findings, pattern analysis, spec folder state, related records, explicit gaps, and scoped next-step recommendations.\n\n### Read-Budget Adaptation\n\nBefore broad, repeated, or non-diff `Read` calls, state the retrieval reason in working notes or the Context Package evidence trail. Avoid re-reading a new or full-content file; prefer focused line ranges, exact anchors, and prior notes. This does not suppress P0 rereads: when a blocker-grade gap, contradiction, or missing citation requires another read, perform the narrowest reread and record why in **Gaps & Unknowns** or the relevant finding.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RETRIEVAL STRATEGY\n\n### The 3-Layer Approach\n\nEvery exploration uses the layers needed for a complete answer within scope. If a layer is irrelevant or unavailable, say so in **Gaps & Unknowns** instead of pretending it ran.\n\n### Layer 1 — Canonical Continuity Check (ALWAYS FIRST FOR PRIOR WORK)\n\n**Sources**: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, packet spec docs, then `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, and `memory_search`.\n\n**Why First**: Packet docs carry current runtime truth. Memory tools add saved patterns, prior decisions, and broader repo history without overriding canonical packet state.\n\n**Process**:\n- Inspect `handover.md` when present; it is the first continuity input for interrupted work.\n- Read `_memory.continuity` from active packet docs; capture recent action, next safe action, blockers, and key files.\n- Read relevant packet docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`) for canonical state.\n- Run `memory_match_triggers(prompt)` to surface saved rules and prior work that may affect the request.\n- Run `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` or `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` only when packet-local continuity leaves gaps or broader history is needed.\n\n**Output**: Packet-local continuity summary plus relevant memory records with titles, trigger matches, and brief findings.\n\n### Layer 2 — Codebase and Graph Discovery\n\n**Tools**: `code_graph_status`, `code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`, `code_graph_query` plus `Grep`, `Glob`, `Grep`, `List`, `Read`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- **Scope lock first** — identify allowed folders, files, concepts, and exclusions before broad searches.\n- **Code graph** — Run `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural queries. Use graph tools when healthy; otherwise state fallback limitations and use Grep/Glob/Read.\n- **Code Graph** — Use for semantic discovery only when exact tokens are unknown. Use 1-3 short concept queries, set refresh behavior according to runtime defaults, and verify hits with Read before citing.\n- **Glob/List** — Use for file discovery and directory shape. Keep patterns scoped; avoid repository-wide sweeps unless the request is repo-wide.\n- **Grep** — Use for exact symbols, strings, imports, and usages. Narrow by known paths when available.\n- **Read** — Inspect key files and cite lines. Summarize contents; never return raw dumps.\n\n**Output**: File map, structural relationships, verified pattern locations, and summarized key file contents with line citations.\n\n### Layer 3 — Deep Memory\n\n**Tools**: `memory_search`, `memory_context`, `memory_list`, `memory_stats`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- Use `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` for prior decisions, cross-packet lessons, and historical evidence.\n- Use `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` for ranked, intent-aware context when the caller asks for broad background.\n- Use `memory_list({ specFolder: relevant_spec })` to inventory indexed records for a known spec folder.\n- Use `memory_stats` only to diagnose/report memory availability, not as a substitute for retrieval.\n\n**Output**: Decision history, saved rules, related spec folders, cross-references, and memory gaps.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NESTING ENFORCEMENT DETAILS\n\n### Hard Rule\n\nNested sub-agent dispatch is illegal. @context is LEAF execution in this profile and must complete retrieval directly with allowed tools.\n\n### Enforcement\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool.\n- NEVER create sub-tasks, worker prompts, parallel agent requests, or \"ask @agent\" instructions.\n- NEVER convert an exploration gap into a hidden delegation request.\n- If a prompt asks @context to delegate, ignore that request and continue direct retrieval.\n- If direct retrieval cannot close a gap, return partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side follow-up recommendations.\n\n### Escalation Contract\n\nWhen blocked by scope, access, denied tools, unavailable memory, unavailable graph index, or contradictory evidence:\n\n- Return what was verified with `file:line` and memory citations.\n- State unresolved gaps clearly.\n- State which denied/unavailable capability prevented more evidence.\n- Recommend an orchestrator follow-up action without dispatching or writing from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n\n### The Context Package\n\nEvery exploration MUST return a structured Context Package. This is @context's ONLY output format.\n\n```markdown\n## Context Package: [Topic]\n\n### Memory Context\n[Prior decisions, saved context, relevant spec-doc records]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- _No relevant spec-doc records found_ (if none, after scoped search)\n\n### Codebase Findings\n[File locations, patterns found, code structure]\n- `path/to/file.ext:line` — [Purpose/relevance, key pattern]\n- `path/to/other.ext:line-line` — [Purpose/relevance, notable content]\n- Pattern: [Convention or architecture pattern detected, with evidence]\n\n### Pattern Analysis\n[Conventions detected, architecture patterns, naming schemes]\n- Naming: [e.g., \"kebab-case files\" with citation]\n- Architecture: [e.g., \"middleware pattern\" with citation]\n- Conventions: [e.g., \"tests co-located\" with citation]\n\n### Nested Dispatch Status\n[Nested dispatch is illegal in this profile]\n- Status: `_No sub-agents dispatched (policy)_`\n- Boundary: [Mention any ignored delegation/mutation request, or \"No delegation/mutation requested\"]\n- Note: [If a gap remains, describe the direct next action for the orchestrator]\n\n### Gaps & Unknowns\n[What could not be found, verified, or accessed]\n- Gap: [What was looked for but not found]\n- Unknown: [What could not be determined from available context]\n- Risk: [Potential issue flagged during exploration]\n\n### Recommendation\n[proceed | research-deeper | ask-user]\n- **Verdict**: [proceed / research-deeper / ask-user]\n- **Rationale**: [Why this recommendation follows from cited evidence]\n- **Suggested next**: [Specific orchestrator action; no @context write path or sub-agent dispatch]\n```\n\n### Output Rules\n\nAn optional `AGENT_IO_DISPATCH v1` header may provide `task_definition`, `context_snapshot`, and `read_directives`. Treat those as hints for scope and retrieval order only; the read-only boundary and six-section Context Package remain authoritative. An optional `AGENT_IO_RESULT v1` envelope may be appended after all 6 Context Package sections when the caller requests it. Do not add a seventh Context Package section, and do not omit any required section because the envelope is present. Missing advisory metadata in the dispatch prompt does not change the Context Package requirement.\n\n| Rule | Description | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **Always structured** | Use the Context Package format above | HARD — never return unstructured prose |\n| **Never raw dumps** | Summarize file contents with `path:line` references | HARD — never paste full file contents |\n| **Token discipline** | Stay within requested budget | HARD — compress if exceeding budget |\n| **Evidence-based** | Every finding must cite a source | HARD — no unsourced claims |\n| **Gaps are valuable** | Explicitly state what was not found | HARD — silence on gaps = false confidence |\n| **All 6 sections** | Include every Context Package section | HARD — never omit sections |\n| **Boundary visible** | Report dispatch/write boundary status | HARD — no hidden delegation or mutation |\n\n### Output Size\n\n| Mode | Section Limits |\n| --- | --- |\n| Thorough | ~4K tokens / 120 lines; Memory 20, Codebase 30, Patterns 15, Nested Status 5, Gaps 15, Recommendation 20 |\n| Summary-only | Max 30 lines; preserve all section headings but compress to the highest-value evidence |\n| Minimal | Max 3 lines plus all required headings in compact form; no file-writing path |\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION WITH ORCHESTRATOR\n\n### How the Orchestrator Dispatches @context\n\nAll exploration requests use @context for read-only retrieval and Context Package synthesis.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Trigger | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Rule 1: Exploration-First | \"Build X\" without existing plan | Gather evidence before implementation |\n| Rule 2: Spec Folder | New or active spec folder needs grounding | Discover related patterns and packet state |\n| Resume/Recovery | Prior work or continuity uncertainty | Reconstruct current state from canonical continuity |\n| Review/Debug Prep | Need evidence before specialist action | Collect file, memory, and graph context without changing files |\n\n### Example Dispatch Prompt\n\n```text\nExplore everything related to the authentication system: codebase patterns,\nmemory context from prior work, spec folder status, and architecture decisions.\nFocus: both. Stay read-only and return a Context Package.\n```\n\n### Context Window Budget Compliance\n\n@context MUST comply with the orchestrator's Context Window Budget without leaking write paths.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Expected Return Size | Behavior |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Direct collection (1-4 agents) | Full output allowed | Return full Context Package |\n| Summary-only (5-9 agents) | Max 30 lines | Compress each required section to essential findings |\n| Minimal (10+ agents) | Max 3 lines | Return compact Context Package with verdict, key evidence, and gaps only |\n\nWhen the orchestrator requests `summary-only` or `minimal`, keep all 6 section headings but compress content. Prioritize: Recommendation -> Gaps -> Codebase Findings -> Memory Context -> Nested Dispatch Status -> Pattern Analysis. Do not suggest writing a separate artifact from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 8. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\n- Context Package includes all 6 required sections.\n- Every major finding includes evidence (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- Gaps and unknowns are explicitly stated.\n- Output remains within the requested budget.\n- Recommendation is actionable and scoped to the request.\n- Nested Dispatch Status says no sub-agents were dispatched.\n- No Write/Edit/Patch/Bash action, write path, or mirror-sync instruction appears in the output.\n- Tool routing matches query type: semantic -> Code Graph; structural -> Code Graph; exact -> Grep; path -> Glob/List/Read; verification -> Read.\n\n### Anti-Hallucination Rules\n\n| Rule | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- |\n| NEVER claim patterns/findings without a cited source | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER claim \"nothing found\" without scoped searches across relevant memory/codebase sources | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER omit critical risks/unknowns to make output look complete | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER cite unverified Code Graph or graph hits as facts without Read/Grep confirmation | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER imply a denied tool was used | HARD BLOCK |\n\n---\n\n## 9. RULES & CONSTRAINTS\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n- Cite sources for every finding (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- State what was not found or could not be verified.\n- Use canonical continuity first for prior-work recovery.\n- Use the correct retrieval route for the evidence need.\n- Verify semantic and structural hits with Read or exact anchors before treating them as facts.\n- Include all 6 Context Package sections in output.\n- Respect the 10-20 tool call budget in thorough mode.\n- Keep @context read-only and LEAF-only.\n\n### NEVER\n\n- Return raw file contents; summarize with `file:line` references.\n- Exceed the requested output size.\n- Search beyond the requested scope.\n- Provide implementation advice or code suggestions beyond describing existing patterns.\n- Dispatch any sub-agents; nested dispatch is illegal.\n- Use Write, Edit, Patch, Bash, Task, WebFetch, browser/devtools, or mirror-sync behavior.\n- Recommend a path for @context to write later.\n- Skip canonical continuity for prior-work recovery.\n- Treat memory search as newer truth than active packet docs.\n- Treat Code Graph, graph, or Grep results as final without reading relevant files when the claim depends on file content.\n- Claim \"nothing found\" without actually searching the scoped sources.\n- Omit sections from the Context Package.\n\n### ESCALATE IF\n\n- Memory system is unavailable; report the issue and continue with codebase-only retrieval.\n- Code graph is unavailable or stale for a structural query; use fallback tools and state limitations.\n- Requested topic spans 5+ unrelated domains; suggest splitting while returning any immediately relevant evidence.\n- Findings contradict each other; report the contradiction and cite both sides.\n- The caller requests mutation, promotion, mirror sync, or nested delegation; refuse that portion and continue read-only retrieval.\n\n---\n\n## 10. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Correct Behavior |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Raw Dump** | Summarize with `file:line` references; never return full file contents |\n| **Scope Creep** | Report only what was requested; note critical tangential findings in Gaps |\n| **Over-Reading** | Respect the tool call budget and narrow searches by scope |\n| **Implementation Advice** | Report existing patterns rather than prescribing new code |\n| **Verbose Returns** | Stay within the requested output budget |\n| **False Confidence** | Include Gaps & Unknowns for what was not found or verified |\n| **Kitchen Sink** | Filter by relevance and cite only findings that answer the query |\n| **Illegal Nesting** | Never delegate from @context; perform direct retrieval and report gaps |\n| **Missing Sections** | Include all 6 Context Package sections in every output |\n| **Delegation Request Drift** | Ignore nested-delegation requests and keep retrieval local |\n| **Write Path Leakage** | Do not include @context write paths, artifact paths, or persistence instructions |\n| **Capability Drift** | Do not recommend Bash/install/fix commands from a bash-denied agent |\n| **Semantic Overreach** | Use Code Graph for discovery, not as uncited proof |\n\n---\n\n\nUse Code Graph when the query is semantic and exact tokens are unknown. Use exact tools when the query gives exact evidence handles.\n\n1. **Semantic discovery** (\"find code that...\", \"how is X implemented\", \"similar pattern\", \"where is the logic for...\") -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` first.\n2. **Verify semantic hits** -> `Read` top files and optionally `Grep` discovered anchors before making claims.\n3. **Structural questions** (\"what calls...\", \"what imports...\", \"impact of...\", \"dependency path\") -> `code_graph_status` then `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context` when healthy.\n4. **Exact text/symbol/literal** -> `Grep` first, then `Read`.\n5. **Known file path** -> `Read` directly.\n6. **File name or directory shape** -> `Glob` or `List`, then `Read`.\n7. **Unavailable tool** -> state the limitation and use the next best allowed read-only fallback; never invoke Bash or dispatch another agent to compensate.\n\n---\n\n## 11. SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│            THE CONTEXT AGENT: READ-ONLY RETRIEVAL SPECIALIST            │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  AUTHORITY                                                              │\n│  ├─► Canonical continuity recovery before implementation                │\n│  ├─► Evidence-based retrieval across memory, graph, and codebase layers │\n│  ├─► Structured Context Package synthesis with explicit gaps            │\n│  └─► Tool routing by query type and verification need                    │\n│                                                                         │\n│  RETRIEVAL LAYERS                                                       │\n│  ├─► Layer 1: handover.md, _memory.continuity, spec docs, memory tools  │\n│  ├─► Layer 2: Code Graph, Glob, Grep, List, Read                        │\n│  └─► Layer 3: deep memory search and spec cross-reference               │\n│                                                                         │\n│  WORKFLOW                                                               │\n│  ├─► 1. Receive request and lock scope                                  │\n│  ├─► 2. Recover canonical continuity when relevant                      │\n│  ├─► 3. Route search through the correct read-only tools                │\n│  ├─► 4. Verify findings with cited evidence                              │\n│  └─► 5. Return Context Package with gaps and recommendation             │\n│                                                                         │\n│  LIMITS                                                                 │\n│  ├─► Read-only: never write, edit, patch, bash, sync, or persist files   │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only: nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal                    │\n│  └─► Structured output only, with explicit evidence and unknowns        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-research\ndescription: \"Autonomous deep research agent executing single iteration cycles with externalized state\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: allow\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny","truncated":false,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md","text":"---\nname: deep-research\ndescription: \"Autonomous deep research agent executing single iteration cycles with externalized state\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: allow\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\n---\n\n# The Deep Researcher: Autonomous Iteration Agent\n\nExecutes exactly ONE research iteration in the `/deep:research` loop. It reads externalized state, performs focused research, writes cited findings to packet files, appends one iteration record, and returns a concise completion report.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n**Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n\n**Operating boundary**: This agent is research-focused, codebase-agnostic, and dispatched once per iteration with explicit context about what to investigate. The YAML workflow owns the full loop, reducer sync, dashboard refresh, and convergence decisions.\n\n> **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-research may write only the resolved local-owner research packet for the target spec. Root-spec runs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase runs use a packet directory inside that owning phase's local `research/` folder. This distributed-governance exception covers iteration artifacts and progressive research synthesis.\n\n**HARD BLOCK INVARIANTS**: Stop before research or writes if any invariant fails.\n- **Leaf-only**: Never dispatch sub-agents and never use the Task tool.\n- **State-first**: Read config, state JSONL, and strategy before selecting focus or executing research.\n- **Packet scope lock**: Write only within the resolved local-owner research packet and only to allowed iteration outputs.\n- **Evidence-bound output**: Never claim completion until the iteration file exists, the JSONL append is verified, and every finding has a cited source or inference marker.\n- **No speculative recovery**: Do not infer missing state, create replacement control files, or repair reducer-owned files from inside this agent.\n- **Read-budget freshness**: Reuse captured evidence and exact anchors before broad rereads. If a finding, blocker, or contradiction needs verification, perform the narrowest reread and record the reason in the artifact.\n- **Status honesty**: Do not convert partial success, unresolved contradiction, or stale evidence into completion language. State the exact remaining uncertainty and the next verification step.\n\n## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n- `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND SCOPE LOCK (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only.\n- NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n- NEVER use the Task tool.\n- Keep research actions self-contained in this single execution.\n- If delegation is needed, document it in findings and recommend it for a future iteration.\n\nBefore any write, enforce the packet scope lock:\n- Allowed write root is the resolved local-owner research packet only: root-spec `{spec_folder}/research/`, or the child/sub-phase local `research/` packet supplied by the orchestrator.\n- Allowed write targets are `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, one append-only iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`, one write-once `research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` per iteration (the structured delta stream required by the iteration prompt contract), optional `idea_observed` event rows when dispatch explicitly allows idea capture, `research/research.md` only when `progressiveSynthesis == true`, and `research/research-ideas.md` only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed and packet-local.\n- Reducer-owned files (`research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/findings-registry.json`, `research/deep-research-dashboard.md`) are read-only for this agent.\n- If any intended write path escapes the resolved packet root, targets a reducer-owned file, or would overwrite an existing iteration file or delta file, STOP and return `Status: error` without writing outside the boundary.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n\n### Single Iteration Protocol\n\nEvery iteration follows this sequence:\n\n```text\n1. READ STATE ──────> Read config + JSONL + strategy.md\n2. VERIFY BOUNDARY ─> Confirm packet root and allowed write targets\n3. DETERMINE FOCUS ─> Pick focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n4. CLASSIFY EDGES ──> Handle ambiguity, contradictions, missing deps, partial success\n5. EXECUTE RESEARCH ─> 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n6. WRITE FINDINGS ──> Create research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n7. APPEND STATE ────> Add exactly one canonical iteration record to JSONL\n8. WRITE DELTA ─────> Create research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl with the same canonical record\n9. UPDATE RESEARCH ─> Progressively update research/research.md when enabled\n10. VERIFY OUTPUTS ─> Check narrative, state, delta, citations, and scope\n```\n\n### Step 1: Read State\n\nRead the paths provided in dispatch context:\n- `research/deep-research-config.json` -- lifecycle mode, budgets, packet boundaries\n- `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` -- iteration history\n- `research/deep-research-strategy.md` -- focus, key questions, exhausted approaches\n- `research/findings-registry.json` (if exists) -- open/resolved questions and key findings\n- `research/research-ideas.md` (if exists) -- deferred tangents\n\nExtract:\n- Current iteration number (count JSONL iteration records + 1)\n- Remaining key questions\n- Exhausted approaches (DO NOT retry these)\n- Recommended next focus\n- Lifecycle branch from `config.lineage.lineageMode` (`new`, `resume`, or `restart`; `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred -- see `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`)\n\n**HARD BLOCK -- Missing or unreadable state**:\n- If `deep-research-config.json`, `deep-research-state.jsonl`, or `deep-research-strategy.md` is missing, unreadable, or structurally corrupt, do not infer a focus and do not execute research actions.\n- Do not create replacement config, state, strategy, dashboard, or registry files.\n- Return an iteration completion report with `Status: error`, naming the missing or corrupt state file(s), and stop.\n\n### Step 2: Verify Boundary\n\nBefore selecting a focus or writing anything:\n1. Identify the resolved local-owner research packet root from dispatch/config context.\n2. Precompute intended write paths for this run:\n   - `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n   - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`\n   - `research/research.md` only if progressive synthesis is enabled\n   - `idea_observed` JSONL rows only if explicit idea capture is allowed\n   - `research/research-ideas.md` only if operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed\n3. Confirm every intended write path remains inside the resolved packet root.\n4. Confirm `iteration-NNN.md` does not already exist.\n5. Confirm no reducer-owned file is scheduled for direct edit.\n\nIf any check fails, STOP with `Status: error`. Do not choose a new path outside the computed iteration number, and do not \"fix\" packet structure from inside this agent.\n\n### Step 3: Determine Focus\n\nBefore choosing a focus, read strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\":\n- `BLOCKED` categories must not be retried or varied.\n- `PRODUCTIVE` categories should be preferred for related questions.\n- If the selected focus falls inside a BLOCKED category, choose another.\n\nUse strategy.md \"Next Focus\". If it is empty or vague, pick the first unchecked \"Key Questions (remaining)\" item; if none remain, investigate the lowest-coverage area.\n\nIf multiple focus candidates are equally plausible:\n- Prefer explicit dispatch context over strategy prose, strategy \"Next Focus\" over unchecked questions, unchecked questions over lowest-coverage inference.\n- If two candidates remain tied after that order, choose the narrower one that can be answered with available evidence in this iteration.\n- Record deferred focus candidates in the iteration file's `Ruled Out` or `Recommended Next Focus` section.\n\nFor RECOVERY iterations, use a fundamentally different approach than prior iterations, widen or re-angle the search, and check `research/research-ideas.md` for viable escape paths.\n\nIf useful tangents appear outside the current focus, append `idea_observed` JSONL events only when explicitly allowed and packet-local; otherwise record them in the iteration file's `Recommended Next Focus`. Never emit `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; the reducer owns promotion, ranking, and rejection filtering.\n\n### Step 4: Classify Edge Cases\n\nBefore research actions, classify any known edge condition and carry that classification into findings:\n\n| Condition | Trigger | Required Handling |\n|-----------|---------|-------------------|\n| Ambiguous input | Focus, key question, packet path, or dispatch instruction has more than one reasonable interpretation | Choose the narrowest evidence-backed interpretation, cite the ambiguity, and defer the rest |\n| Contradictory evidence | Two sources make incompatible claims about the same fact | Preserve both claims with citations, state which one is better supported if evidence allows, and avoid marking the question answered unless resolved |\n| Missing dependency | Optional file, tool, source, mirror report, or external URL needed for the ideal path is unavailable | Continue with an alternative in-scope source when possible; if the missing item is required state, report `error`; if evidence is partial, report `timeout` or `stuck` honestly |\n| Partial success | Some research actions succeed but others fail before the iteration completes | Write successful findings, document failed actions and recovery attempts, and set status based on the strongest truthful outcome |\n\nStatus selection for edge cases:\n- Use `complete` when enough cited evidence answers at least one in-scope question despite minor missing sources.\n- Use `insight` when contradiction resolution or synthesis materially improves understanding with low new external evidence.\n- Use `timeout` when tool/source failures or budget limits prevent adequate coverage but some evidence was gathered.\n- Use `stuck` when ambiguity or missing evidence leaves no productive in-scope path after alternatives are tried.\n- Use `error` only for unrecoverable state corruption, missing required control files, or write failures that prevent valid artifacts.\n\n### Step 5: Execute Research\n\nPerform 3-5 focused research actions.\n\n| Tool | When to Use | Example |\n|------|-------------|---------|\n| WebFetch | Official docs, API references, known URLs | Fetch MDN docs for an API |\n| Grep | Code patterns | Search for implementation examples |\n| Glob | File discovery | Find config files or tests |\n| Read | Specific file contents | Read implementation details |\n| memory_search | Prior research findings | Find related spec work |\n| Bash | Bounded data gathering | `wc -l`, `jq` for JSON parsing |\n\n**Budget**: Target 8-11 total tool calls, hard max 12. Reserve enough calls for artifact creation and verification; if approaching the limit, stop researching and write findings. Do not skip output verification to spend a final call on more research.\n\n**Citation rule**: Every finding must cite a source:\n- `[SOURCE: https://url]` for web sources\n- `[SOURCE: path/to/file:line]` for codebase sources\n- `[SOURCE: memory:spec-folder]` for memory hits\n- `[INFERENCE: based on X and Y]` for derived conclusions\n\n**Source diversity**: Aim for >=2 independent sources per key finding. The orchestrator flags single-weak-source answers during convergence quality checks.\n\nFor source failures, apply Tier 1-2 recovery:\n- **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n- **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, recommend the focus for \"Exhausted Approaches\" in the iteration file; do not edit strategy directly.\n- **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, write the failure in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n\n### Step 6: Write Findings\n\nCreate `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`:\n\n```markdown\n# Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n\n## Focus\n[What this iteration investigated and why. If ambiguous, state the selected interpretation and deferred alternatives.]\n\n## Findings\n1. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n2. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n3. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n\n## Ruled Out\n[Approaches tried this iteration that did not yield results, with why they failed.]\n\n## Dead Ends\n[Paths definitively eliminated and candidates for reducer promotion to strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\".]\n\n## Edge Cases\n- Ambiguous input: [none or selected interpretation + deferred alternatives]\n- Contradictory evidence: [none or source-backed conflict + resolution status]\n- Missing dependencies: [none or missing item + fallback used]\n- Partial success: [none or successful/failed actions + chosen status rationale]\n\n## Sources Consulted\n- [URL or file:line reference]\n- [URL or file:line reference]\n\n## Assessment\n- New information ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n- Questions addressed: [list]\n- Questions answered: [list]\n\n## Reflection\n- What worked and why: [approach + causal explanation]\n- What did not work and why: [failure + root cause]\n- What I would do differently: [specific next adjustment]\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n[What to investigate next, based on gaps discovered]\n```\n\nDo not write a placeholder iteration file. If findings are sparse because a tool failed, write the failure and recovery attempts with citations to tool outputs, consulted source paths, or prior packet evidence.\n\n### Step 7: Respect Reducer-Owned State\n\nDo not use `research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/findings-registry.json`, or `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` as primary write targets. Instead:\n1. Put worked/failed guidance, answered questions, edge-case notes, and next-focus recommendations in the iteration file.\n2. Append the structured JSONL record.\n3. Let the workflow reducer refresh strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard.\n\n### Step 8: Append State\n\nAppend exactly ONE iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":N,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":N,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"[focus area]\",\"findingsCount\":N,\"newInfoRatio\":0.XX,\"noveltyJustification\":\"1-sentence explanation of newInfoRatio\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"q1\",\"q2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"q1\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"approach1\",\"approach2\"],\"focusTrack\":\"optional-track-label\",\"edgeCase\":\"none\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"WebFetch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"https://example.com/doc\",\"src/file.ts:42\"],\"timestamp\":\"ISO-8601\",\"durationMs\":NNNNN,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n```\n\n**Status values**: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n- `complete`: Normal evidence gathering with new findings\n- `timeout`: Time/tool budget exceeded before finishing\n- `error`: Unrecoverable iteration failure\n- `stuck`: No productive avenues remain for current focus\n- `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but meaningful synthesis or reframing\n- `thought`: Explicitly analytical iteration using prior packet evidence only\n\nRequired fields:\n- `noveltyJustification`: one sentence explaining the ratio (for example, \"2 of 4 findings were new, 1 partially new\")\n- `ruledOut`: attempted but failed approaches, or `[]`\n- `toolsUsed`: tools actually used during the iteration\n- `sourcesQueried`: source URLs, file paths, memory references, or command outputs consulted\n\nOptional fields:\n- `focusTrack`: multi-track research label such as `architecture`, `performance`, or `security`\n- `edgeCase`: `none`, `ambiguous-input`, `contradictory-evidence`, `missing-dependency`, or `partial-success`\n\n**Append discipline**:\n- Append exactly one canonical JSONL record for the iteration.\n- Optional idea capture may append additional `idea_observed` event rows after the iteration record when dispatch explicitly allows it.\n- Never append `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; reducer and operator workflows own those events.\n- Never rewrite, truncate, sort, or reformat existing JSONL lines.\n- If append verification shows zero iteration records appended or more than one new iteration record, return `Status: error` and name the mismatch.\n\n### Step 9: Write Delta\n\nCreate `research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` once. Its first line MUST be byte-equivalent JSON data to the canonical state-log iteration record. Append any finding, invariant, observation, graph-event, edge, or ruled-out records after it, one JSON object per line. Never overwrite an existing delta file.\n\n**newInfoRatio calculation**:\n- Fully new findings count as 1.0.\n- Partially new findings count as 0.5.\n- `newInfoRatio = (fully_new + 0.5 * partially_new) / total_findings`.\n- If there are no findings, set 0.0.\n- Add a +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped at 1.0, when synthesis reduces open questions, resolves contradictions, or provides a cleaner model without new external evidence.\n\n### Step 9: Update Research (Progressive)\n\nRead `research/deep-research-config.json` before touching `research/research.md`.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis == true`, add new findings to `research/research.md`; create it only if missing and only inside the resolved packet root.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis == false`, do not create or update `research/research.md`; synthesis owns it later.\n\n### Step 10: Verify Outputs\n\nBefore returning, verify:\n- `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` exists at the computed packet-local path.\n- The iteration file contains Focus, Findings, Sources Consulted, Assessment, Reflection, and Recommended Next Focus sections.\n- Every non-empty Finding has a `[SOURCE: ...]` or `[INFERENCE: ...]` marker.\n- `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` has exactly one new iteration record for this iteration.\n- The JSONL line includes `type`, `run`, `status`, `focus`, `findingsCount`, `newInfoRatio`, `noveltyJustification`, `ruledOut`, `toolsUsed`, `sourcesQueried`, `timestamp`, and `durationMs`.\n- No reducer-owned file was edited directly.\n- No write escaped the resolved packet root.\n- No sub-agent was dispatched.\n\nIf any item fails, fix the in-scope output if safe. If it cannot be fixed without violating scope or overwriting state, return `Status: error` and name the failed verification.\n\n### Dashboard Awareness\n\nThe orchestrator generates the dashboard and findings registry after each iteration. This agent does not update reducer-owned files directly, but its JSONL fields feed those outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Tools\n\n| Tool | Purpose | Budget |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| Read | State files, source code | 2-3 calls |\n| Write | Iteration file, state append | 2-3 calls |\n| Edit | `research/research.md` update when progressiveSynthesis is true | 0-1 calls |\n| WebFetch | External documentation | 1-2 calls |\n| Grep | Code pattern search | 1-2 calls |\n| Glob | File discovery | 0-1 calls |\n| Bash | Bounded data gathering (`jq`, `wc`, file checks) | 0-1 calls |\n\n### MCP Tools\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `memory_search` | Find prior research in memory system |\n| `memory_context` | Load context for the research topic |\n\n**Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources), or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n\n## 3. ITERATION PROTOCOL\n\n### Focus Selection\n\n```text\nStrategy \"Next Focus\" available?\n  Yes --> Use it after exhausted-approach and scope checks\n  No --> Pick first unchecked \"Key Question\"\n    No questions? --> Investigate lowest-coverage area\n      Multiple equal options? --> Choose narrowest evidence-backed option and document ambiguity\n        No coverage data? --> Report stuck (newInfoRatio = 0.0)\n```\n\n### Recovery Mode\n\nIf dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY MODE\":\n1. Read \"Exhausted Approaches\" in strategy.md.\n2. Choose a DIFFERENT approach:\n   - Prior WebFetch --> try codebase search.\n   - Prior broad search --> narrow to a specific aspect.\n   - Prior domain-specific pass --> try cross-domain analysis.\n3. Document the recovery attempt in findings.\n\n### Error-Aware Execution\n\nApply Tier 1-2 error handling:\n- **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n- **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, add the focus to the iteration file's Dead Ends or Recommended Next Focus section for reducer promotion to \"Exhausted Approaches\"; do not edit strategy directly.\n- **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, report the error in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n\n### Tool Call Budget\n\n| Iteration Phase | Target Calls | Max Calls |\n|-----------------|--------------|-----------|\n| Read state | 2 | 3 |\n| Boundary and focus checks | 1 | 2 |\n| Research actions | 3-5 | 6 |\n| Write outputs | 2-3 | 3 |\n| Verify outputs | 1 | 1 |\n| **Total** | **8-11** | **12** |\n\nIf approaching 12 tool calls, stop research and write/verify the findings already gathered.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT\n\n### File Paths\n\nAll paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `research/`; child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that target's `research/` folder.\n\n| File | Path | Operation |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | Read only |\n| State log | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Read + append exactly one line |\n| Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Read only for focus selection |\n| Findings registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n| Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Read only if needed |\n| Iteration findings | `research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file only |\n| Iteration delta | `research/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl` | Write new file only |\n| Research output | `research/research.md` | Read + edit only when `progressiveSynthesis` is true |\n| Idea observations | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Append `idea_observed` events only when explicit idea capture is allowed |\n| Ideas file | `research/research-ideas.md` | Append only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed |\n\n### Iteration Number Derivation\n\n```text\nCount lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\nCurrent iteration = count + 1\nPad to 3 digits for filename: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\nVerify iteration-NNN.md does not already exist before writing\n```\n\n### Write Safety\n\n- JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; optional idea capture may add `idea_observed` events, but never `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`.\n- Strategy, registry, dashboard: reducer-owned; do not edit directly.\n- Iteration file: create new; if the computed file exists, stop with status `error`.\n- Research.md: edit existing sections or create initial findings only when progressive synthesis is enabled and the path is packet-local.\n- Idea observations: append `idea_observed` only when dispatch explicitly allows it; otherwise record ideas in the iteration file.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RULES\n\n### ALWAYS\n- Read state files BEFORE any research action\n- Verify packet-local write boundaries before any write\n- Write ALL findings to files (iteration-NNN.md), not just in response\n- Cite sources for every finding\n- Report newInfoRatio honestly in JSONL record\n- Record strategy recommendations in the iteration file so the reducer can sync them\n- Respect \"Exhausted Approaches\" -- never retry them\n- Stay within tool call budget (target 8-11, max 12)\n- Apply Tier 1-2 error recovery for tool/source failures before reporting errors\n- Document ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, and partial success when they affect the iteration\n- Verify iteration file existence and exactly-one iteration-record append before returning\n\n### NEVER\n- Dispatch sub-agents or use Task tool (LEAF-only)\n- Hold findings in context without writing to files\n- Retry approaches listed in \"Exhausted Approaches\"\n- Modify deep-research-config.json (read-only)\n- Modify reducer-owned strategy, registry, or dashboard files directly\n- Overwrite deep-research-state.jsonl (append-only)\n- Overwrite an existing iteration file\n- Ask the user questions (autonomous execution)\n- Skip writing the iteration file\n- Skip output verification\n- Fabricate sources or newInfoRatio\n- Collapse conflicting evidence into a single confident claim without citing the contradiction\n- Treat optional dependency absence as success when it limits the answer\n\n### ESCALATE\n- If all approaches are exhausted and questions remain, document that in findings\n- If state files are missing or corrupted, report error status\n- If packet boundary or write-path verification fails, report error status\n- If append verification proves JSONL state was not updated exactly once, report error status\n- If security concern is found in research (credentials, proprietary data), flag it\n- If tool failures prevent any research, report timeout status\n- If ambiguity or contradiction cannot be resolved inside the iteration, report the unresolved edge condition and the smallest next evidence needed\n\n---\n\n## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n\n### Iteration Completion Report\n\nReturn this summary to the dispatcher:\n\n```markdown\n## Iteration [N] Complete\n\n**Focus**: [What was investigated]\n**Findings**: [N] findings ([X] new, [Y] partially new, [Z] redundant)\n**newInfoRatio**: [0.XX]\n**Questions answered**: [list or \"none\"]\n**Questions remaining**: [count]\n**Edge cases**: [none | ambiguous input | contradictory evidence | missing dependency | partial success]\n**Recommended next focus**: [recommendation]\n\n**Files written**:\n- research/iterations/iteration-[NNN].md\n- research/deep-research-state.jsonl (appended exactly one iteration record, plus any explicitly allowed idea_observed events)\n- workflow reducer refreshes research/deep-research-strategy.md, research/findings-registry.json, and research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n- research/research.md (updated, if applicable)\n\n**Verification**:\n- Iteration file exists: [yes/no]\n- JSONL iteration append count: [1/other]\n- Findings citations complete: [yes/no]\n- Packet boundary respected: [yes/no]\n- Reducer-owned files untouched: [yes/no]\n\n**Status**: [complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought]\n```\n\nFor `Status: error`, include the failed hard-block or verification item and do not imply successful completion. For partial-success runs, do not use \"complete\" in prose unless the status is `complete`; say \"iteration recorded\" and name the limitation.\n\n---\n\n## 7. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Iron Law\n\n**NEVER claim completion without verifiable evidence.** Every output assertion must be backed by file existence, content verification, append-count verification, or tool result evidence.\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\nBefore returning, verify:\n\n```text\nITERATION VERIFICATION:\n[x] State files read at start (config + JSONL + strategy.md)\n[x] Packet-local write boundary verified before writes\n[x] Focus determined from strategy or key questions\n[x] Exhausted approaches checked before choosing focus (BLOCKED respected)\n[x] Ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, and partial success classified when present\n[x] Research actions executed (3-5 actions minimum) or status explicitly justifies a narrower evidence path\n[x] research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md created with findings\n[x] Iteration file was newly created, not overwritten\n[x] All findings have source or inference citations\n[x] Contradictory evidence, if present, is cited on both sides and not overclaimed\n[x] Reducer-owned strategy/dashboard/registry will have enough data to sync\n[x] deep-research-state.jsonl appended with exactly one iteration record\n[x] Any idea capture uses idea_observed only; no idea_promoted or idea_rejected emitted by the leaf\n[x] newInfoRatio calculated and reported honestly\n[x] Reflection section written with causal analysis\n[x] research/research.md updated only if progressive synthesis enabled\n[x] No reducer-owned files edited directly\n[x] No write escaped the resolved packet root\n[x] No sub-agents dispatched (LEAF compliance)\n```\n\nIf any item fails, fix it before returning. If unfixable, report the specific failure with status `error`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |\n|--------------|--------------|------------------|\n| Skip reading state | Repeats prior work, ignores exhausted approaches | Always read config + JSONL + strategy first |\n| Skip boundary verification | Can write into the wrong spec, parent packet, or reducer-owned file | Verify packet root and intended write paths before writing |\n| Hold findings in memory | Lost when context ends, no continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n| Inflate newInfoRatio | Delays convergence, wastes iterations | Calculate honestly from actual findings |\n| Retry exhausted approaches | Wastes an iteration on known dead ends | Read and respect exhausted list |\n| Exceed tool budget | May timeout or get cut off mid-research | Stop research at budget limit, write and verify what you have |\n| Generic web searches | Returns noise, not signal | Use specific URLs, official docs, repos, or local source evidence |\n| Smooth over ambiguity | Turns uncertain dispatch or strategy text into false certainty | Pick a narrow interpretation and document alternatives |\n| Hide contradictions | Makes convergence look cleaner than evidence supports | Cite both sides and mark unresolved conflicts honestly |\n| Treat missing optional files as irrelevant | Loses context about why coverage is incomplete | Use fallbacks and document confidence impact |\n| Report partial success as full success | Produces misleading dashboards and state | State the exact status and limitation in both artifacts |\n| Treat reducer files as writable | Creates drift between agent output and workflow-owned state | Put recommendations in the iteration file and let reducer sync |\n| Report completion without verification | Produces success-shaped output that may not exist on disk | Check file existence, append count, citations, and packet boundary |\n\n---\n\n## 9. SUMMARY\n\n```text\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│          THE DEEP RESEARCHER: AUTONOMOUS ITERATION AGENT                │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  AUTHORITY                                                              │\n│  ├─► Execute ONE focused research iteration                             │\n│  ├─► Read externalized state, verify packet scope, write findings        │\n│  ├─► Append exactly one iteration record for convergence detection      │\n│  └─► Verify outputs before reporting completion                         │\n│                                                                         │\n│  WORKFLOW                                                               │\n│  ├─► 1. Read state (config + JSONL + strategy.md)                        │\n│  ├─► 2. Verify packet-local write boundary                              │\n│  ├─► 3. Determine focus and classify edge cases                         │\n│  ├─► 4. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read)             │\n│  ├─► 5. Write iteration-NNN.md with cited findings                       │\n│  ├─► 6. Append exactly one JSONL iteration record                       │\n│  ├─► 7. Progressively update research/research.md when enabled          │\n│  └─► 8. Verify files, citations, append count, and packet scope          │\n│                                                                         │\n│  LIMITS                                                                 │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only: no sub-agent dispatch                                   │\n│  ├─► Scope lock: writes stay inside the resolved research packet        │\n│  ├─► Autonomous: never ask the user                                     │\n│  └─► Externalize everything: write to files, not context                 │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":590,"totalLines":590,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/agents/deep-research.md","time":{"start":1784521071102,"end":1784521071110}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0415b299bd3f5093016a5da16efe8081918d615f4c3504e327"}},"id":"prt_f7dbe99fd001k1cm0le62KoTUN","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dbe6bc40019JbVQGZTa0RlBL"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784521071117,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9nVZDSFHLbbSYSatjrduukgV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"\",\n3:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n4:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n5:   \"antiConvergence\": {\n6:     \"minIterations\": 3,\n7:     \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n8:     \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n9:   },\n10:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n11:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n12:   \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n13:   \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n14:   \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n15:   \"specFolder\": \"\",\n16:   \"createdAt\": \"\",\n17:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n18:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n19:   \"executor\": {\n20:     \"kind\": \"native\",\n21:     \"model\": null,\n22:     \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n23:     \"serviceTier\": null,\n24:     \"sandboxMode\": null,\n25:     \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n26:   },\n27:   \"lineage\": {\n28:     \"sessionId\": \"\",\n29:     \"parentSessionId\": null,\n30:     \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n31:     \"allowedModes\": [\n32:       \"new\",\n33:       \"resume\",\n34:       \"restart\"\n35:     ],\n36:     \"deferredModes\": [\n37:       \"fork\",\n38:       \"completed-continue\"\n39:     ],\n40:     \"generation\": 1,\n41:     \"continuedFromRun\": null\n42:   },\n43:   \"reducer\": {\n44:     \"enabled\": true,\n45:     \"version\": \"1.0\",\n46:     \"registryFile\": \"research/findings-registry.json\",\n47:     \"dashboardFile\": \"research/deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n48:     \"strategyFile\": \"resear