{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784522645236,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_HudZCrNNOfXpA5rIQk6EM3Dh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":75,"limit":20},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n75: - Which indexing and embedding automations materially improve with Rust? (iteration 1)\n76: - What measured p50/p95 query latency, vector dimension, eligible-row distribution, and query rate trigger the 10x or 100x migration gate? (iteration 1)\n77: - What are the measured production or replayed eligibility percentiles, active embedding dimensions, stage p50/p95 values, and query-rate distribution on the declared reference host? (iteration 2)\n78: - What are production arrival-rate percentiles and representative facet-selectivity percentiles after persistent opt-in? (iteration 3)\n79: - Which vector-search architecture, if any, unlocks meaningful capability once a published vector projection and representative trace exist? (iteration 3)\n80: - Which indexing and embedding automations become materially better with Rust? (iteration 3)\n81: \n82: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n83: \n84: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n85: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n86: Which indexing and embedding automations become materially better with Rust?\n87: \n88: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n89: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n90: \n91: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n92: - The current lexical lane runs as FTS5 SQL through `node:sqlite`; vector rows are loaded from SQLite and only cosine scoring/sorting occurs in JS. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/retrieval.mjs:200-249]\n93: - Weighted RRF is a deterministic map-and-sort over already-ranked candidate lists. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/retrieval.mjs:252-283]\n94: - Vector embedding work already has an incremental queue, retrieval-hash cache, bounded retries, and lexical fallback semantics. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/vectors.mjs:78-313]\n\n(Showing lines 75-94 of 112. Use offset=95 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- Which indexing and embedding automations materially improve with Rust? (iteration 1)\n- What measured p50/p95 query latency, vector dimension, eligible-row distribution, and query rate trigger the 10x or 100x migration gate? (iteration 1)\n- What are the measured production or replayed eligibility percentiles, active embedding dimensions, stage p50/p95 values, and query-rate distribution on the declared reference host? (iteration 2)\n- What are production arrival-rate percentiles and representative facet-selectivity percentiles after persistent opt-in? (iteration 3)\n- Which vector-search architecture, if any, unlocks meaningful capability once a published vector projection and representative trace exist? (iteration 3)\n- Which indexing and embedding automations become materially better with Rust? (iteration 3)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nWhich indexing and embedding automations become materially better with Rust?\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n- The current lexical lane runs as FTS5 SQL through `node:sqlite`; vector rows are loaded from SQLite and only cosine scoring/sorting occurs in JS. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/retrieval.mjs:200-249]\n- Weighted RRF is a deterministic map-and-sort over already-ranked candidate lists. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/retrieval.mjs:252-283]\n- Vector embedding work already has an incremental queue, retrieval-hash cache, bounded retries, and lexical fallback semantics. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/vectors.mjs:78-313]","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"- Which indexing and embedding automations materially improve with Rust? (iteration 1)\n- What measured p50/p95 query latency, vector dimension, eligible-row distribution, and query rate trigger the 10x or 100x migration gate? (iteration 1)\n- What are the measured production or replayed eligibility percentiles, active embedding dimensions, stage p50/p95 values, and query-rate distribution on the declared reference host? (iteration 2)\n- What are production arrival-rate percentiles and representative facet-selectivity percentiles after persistent opt-in? (iteration 3)\n- Which vector-search architecture, if any, unlocks meaningful capability once a published vector projection and representative trace exist? (iteration 3)\n- Which indexing and embedding automations become materially better with Rust? (iteration 3)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nWhich indexing and embedding automations become materially better with Rust?\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n- The current lexical lane runs as FTS5 SQL through `node:sqlite`; vector rows are loaded from SQLite and only cosine scoring/sorting occurs in JS. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/retrieval.mjs:200-249]\n- Weighted RRF is a deterministic map-and-sort over already-ranked candidate lists. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/retrieval.mjs:252-283]\n- Vector embedding work already has an incremental queue, retrieval-hash cache, bounded retries, and lexical fallback semantics. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/vectors.mjs:78-313]","lineStart":75,"lineEnd":94,"totalLines":112,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784522645230,"end":1784522645235}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0698b7feed7a2188016a5da7948eb08191802c0d90456d6565"}},"id":"prt_f7dd69c640013B1qU2BYX5nTpA","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","messageID":"msg_f7dd687b5001BjwUhvJnJ5s120"}}
