{"type":"text","timestamp":1784522908960,"sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","part":{"id":"prt_f7ddaa08a001DJwPPuYhF1nREM","messageID":"msg_f7dda90280012gZqDKFTLDxMqY","sessionID":"ses_082429307ffehbt81HPaprV8I0","type":"text","text":"Iterations 2-4 added two concrete gates: broad 100x queries exceed SQLite’s default host-parameter ceiling before ANN becomes the issue, and the existing queue/cache already handles most control-flow automation. Rust’s strongest automation case is therefore a long-lived local inference/indexing worker with model residency and parallel CPU stages, not replacing the current queue bookkeeping.","time":{"start":1784522907786,"end":1784522908958},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c88a7f3d8eccca1016a5da89bc32c8191b466a3407cc34878","phase":"commentary"}}}}
