ad}.md`,prompt,\"utf8\"); writeFirstRecordExecutor(`${a}/deep-research-state.jsonl`,executor,run); const env={...process.env,SPECKIT_CLI_DISPATCH_STACK:undefined,OPENCODE_SESSION_ID:undefined}; runAuditedExecutorCommand({command:\"opencode\",args:[\"run\",\"--model\",executor.model,\"--format\",\"json\",\"--dangerously-skip-permissions\",\"--pure\",\"--dir\",process.cwd(),`Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\\n\\n${prompt}`],cwd:process.cwd(),timeoutSeconds:executor.timeoutSeconds,stateLogPath:`${a}/deep-research-state.jsonl`,executor,iteration:run,input:\"\",guardContext:{env,ancestryCmdlines:[],statePaths:[]},receiptDir:`${a}/dispatch-receipts`,dispatchId:`research-i${run}-g1`,lineageId:\"sol-opencode\"}); writeFirstRecordExecutor(`${a}/deep-research-state.jsonl`,executor,run); const verified=spawnSync(\"node\",[\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs\",\"--loop-type\",\"research\",\"--artifact-dir\",a,\"--iteration\",String(run),\"--json\"],{cwd:process.cwd(),encoding:\"utf8\"}); process.stdout.write(verified.stdout||\"\"); process.stderr.write(verified.stderr||\"\"); if(verified.status!==0) process.exit(verified.status||1); const require=createRequire(path.resolve(\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/package.json\")), abs=path.resolve(a), seam=require(\"./lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs\"); seam.resolveArtifactRoot=()=>({rootDir:abs,subfolder:null,artifactDir:abs,artifactArchiveRoot:path.join(abs,\"_archive\")}); const {reduceResearchState}=require(\"../deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\"); const reduced=reduceResearchState(c.specFolder,{write:true,lenient:false}); console.log(JSON.stringify({reducedIteration:run,metrics:reduced.registry.metrics}));'","timeout":920000,"workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /Users/michelkerkmeester/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_f7df159cf001XkOGSKWIolTnCM\n\n{\"ok\":true,\"reason\":null,\"detail\":\"iteration 9 complete: narrative + route-proof + delta\"}\n[deep-research] detected 5 legacy-import question(s) in key-questions; append external questions to research/inbox.jsonl instead.\n{\"reducedIteration\":9,\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":9,\"openQuestions\":5,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\":34,\"keyFindings\":0,\"rejectedPatterns\":0,\"suppressedCandidates\":0,\"observedIdeas\":0,\"promotedIdeas\":0,\"suppressedIdeas\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.58,\"coverageBySources\":{\"code\":9,\"other\":5},\"completedPivots\":0,\"failedPivots\":0,\"pivotOverrides\":0}}\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\nn+\\n+The prior cross-system result remains intact: styles retrieval and Spec Kit Memory have different ranking policy, persistence, publication, and fallback contracts, while system-code-graph has no vector workload. A shared generic ranking platform would move policy into a lowest-common-denominator ABI and create coordinated release ownership without adding capability. Reuse should be limited to transport-neutral primitives inside a component already warranted by local inference, ANN, or measured build preprocessing; subsystem-specific scoring and fusion profiles remain local.\\n+\\n+### F3. The current retrieval test is a useful behavioral seed but not a release-grade parity oracle\\n+\\n+The existing weighted-RRF test confirms rank-only behavior, attribution keys, and deterministic ID ordering for two channels and two IDs, using semantic `deepEqual`. It does not pin serialized bytes, channel insertion-order permutations, duplicate IDs within a lane, zero or invalid weights, complete ties, Unicode ID ordering, negative zero, number spelling, omitted fields, error shapes, or all three channels. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/retrieval.test.mjs:18-31]\\n+\\n+Repository Rust rules require fixtures generated by the pinned TypeScript implementation and byte-for-byte comparisons; semantic equality is explicitly insufficient because JavaScript and Rust may differ in floating-point reduction order, negative zero, number spelling, object key order, and map iteration. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style-guide/interop-errors-and-parity.md:152-188] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style-guide/interop-errors-and-parity.md:271-312]\\n+\\n+Before any Rust prototype, freeze the supported domain and generate oracle fixtures from TypeScript. Preserve lane iteration order and sequential floating-point accumulation exactly; do not parallelize parity-visible reductions. Require a complete terminal comparator key and canonical boundary serialization. This oracle investment is reusable supporting infrastructure, but it is not independently a reason to ship Rust.\\n+\\n+### F4. Adapter choice follows residency and failure isolation; ranking does not choose it\\n+\\n+For a Node-only, in-process, CPU-bound kernel that demonstrably blocks the event loop, napi-rs is the lowest-friction adapter and can use an async task after measurement. For browser portability, WASM is viable, but the styles database has no browser execution requirement and baseline WASM is single-threaded; Promise bridging does not create CPU parallelism. For a resident model or large ANN process, a sidecar can justify IPC through crash containment, independent RSS lifecycle, model residency, and potentially multi-client service. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style-guide/interop-errors-and-parity.md:190-213] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style-guide/interop-model.md:160-178]\\n+\\n+None of those advantages applies to at most 600 RRF contributions. A sidecar would add framing and process latency, WASM would add packaging without required portability or parallelism, and napi-rs would add native release complexity without a material compute win. If ANN or inference later clears its own gate, its residency determines the adapter and the bounded ranking primitive may travel inside that already-funded boundary.\\n+\\n+### F5. Deterministic hashing and ranking are necessary parity infrastructure for material features, not separate opportunities\\n+\\n+The durable SHA-256 identities and comparator chains protect cache, generation, cursor, and output contracts. Rust must reproduce the exact TypeScript preimage, field order, separators, UTF-8 encoding, hash algorithm, hexadecimal form, numeric reduction order, and terminal tie-break; a semantically similar implementation is not enough. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style-guide/interop-errors-and-parity.md:127-150] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/retrieval.mjs:218-249]\\n+\\n+This makes deterministic primitives a mandatory acceptance layer for any future Rust ANN, inference, or build accelerator. It does not make them a user-visible feature and does not clear residency or materiality at current, 10x, or 100x corpus scale. The scale gates must stay attached to the unbounded or resident work: eligible-vector search, model execution, image preprocessing, or cold-build verification and parsing. Candidate-bounded fusion and native SHA-256 remain TypeScript/Node baselines unless bundled with such a feature and proven byte-identical.\\n+\\n+## Questions Answered\\n+\\n+- **Is deterministic RRF, hashing, or ranking a standalone Rust opportunity?** No. RRF is capped independently of corpus size, hashing is already native, and deterministic primitives add no user capability by themselves.\\n+- **Is a reusable pure core valuable?** Yes, but only as an internal boundary for an independently material Rust component. It is not justification for a shared cross-system search platform.\\n+- **Which adapter should host a deterministic kernel?** The owner workload decides: napi-rs for measured in-process Node CPU work, WASM only for a real portability requirement, and a sidecar for resident-model or ANN isolation. Ranking alone warrants none.\\n+- **What parity work is required?** A pinned TypeScript fixture generator, byte-level expected outputs, exhaustive numeric/order/error cases, sequential parity-visible reductions, and adapter-specific differential tests.\\n+- **Which scale gate clears?** None for standalone fusion or hashing at current, 10x, or 100x. Only the surrounding unbounded or resident feature can clear a gate.\\n+\\n+## Questions Remaining\\n+\\n+- What exact versioned generation-manifest schema atomically binds SQLite, screenshot-derived features, model/profile identity, and a conditional external ANN projection?\\n+- What measured DISCOVER, VERIFY, PARSE_VALIDATE, COMMIT, VECTOR_DRAIN, PUBLISH, query-stage, model-load, and image-processing values clear each current, 10x, and 100x adoption gate?\\n+- Which final ranked opportunity set is unconditional, benchmark-gated, growth-gated, or ruled out?\\n+\\n+## Ruled Out Directions\\n+\\n+- Standalone Rust weighted-RRF package: the kernel is capped at about 600 contributions and adds no capability.\\n+- Cross-system generic ranking core: subsystem policies and ownership contracts are intentionally different.\\n+- Sidecar for bounded ranking: process framing and lifecycle cost exceed the work being isolated.\\n+- WASM as the default styles adapter: there is no browser portability requirement and baseline WASM adds no CPU parallelism.\\n+- Treating semantic deep equality as oracle parity: release equivalence requires TypeScript-authored byte fixtures.\\n+\\n+## Assessment\\n+\\n+- **newInfoRatio:** 0.58\\n+- **Novelty justification:** This iteration proved that candidate caps decouple RRF cost from corpus growth, identified the current test oracle's exact parity gaps, and made adapter selection derivative of an independently material resident or unbounded workload.\\n+- **Confidence:** High on current code bounds, ownership, and parity requirements; medium on future adapter choice because no ANN, multimodal, or cold-build prototype has yet cleared its own measured gate.\\n+\\n+## Next Focus\\n+\\n+Complete the opportunity matrix and phased adoption decision: bind each candidate to current, 10x, and 100x evidence gates, define the minimum multi-artifact generation-manifest contract, and classify deterministic kernels as acceptance infrastructure for only the surviving material features.\\n\",\"additions\":78,\"deletions\":0},{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deltas/iter-009.jsonl\",\"relativePath\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deltas/iter-009.jsonl\",\"type\":\"add\",\"patch\":\"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deltas/iter-009.jsonl\\n===================================================================\\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deltas/iter-009.jsonl\\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deltas/iter-009.jsonl\\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":9,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\\\",\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.58,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"This iteration proved that candidate caps decouple RRF cost from corpus growth, identified the current test oracle's exact parity gaps, and made adapter selection derivative of an independently material resident or unbounded workload.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Pressure-test deterministic ranking kernels, reusable pure-core boundaries, and TS-oracle parity across napi-rs/WASM/sidecar choices.\\\",\\\"graphEvents\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"q-deterministic-core-materiality\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"QUESTION\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Deterministic Rust core materiality\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"FINDING\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"RRF cost is candidate bounded\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-oracle-not-byte-complete\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"FINDING\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Current oracle lacks byte parity\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-adapter-follows-residency\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"FINDING\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Adapter follows owner workload residency\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"c-kernel-supporting-only\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"CLAIM\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Deterministic kernel is supporting infrastructure\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"s-retrieval-rrf-bound\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"SOURCE\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Styles retrieval candidate and fusion contract\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"s-retrieval-test-oracle\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"SOURCE\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Styles weighted RRF test\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"s-rust-parity-standard\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"SOURCE\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Rust differential parity standard\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-bounded-answers-materiality\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"q-deterministic-core-materiality\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"ANSWERS\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-bounded-supports-supporting\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"c-kernel-supporting-only\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"SUPPORTS\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-residency-supports-supporting\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"f-adapter-follows-residency\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"c-kernel-supporting-only\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"SUPPORTS\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-code-supports-bounded\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"s-retrieval-rrf-bound\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"SUPPORTS\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-test-supports-oracle-gap\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"s-retrieval-test-oracle\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"f-oracle-not-byte-complete\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"SUPPORTS\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-standard-supports-oracle-gap\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"s-rust-parity-standard\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"f-oracle-not-byte-complete\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"SUPPORTS\\\"}]}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"q-deterministic-core-materiality\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"QUESTION\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Deterministic Rust core materiality\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"FINDING\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"RRF cost is candidate bounded\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-oracle-not-byte-complete\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"FINDING\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Current oracle lacks byte parity\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-adapter-follows-residency\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"FINDING\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Adapter follows owner workload residency\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"c-kernel-supporting-only\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"CLAIM\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Deterministic kernel is supporting infrastructure\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"s-retrieval-rrf-bound\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"SOURCE\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Styles retrieval candidate and fusion contract\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"s-retrieval-test-oracle\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"SOURCE\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Styles weighted RRF test\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"s-rust-parity-standard\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"SOURCE\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Rust differential parity standard\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-bounded-answers-materiality\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"q-deterministic-core-materiality\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"ANSWERS\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-bounded-supports-supporting\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"c-kernel-supporting-only\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"SUPPORTS\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-residency-supports-supporting\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"f-adapter-follows-residency\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"c-kernel-supporting-only\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"SUPPORTS\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-code-supports-bounded\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"s-retrieval-rrf-bound\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"SUPPORTS\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-test-supports-oracle-gap\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"s-retrieval-test-oracle\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"f-oracle-not-byte-complete\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"SUPPORTS\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-standard-supports-oracle-gap\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"s-rust-parity-standard\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"f-oracle-not-byte-complete\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"SUPPORTS\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-iter009-001\\\",\\\"severity\\\":\\\"P1\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Candidate caps prevent corpus growth from making weighted RRF material\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":9}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-iter009-002\\\",\\\"severity\\\":\\\"P1\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Current RRF tests do not satisfy byte-level TypeScript oracle parity\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":9}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-iter009-003\\\",\\\"severity\\\":\\\"P1\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Adapter selection belongs to the material owner workload, not ranking\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":9}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"invariant\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"inv-iter009-001\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"TypeScript retains routing, feature flags, fallback, cursors, and public response ownership\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":9}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"invariant\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"inv-iter009-002\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Parity-visible floating-point reductions preserve TypeScript order and byte output\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":9}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"ruled_out\\\",\\\"direction\\\":\\\"Standalone Rust weighted-RRF package\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"At most 200 candidates per lane makes fusion bounded independently of corpus size.\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":9}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"ruled_out\\\",\\\"direction\\\":\\\"Cross-system generic ranking platform\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"Subsystem-specific policy and ownership outweigh primitive reuse.\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":9}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"ruled_out\\\",\\\"direction\\\":\\\"WASM or sidecar for bounded ranking\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"No portability, isolation, or residency requirement offsets adapter overhead.\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":9}\\n\",\"additions\":23,\"deletions\":0},{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\",\"relativePath\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\",\"type\":\"update\",\"patch\":\"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\\n===================================================================\\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl\\n@@ -23,4 +23,5 @@\\n {\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration_start\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":8,\\\"executor\\\":{\\\"kind\\\":\\\"cli-opencode\\\",\\\"model\\\":\\\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\\\",\\\"reasoningEffort\\\":null,\\\"serviceTier\\\":null},\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-07-20T05:05:08.853Z\\\"}\\n {\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":8,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\\\",\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.71,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"This iteration found the cross-generation parsed-projection cache as the real missing capability, measured current hashing cost, isolated the safe bounded pre-transaction worker seam, and proved that watcher correctness and external-artifact publication are separate contracts.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Assess content-addressed caches, incremental hashing, parallel streaming corpus indexing, and a Rust file watcher for automatic reindex.\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":5,\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"Which indexing automations materially benefit from Rust today?\\\",\\\"Is a new content-addressed cache useful?\\\",\\\"Does a Rust watcher improve correctness?\\\",\\\"Where must atomicity remain?\\\",\\\"What is the scale gate?\\\"],\\\"ruledOut\\\":[{\\\"approach\\\":\\\"Replace existing content identities with a Rust cache\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"Aggregate, retrieval, generation, and embedding content identities already exist; only cross-generation parsed-projection reuse is missing.\\\"},{\\\"approach\\\":\\\"Replace canonical SHA-256 with BLAKE3\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"Current hashing is not material at present scale and the change would break persisted identity and oracle parity.\\\"},{\\\"approach\\\":\\\"Parallel SQLite publication\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"The single transaction is the correctness boundary; bounded parallelism belongs in verification and parsing.\\\"},{\\\"approach\\\":\\\"Watcher as freshness authority\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"Node, Chokidar, and Rust notify all consume fallible platform events, so authoritative reconciliation remains required.\\\"},{\\\"approach\\\":\\\"Standalone Rust watcher at current scale\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"Chokidar provides normalized atomic and chunked-write handling without a new binary lifecycle.\\\"}],\\\"graphEvents\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"q-index-automation-scale\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"QUESTION\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Index automation by scale\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-projection-cache-gap\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"FINDING\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Parsed projection cache is missing\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-precommit-worker-seam\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"FINDING\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Parallel seam is pre-transaction\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"f-watcher-hints-only-i8\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"FINDING\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Watch events remain hints\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"c-manifest-required-external\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"CLAIM\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"External projections require manifest\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"s-styles-indexer-i8\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"SOURCE\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Styles indexer and publisher\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"s-watcher-docs-i8\\\",\\\"kind\\\":\\\"SOURCE\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Node Chokidar notify watcher docs\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-cache-answers-automation-i8\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"f-projection-cache-gap\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"q-index-automation-scale\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"ANSWERS\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"e-worker-answers-automation-i8\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"f-precommit-worker-seam\